<HEAD>I. [IN DOMINICA PALMARUM.]</HEAD>
<P><I>[Q]uum appropinquasset ihesus ierosolimam &amp; cetera.</I> Gode<MILESTONE N="1a" UNIT="folio"> men hit is an heste dei to dei &thorn;e is on .xii. mon&thorn;e &thorn;is godspel sed hu &thorn;e helend nehlechede to-ward ierusalem &thorn;are burh to dei mid his apostles and ec mid o&eth;ere floc manna &thorn;a he com to &thorn;ere dune oliueti his ihaten &thorn;a sende he is .ii. leornicnihtes and o&thorn;ed<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.,? cwed.</NOTE> to heom God in &thorn;ane castel &thorn;et is on|&yogh;ein eou and &yogh;e finded redliche &thorn;ar ane asse &yogh;e-bunden mid hire colt unbinded heo and leaded heo to me. &yogh;if eniman seid eawiht to eou segged &thorn;et &thorn;e lauerd haued &thorn;ar-of neode and redliche heo eou leted fere &thorn;er-mid. <I>Euntes autem discipuli fecerunt sicut precepit illis ihesus &amp; cetera.</I> &THORN;a apostles eoden and dedeun<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE> alswa &thorn;e helende heom het heo nomen &thorn;e asse and here colt and ledden to him and heo duden heore cla&thorn;es huppon &thorn;e asse fole and ure drihten seod&thorn;an rad &thorn;er-on uppen toward ierusalem &thorn;a wes hit cud ouer al &thorn;e burh &thorn;et &thorn;e helind wes &thorn;iderward. heo urnen on-&yogh;ein him al &thorn;a hebreisce men mid godere heorte and summe mid ufele &thorn;eonke. Moni of &thorn;an floc manna &thorn;e ear&thorn;on fulieden ure drihten and ec &thorn;a &yogh;e-leafulle of &thorn;ere burh heo nomen heore cla&thorn;es and &thorn;e beste &thorn;et heo hefde and strehiten under &thorn;a assa fet &thorn;er drihten rad inne &thorn;e 
<PB REF="00000069.tif" N="5"> weye. him to luue and heri&yogh;inge &thorn;a o&eth;re men &thorn;e reil nefden heo sti&yogh;en uppeon &thorn;e godes cunnes treowe and nomen &thorn;a twigga and &thorn;a blostme and duden under &thorn;e assa fet and bistreweden al &thorn;ane weye him to wur&thorn;scipe<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. wur&thorn;|seipe.</NOTE> and al &thorn;e <MILESTONE N="1b" UNIT="folio">hebreisce folc &thorn;e eode efter him and biuoren him sungun &thorn;isne lofsong hehliche to heringe and cwe&thorn;en. <I>Osanna filio dauid benedictus qui uenit in nomine domini</I>. &thorn;et is he is iblesced &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">? he.</NOTE> &thorn;e her cumet on drihtenes nome. &THORN;us ha hine hereden a &thorn;e &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">? he.</NOTE> rad in et &thorn;an est &yogh;ete &thorn;ere burh &thorn;et &yogh;et me hat. Speciosa porta. &thorn;et his &thorn;et faire &yogh;et me hat hit and seod&thorn;an &thorn;e cristindom wes; nefre ouer .xii. mon&thorn;e nis hit undon bute to dei al &thorn;at folc eode &thorn;ar ford to processiun to munte oliueti; and in al swa. Nu leoue bro&eth;re nu ic eou habbe &thorn;et godspel iseid anfaldeliche nu scule &yogh;e understonden twafaldeliche &thorn;et hit bi-tacnet. &yogh;e iherden er on &thorn;e godspel hu ure drihten sende his .ii. apostles petrum and iohannem on-&yogh;ein &thorn;ene castel &thorn;et heo unbunden &thorn;at assa and hire fole mid hire. and hu hure drihten set uppen &eth;a assa fole. Leoue bro&eth;re and sustre &yogh;e hi hered hu muchel edmodnesce ure drihten dude for us. he mihte ridan &yogh;if he walde on riche stede and palefrai and mule and arabisz nalde he no. na for&thorn;on uppon &thorn;a muchele assa a&yogh;c uppon &thorn;a lutthle fole &thorn;at &yogh;et hit wes sukinde ne ber hit nes nefre nane bur&eth;ene ne hit nes nefere ifuled of nane o&eth;re assa. In swa muchele edmodnesse godalmihti hine dude for us and ec sette us bisne &thorn;a&yogh;<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &thorn;a &yogh;e.</NOTE> habbe wele to ouer stohwennesse on &thorn;isse liue ne beo &thorn;u &thorn;ereuore prud ne wilde ne sterc ne wemod ne ouer modi ah &thorn;es &thorn;e we heoueden mare wele on &thorn;isse liue. &thorn;es we ahte to beon &thorn;e edmoddre. and &thorn;a mare imete al swa hit ure wele nere and &thorn;onkien hit ure drihten &thorn;e hit us lende and don &thorn;an monna &thorn;erof &thorn;at hit nabbet. Godemen &thorn;a &yogh;e-leafule ebreisce folc eoden and streweden mid twigan in drihtenes weye &thorn;er he rad. &thorn;a hit wes ifullet &thorn;et ysaias &thorn;e prophete iwitegede ueale hund wintra er &thorn;is were and cwed.</P>
<P><I>Parate uiam domini rectas facite semitas eius</I>. Rere&eth; up drihtenes wei and makiet his weo&yogh;es rihte. &THORN;et tacnet &thorn;et we sulen habben ure heorte and habben godne ileafe to ure drihten. 
<PB REF="00000071.tif" N="7"> &thorn;e wite&yogh;a het &thorn;et we sculde makien his sti&yogh;es &thorn;enne make we ham rihte &yogh;ef we haldet his beode and &yogh;ef we beod under sod scrifte and god fructe &thorn;urh-ut of alle &thorn;inge. and we luuien ure efrec o&eth;er us bi-twenen swa we weren bro&eth;re and sustre and &yogh;if we &thorn;onkiet ure drihten alles &thorn;inges &thorn;e he us sent. &thorn;et gode and &thorn;et ufele. &yogh;if we &thorn;is do&eth;; &thorn;enne make we rihte and clene godes weies and his sties &thorn;et god almihti mei riden on. &yogh;if we &thorn;is do&eth; &thorn;enne wunet god almihti in us. Al swa ic er cwet hu hure drihten rad to ierusalem &thorn;at ebreisce folc sungen heore leof song ure helende to wur&eth;inge summe hit sungen &thorn;urh &thorn;ene halie gast walden heo naldden heo and &thorn;a children plo&yogh;eden in &thorn;ere strete heriende ure drihten and cwe&thorn;en. <I>Osanna filio dauid</I>. &thorn;is wite&yogh;ede dauid &thorn;e &thorn;e salm scop in &thorn;e saltere muchel erd&thorn;on &thorn;a wile he liuede and cwet. <I>Ex ore infancium &amp; lactancium</I>. &thorn;is he wite&yogh;ede bi drihtene &thorn;urh &thorn;ene halie gast. Drihten &thorn;u dest &thorn;e lof of milc drinkende childre mu&eth;e wu<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &thorn;u.</NOTE> warpest &thorn;ene alde feont for &thorn;ine feonden and &thorn;ine feond &thorn;u bi|scildest. Nu we wulle&eth; seggen mare wet &thorn;is godspel itacnet &thorn;e castel &thorn;e wes a&yogh;eines drih[t]nes twa leornikenehtes; he bi-tacnet &thorn;eos world is whilende and ontful and swi&eth;e lewe. and swinc|ful Ne swincke &thorn;u nefre swa muchel; a hit bi&eth; undon and misliche wederes comet o&eth;er while. and unfrit. and hunger. and licome un-hele al for ure gulte and &thorn;enne &thorn;u wenest &thorn;et &thorn;u scalt libben alre best. &thorn;enne gest &thorn;u for&eth; and o&eth;er cumed for|&thorn;i ne litmie namon to swi&eth;e to &thorn;isse liue. al heo us truket &thorn;er we lest wenet. Ne we ne beo&eth; iboren for to habbene nane prudu ne for&eth;e nane o&eth;re rencas ah we beo&eth; on &thorn;isse liue for to ernien &thorn;a eche blisse in houeneriche. &yogh;e habbet iherd hu god almihti sende his apostles o&yogh;ein &thorn;ene castel efter &thorn;e assa fole &thorn;e wes ibunden and seo&eth;an un-bunden. &thorn;a apostles itacned &thorn;a leorneres &thorn;et beo&eth; &thorn;a wise witega &thorn;e beo&eth; nu ouer &thorn;e halie chirche and libbed gastliche heore lif heo sullen eure un-binden godes folc from &thorn;am deofle <MILESTONE N="2a" UNIT="folio">and heom seggen godes lore hu heo sculen leden heore lif and ernien &thorn;a eche blisse mid ibede and mid scrifte to betende mid festene and mid elmesse and bidden for heom deies and nihtes &thorn;et crist heom milcie of heore 
<PB REF="00000073.tif" N="9"> misdede. &THORN;at<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &thorn;a.</NOTE> assa itacned &thorn;e chirche o&eth;er &thorn;e sinagoga heo wes ibunden on &thorn;a ealde la&yogh;e and nu&eth;a heo is unbunden in &thorn;isse newe la&yogh;e. Godemen wite &yogh;e hwet &thorn;es sinagoge on &thorn;am alde la&yogh;e ere crist were iboren alswa hefden &thorn;e giwis heore sinagoge efter moises la&yogh;e alswa we habbet nu chirche efter drihtenes la&yogh;e and efere to &thorn;am setteres dei heo comen &thorn;a iudeisce folc to settes tima to &thorn;an sinagoge and hereden heore drihten swa heore la&yogh;e wes. &THORN;at wes heore sunedei and bet heo heolden heore wur&eth;ing dei &thorn;ene we do&eth; and &yogh;et do&eth; &thorn;er &thorn;e heo beo&eth;. leofemen alle &thorn;a ileafulle iudeisce men &thorn;e heolden wel heore la&yogh;e and hersumeden heore drihten her he come on &thorn;isse middelerd heo weren iclipet synagoge al swa is nu iclepet al cristen folc. &thorn;a ilke &thorn;a haldet cristes heste. &THORN;a assa &thorn;e wes ibunden and seod&eth;an unbunden &thorn;et itacned &thorn;e sinagoge &thorn;e wes ibunden on &thorn;an alde la&yogh;e. &thorn;et wes al &thorn;et ileafule folc of iudeus heo weren strongliche ibunden er ure drihten come to &thorn;isse liue. heo heofden od&eth;re la&yogh;e &thorn;enne we habbet. &THORN;et wes <MILESTONE N="2b" UNIT="folio">&thorn;a la&yogh;e &thorn;a ilke wrake &thorn;e ic dude &thorn;e; &thorn;u scoldest don me and &yogh;ef &thorn;u sungedest to-ward &thorn;ine drihtene and me hit mihte witen nou&thorn;er gold ne seoluer ne moste gan for &thorn;e. ac me &thorn;e sculde nimen and al to-teon mid horse o&eth;er &thorn;e al to-toruion mid stane. For-&thorn;i leofe bre&eth;re hit is muchel neot &thorn;et we &thorn;onkien ure drihten &thorn;a<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &thorn;at.</NOTE> haued &thorn;a stronge ealde la&yogh;e auulsed mid &thorn;ere newe. Nu ne &thorn;erf<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. &thorn;eif.</NOTE> na mon his sunne mid wite abuggen bute towar[d] crist ane mid scrifte swa him his preost lered al swa his festen. &thorn;e swi&eth;e ouerkimet &thorn;es flesces wlongnesse and chuc<NOTE PLACE="marg">? chirc.</NOTE> &yogh;ong and god to donne &thorn;eruore monie and feole o&eth;re godere werke &thorn;e nu were long eou to telle. A. hu &thorn;enne &yogh;if hwa is swa sunful and mid deofle biuon &thorn;et nulle for his ouer-mo&eth;. o&eth;er for his prude. o&eth;er for his fule heorte wil his scrift ihalden. &thorn;enne segge ic eou to so&eth;e &thorn;et nis hit nan &thorn;erf &thorn;et me her on &thorn;isse liue for his saule bidde pater noster. ne messe singe ne nan o&eth;er god don. A. hu scolde o&eth;ermonnes goddede comen him to gode &thorn;e nefre on &thorn;isse liue nanes godes ne rohte; A. hwa is &thorn;et mei &thorn;et hors wectrien &thorn;e him self nule drinken; Na ma ne mei me her god don for &thorn;ere saule &thorn;e 
<PB REF="00000075.tif" N="11"> on &thorn;isse liue god bi-&yogh;innen nalde. Muchel is us &thorn;enne neod leoue bre&eth;ren wet we on &thorn;isse middelerd liuien sod scrift and swi&eth;e adreden ure monifolde sunne. and &yogh;erne bidden ure milciende drihten &thorn;et he us leue swa libben on <MILESTONE N="3a" UNIT="folio">&thorn;isse scorte liue &thorn;et we moten heonene feren to &thorn;an echeblisse &thorn;e hon wunet. &thorn;e feder. and &thorn;e sune. and &thorn;e halie gast a buten ende. per omnia secula seculorum amen.</P>
