<HEAD>III. [DOMINICA PRIMA IN QUADRAGESIMA.]</HEAD>
<P>[I]n leinten time uwilc mon ga&eth; to scrifte; &thorn;er beo&eth; summe &thorn;e mare herm is &thorn;e ga&eth; al swa ic nu&thorn;e eow tellen wulle. He sei&eth; mi&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg">? mid.</NOTE> &thorn;a mu&eth;e &thorn;et nis naut in his heorte. ic wulle gan to scrifte for scome alswa do&eth; o&eth;er men. &yogh;if ic forlete &thorn;e preost me walde eskien on ester dei hwa me scriue er he me &yogh;efe husul and ec for monne weordes &eth;inge. he ne gad naut to scrifte al swa do&eth; o&eth;er men. Ah al swa he do&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>originally</I> de&eth;.</NOTE> swa &thorn;e swica &thorn;e bi-swike&eth; hine seolfe on-ende and bi&eth; al swa is an eppel iheowe&eth;. he bi&eth; wi&eth;-uten feire and frakel wi&eth;-innen. Awah &thorn;et he efre wulle &thorn;ristelechen o&eth;er bi-&thorn;enchen mid his fule heorte &thorn;e heo wulle underfon swa he&yogh; &thorn;ing and swa hali swa is cristes licome in his sunfulle buke. and wene&eth; &thorn;et hit wulle 
<PB REF="00000091.tif" N="27"> him helpen; Neiso&eth;liche nawiht ah &thorn;enne &thorn;e preost hit de&eth; in his mu&thorn;e. &thorn;enne cume&eth; drihtenes engel and binime&eth; &thorn;a halinesse mid him toward heouene <MILESTONE N="9b" UNIT="folio">riche. &thorn;et &thorn;er bilef&eth; in his mu&eth;e. ah &yogh;if eni mon hit muste isean. he mahte iseon ane berninde glede &thorn;et hine al for-berna&eth; &thorn;urut to cole. Leofemen &yogh;if &thorn;u ert swi&eth;e for-gult wi&eth; &thorn;ine eor&eth;liche lauerd he &thorn;e wule for|beode of his e&yogh;ane on siht.<NOTE PLACE="marg">? a&yogh;ene on|siht.</NOTE> and ec &thorn;u ne derst cumen bi-foren him fore &thorn;ine gulte. Hu der &thorn;e wrecche mon underfon drihtenes fleis and his blod in his licome. hu derst &thorn;u mon &thorn;er on-&yogh;ein underfon drihtenes [fleis] and his blod in &thorn;ine licome imong &thorn;an unwreste sunne and ec imong &thorn;an deofle &thorn;e wune&eth; in him. Mare hit him de&eth; to herme &thorn;enne to gode for hit hine ti&eth; to &thorn;an bittre de&eth;e to helle mare &thorn;enne to &thorn;an eche liue. Swa longe &thorn;e deofle wuna&eth; swa inne &thorn;e sunfulle men a &thorn;et he hine haue&eth; al ifonded to his wille &thorn;urhut. and &thorn;e deofel &thorn;et to so&thorn;e &thorn;e rixat in-nan him &thorn;et he nulle nefre forleten his sunne. He &thorn;en-che&eth; &thorn;e deofel. &thorn;esne mon ic habbe itaken to mine a&yogh;ene bihof&thorn;e.<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. bi|hos&thorn;e.</NOTE> Ma monna ic scolde bi&yogh;eten swa bi hulche monna sei&eth; drihten in his spelle. &thorn;a he &thorn;us cwe&thorn; <I>Cum inmundus spiritus exierit ab homine ambulat per uia[s] inaquosa[s] querens requiem &amp; non inuenit</I> &thorn;e unclene gast &thorn;e ge&eth; him of &thorn;an sunfulle mon and ge&eth; him of &thorn;an stude to stude. and seche&eth; reste hwer he mei wunian. <MILESTONE N="10a" UNIT="folio">ah he ne mei in nane gode men. for&eth;on &yogh;if he bi&eth; wel iscrifen and godfurht ne &thorn;e deofel mey nefre cumen in-ne him for his gode werkes. &thorn;enne cwe&eth; he eft. <I>Reuertar in domum meam unde exiui</I>. Nu ic mot in &thorn;et ilke hus &thorn;et ic er wes. and &thorn;enne fera&eth; he and nime&eth; him. vii. deofle &thorn;e beo&eth; muchele wurse &thorn;enne he. heo fere&eth; swa ic er cwe&eth;. and wunia&eth; in him a mare and swa dreie&eth; his erme saule in eche pine to helle grunde. Er&eth;on he nefde bute enne deofel. nu he haue&eth; sefene. Nu &thorn;ah he walde &thorn;a ufele sunne for-leten; Ne mei he for &thorn;an deoflan. Ah wulche men ilimpe&eth; swa ic habbe er icwe&eth;en; witicrist &thorn;et beo&eth; &thorn;a men &thorn;e ga&eth; to scrifte mare for worl[d]es scome &thorn;enne for heore sunne to beten; and to reusi[e]n. for hwet wule mon et scrifte bute he wulle for leten his misdede. and beten. So&eth;liche &yogh;if &thorn;u wreiest &thorn;e seolfen to 
<PB REF="00000093.tif" N="29"> &thorn;ine scrifte; ne mei &thorn;e deofel &thorn;e wreienson<NOTE PLACE="marg">? wreien on.</NOTE> &thorn;an o&eth;re liue. for &thorn;e mon &thorn;e hele&eth; his sunne a&eth;isse liue ne siht he nefre almihtin drihten. ne nawiht of his blisse. Hu maht &thorn;u iseon &thorn;ine sceadewe in worie watere; Hwet is scrift bute forlete &thorn;ene deofel. and &thorn;ine sunne. and bi-rewsien and beten and wepen. and habben in his &thorn;onke &thorn;e he nule nefre mare eft &yogh;e don &thorn;eo sunnen; &thorn;e he ge&eth; to scrifte <MILESTONE N="10b" UNIT="folio">fore and cumen to &thorn;an preoste and werian<NOTE PLACE="marg">? wreian.</NOTE> hine seolfe. and cwe&eth;en in his &thorn;onke &thorn;ar hi<NOTE PLACE="marg">? he.</NOTE> bi&eth;. Awah; &thorn;et ic hit efre dude mid mine wrechede licome &thorn;as sunnen. for godes luue bete&eth; ower sunnen &thorn;a wile &yogh;e beo&eth; heren on &thorn;isse scorte liue. and i&thorn;enche&eth; hu lutte hw[i]le &yogh;e beo&eth; here. Mid so&eth;e &thorn;us sei&eth; &thorn;e boc. Rubberes.<NOTE PLACE="marg">? rupperes.</NOTE> and &thorn;a reueres. and &thorn;a &thorn;eoues. and &thorn;a mor&eth;sla&yogh;a. and &yogh;itteres. and &thorn;a eawbrekeres. and &thorn;a li&yogh;eres and &thorn;a wohdemeres and &thorn;a iuguleres. and &thorn;a o&eth;er sottes alle heo habbe&eth; an &thorn;onc fulneh. hwet segge&eth; heo. we moten idre&yogh;an ure wil &thorn;e hwile &thorn;e we beo&eth; &yogh;unge. and eft &thorn;enne we beo&eth; eldre bete we hit &thorn;enne weilawei wrecche. &thorn;us cwe&eth; &thorn;e boc. So&eth;liche al swa e&eth;a &thorn;u mihtest neoman &thorn;ine a&yogh;en wepne and smiten of &thorn;in a&yogh;en heaue&eth;. and gan eft to &thorn;in a&yogh;ene liche. hu mahtest &thorn;u gan to &thorn;ine a&yogh;ene liche &yogh;if &thorn;in hefet were offe; Nefre. Alswa nauest &thorn;u nefre milce of heofenlic drihten; &yogh;if &thorn;u eart inumen in &thorn;on ilke &thorn;onke. on enelpi luttele hwile mon mei underfon ane wunde on his licome; &thorn;et ne mei beon longe hwile hal. And o&eth;er hwile hit is on wane of his hele. &thorn;a lutle hw[i]le &thorn;u ha dest ha &thorn;e &thorn;unche&eth; fulgod. and ful swete. and eft wite crist heo is ful biter<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. bicer.</NOTE> to betene, and o&eth;er hwile hit itit &thorn;et &thorn;u heo nefre ne ibettest on &thorn;isse liue. hwet <MILESTONE N="11a" UNIT="folio">wene&eth; &thorn;as ruperes and &thorn;as reueres &thorn;et neme&eth; o&eth;res monnes eahte mid wohe. &thorn;et crist heom wulle milcien &thorn;ah heo habbe&eth; inumen and heom bi-&yogh;eten freondscipe et &thorn;on monnen; &thorn;et heo a-gult habbe&eth;; nei. hwet &thorn;enche&eth; heo &thorn;us ic wulle bi-&yogh;eten mid wohe. &thorn;a hwile ic mei. and seo&eth;an ic wulle gan to scrifte. and forleten and festen &thorn;er fore. he haue&eth; &thorn;es deofles costes. &thorn;et a feste&eth; and a de&eth; uuel. &thorn;us ha &thorn;enche&eth; &thorn;et heo wulle&eth; bi&yogh;eten; and nawiht a&yogh;efen ah so&eth;liche al he hit mot a&yogh;efen &yogh;if he hit haue&eth;. and &yogh;if he hit naue&eth; a&yogh;efe swa muchel swa he mei and for&yogh;euenesse 
<PB REF="00000095.tif" N="31"> weorne<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &YOGH;eorne.</NOTE> bidde et &thorn;an ouereake &thorn;is him wule &thorn;unche swi&eth;e strong and swi&eth;e scondful &thorn;et he scal al a-&yogh;euen and seod&eth;an bisechen milce et &thorn;an ilke monne &thorn;e he haue&eth; er istolen o&eth;er o&eth;er-weis wa idon. Blu&eth;eliche &thorn;e mon wile gan to scrifte and segge &thorn;e preoste &thorn;et he haue&eth; ireaue&eth; and istolen. and blu&eth;eliche he wule herkien. &thorn;et &thorn;e preost him lei&eth; on; ah &thorn;enne &thorn;e preost hine hat a&yogh;efen &thorn;a ehte &thorn;on monne &thorn;et hit er ahte. &thorn;et he nulle iheren his &thorn;onkes. ah he wile seggen. and foxliche sme&thorn;ien mid worde. Nabbe ic nawiht &thorn;er-of ic hit habbe al ispened &thorn;us sei&eth; &thorn;enne &thorn;e preost &thorn;er on&yogh;ein. God mon nim &thorn;u nu&eth;e of &thorn;in a&yogh;en ehte and do &thorn;er on&yogh;ein. hit mei ilimpen &thorn;et he wile seggen &thorn;ah ic hefde al &thorn;et<MILESTONE N="11b" UNIT="folio">ic efre bi&yogh;et ne mahtic &yogh;elden swa muchel swa ic habbe idon to herme. witecrist he mot a&yogh;euen al swa muchel swa he mei. for&eth;on moni mon hit walde him for&yogh;euen half o&eth;er &thorn;ridde lot &thorn;enne he ise&yogh;e &thorn;et he ne mahte na mare &yogh;e-for&eth;ian. Hit mei ilimpen &thorn;et he wile seggen &thorn;am preoste. Lauer&eth; nat ic hwer heo beo&eth; &thorn;eo men &thorn;e ic &thorn;ene herm to dude. Summe beo&eth; deade and summe on o&eth;re stude. ne ic cume to heom nawiht. So&eth;liche &thorn;us cwe&thorn;e&eth; &thorn;e boc he mot ham isecham.<NOTE PLACE="marg">? isechan.</NOTE> &yogh;if he wat to so&eth;e &thorn;et heo beo&eth; liues. and &thorn;ene preost he mot isechen &thorn;e hine acursede. &thorn;et he hine iblecie on&yogh;ein &thorn;et he hine acursede. and &yogh;if he nat to so&eth;e &thorn;et heo beo&eth; liues &thorn;a men ne &thorn;e preost; cume &thorn;enne to &thorn;er ilke chirche