<HEAD>IV. IN DIEBUS DOMINICIS.</HEAD>
<P>[L]eofemen &yogh;ef &yogh;e lusten wule&eth;. and &yogh;e willeliche hit under|stonden we eow wulle&eth; <MILESTONE N="16a" UNIT="folio">suteliche seggen of &thorn;a fredome &thorn;e limpe&eth; to &thorn;an deie &thorn;e is iclepe&eth; su<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE> sunedei. Sunedei is ihaten &thorn;es lauerdes dei and ec &thorn;e dei of blisse and of lisse and of alle|irest. On &thorn;on deie &thorn;a engles of heofene ham iblissie&eth;. for&eth;i &thorn;e &thorn;a erming saulen habbe&eth; rest of heore pine. Gif hwa wule witen hwa erest bi-won reste &thorn;am wrecche saule to so&thorn;e ic eow segge. &thorn;et wes sancte paul &thorn;e apostel and mihhal &thorn;e archangel heo tweien eoden et sume time in to helle alswa heom drihten het for to lokien hu hit &thorn;er ferde. Mihhal eode bi-foren and paul com efter and &thorn;a scawede mihhal to sancte paul &thorn;a wrecche sun|fulle &thorn;e &thorn;er were wuniende &thorn;er-efter he him sceawede he&yogh;e treon eisliche beorninde et-foren helle &yogh;ete. and uppon &thorn;an treon he him sceawede &thorn;e wrecche saulen a-honge. Summe bi &thorn;a fet. summe bi &thorn;a honden. summe bi &thorn;e tunge. summe bi &thorn;e e&yogh;en. summe bi &thorn;e hefede. summe bi &thorn;er heorte. Seod&eth;an he him sceaude an ouen on berninde fure he warp ut of him seofe leies uwilan<NOTE PLACE="marg">? uwilcan.</NOTE> of seolcu&eth;re heowe &thorn;e alle weren eateliche to bihaldene and muchele strengre &thorn;en eani &thorn;urg to &thorn;olien. and &thorn;er wi&eth;-innen weren swi&eth;e feole saule a-honge. &yogh;ette he him sceawede ane welle of fure and alle hire stremes<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. strenies.</NOTE> urnen fur berninde. and &thorn;a welle bi-wisten .xii. meister <MILESTONE N="16b" UNIT="folio">deoflen swilc ha weren kinges to pinen &thorn;er wi&eth;innen &thorn;a earming saulen &thorn;e for-gult weren; and heore 
<PB REF="00000107.tif" N="43"> a&yogh;ene pine neure nere &thorn;e lesse &thorn;ah heo meistres weren. Efter &thorn;on he him sceawede &thorn;e sea of helle and innan &thorn;an sea weren .vii. bittere u&thorn;e. &thorn;e forme wes swnan<NOTE PLACE="marg">? snaw.</NOTE>. &thorn;at o&eth;er is. &thorn;et &thorn;ridde fur. &thorn;et feor&eth;e blod. &thorn;e fifte neddren. &thorn;e siste smor&eth;er. &thorn;e seofe&thorn;e ful stunch. heo wes wurse to &thorn;olien &thorn;enne efreni of alle &thorn;a o&eth;re pine. Innan &thorn;an ilke sea weren un-aneomned deor summe fe&eth;er fotetd. Summe al bute fet. and heore e&yogh;en weren al swilc swa fur. and heore e&thorn;em scean swa de&eth; &thorn;e leit a-monge &thorn;unre. &thorn;as ilke nefre ne swiken ne dei ne niht to brekene &thorn;a erming licome of &thorn;a ilca men &thorn;e on &thorn;isse liue her hare scrift enden nalden. Summe of &thorn;an monne sare wepe&eth;. Summe swa deor lude reme&eth;. summe &thorn;er graninde sike&eth;. summe &thorn;er reowliche gne&yogh;e&eth; his a&yogh;ene tunge. Summe &thorn;er wepe&eth;. and alle heore teres beo&eth; berninde gleden glidende ouer heore a&yogh;ene nebbe. and swi&eth;e reowliche ilome &yogh;ei&yogh;e&eth; and &yogh;eorne biseche&eth; &thorn;at me ham ibure&yogh;e from &thorn;am uuele pinan of &thorn;as pinan speked dauid &thorn;e halie wite&yogh;e. and &thorn;us sei&eth;. <I>Miserere nostri domine quia penas inferni sustinere non possumus.</I> Lauerd haue merci of us for&eth;on &thorn;a pinen of helle we ham ne ma&yogh;en i&eth;olien. <MILESTONE N="17a" UNIT="folio">Seo&eth;-&thorn;an he him sceawede and<NOTE PLACE="marg">? ane.</NOTE> stude inne midde-war&eth;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">? midde|warde.</NOTE> helle. and bi-foren &thorn;am ilke stude weren seofen clusterlokan &thorn;ar neh ne mihte nan liuiende mon gan for &thorn;an ufele bre&eth;e and &thorn;er wi&eth;-inna he him sceawede gan on ald mon &thorn;et .iiii. deoflen ledden abuten. &thorn;a escade paul to mihhal hwet &thorn;e alde mon were. &thorn;a cwe&eth; mihhal heh angel he wes an biscop on eo&eth;re liue &thorn;e nefre nalde cristes la&yogh;en lokien ne halden. ofter he walde anuppon his underlinges mid wohe motien and longe dringan &thorn;enne he walde salmes singen o&eth;er eani o&eth;er god don. Herefter iseh paul hwer .iii. deoflen ledden an meiden swi&eth;e unbisor&yogh;eliche; &yogh;eorne escade to mihhal hwi me heo swa ledde. &thorn;a cwe&eth; mihhal. heo wes an meiden on o&eth;er liue &thorn;et wel wiste hire licome in alle clenesse. ah heo nalde nefre nan o&eth;er god don. Elmes&yogh;eorn nes heo nefre. ah prud heo wes swi&eth;e and modi. and li&yogh;ere and swikel. and wre&eth;ful and ontful. and for&eth;i heo bi&eth; wuniende inne &thorn;isse pine. Nu bi-gon paul to wepen wunder|liche. and mihhal heh engel &thorn;er weop for&eth; mid him. &thorn;a com ure drihten of heueneriche to heom on wunres<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &thorn;unres.</NOTE> liche and &thorn;us cwe&eth;. 
<PB REF="00000109.tif" N="45"> Ahwi wepest &thorn;u paul. paul him onswerde. Lauer&eth; ic biwepe &thorn;as monifolde pine &eth;e ic her in helle iseo. &thorn;a cwe&eth; ure lauerd. Ahwi nalden heo witen mine <MILESTONE N="17b" UNIT="folio">la&yogh;e &thorn;e hwile heo weren en eor&eth;e; &thorn;a seide paul him mildeliche to &yogh;eines. Louerd nu ic bidde &thorn;e &yogh;ef &thorn;in wille is &thorn;et &thorn;u heom &yogh;efe rest la hwure &thorn;en sunne dei a &thorn;et cume domes-dei. &thorn;a cwe&eth; drihten to him. paul wel ic wat hwer ic sceal milcien. Ic heom wulle milcien &thorn;e weren efterward mine milce &thorn;a hwile heo on liue weren. &thorn;a wes sancte paul swi&eth;e wa. and abeh him redliche to his lauerdes fet and on halsien hine gon mid &thorn;as ilke weord &thorn;e &yogh;e ma&yogh;en iheren. Lauerd he cwe&eth; &thorn;a. Nu ic &thorn;e bidde for &thorn;ine kinedome and for &thorn;ine engles. and for &thorn;ine muchele milce. and for alle &thorn;ine weorkes. and for alle &thorn;ine hale&yogh;en. and ec &thorn;ine icorene. &thorn;at &thorn;u heom milcie &thorn;es &thorn;e red&thorn;er &thorn;et ic to heom com and reste &yogh;efe &thorn;en sunne-dei a &thorn;et cume &thorn;in heh domes dei. &thorn;a onswerede him drihten mildere steuene. Aris nu paul aris. Ic ham &yogh;eue reste alswa &thorn;u ibeden hauest from non on saterdei a &thorn;a cume monedeis lihting. &thorn;et efre for&eth; to domes dei. Nu leofe bre&eth;re &yogh;e habbe&eth; iher&eth; hwa erest bi-won reste &thorn;am forgulte saule. Nu bi-cume&eth; hit &thorn;erfore to uwilche cristene monne mucheles &thorn;e mare to hali&yogh;en and to wur&eth;ien &thorn;enne dei &thorn;e is icleped sunne-dei. for of &thorn;am deie ure lauerd seolf sei&eth;. <I>Dies dominicus est dies leticie &amp; requiei.</I> <MILESTONE N="18a" UNIT="folio">Sunne dei is dei of blisse and of alle ireste. <I>Non facietur in ea aliquid nisi deum orare manducare &amp; bibere cum pace et leticia</I>. Ne beo in hire na&thorn;ing iwrat bute chirche bisocnie and beode to criste and eoten and drinken mid gri&eth;e and mid gledscipe. <I>Sicut dicitur. pax in terra. pax in celo. pax inter homines.</I> for swa is iset. gri&eth; on eor&eth;e. and gri&eth; on hefene. and gri&eth; bitwenen uwilc cristene monne. eft ure lauerd seolf seit. <I>Maledictus homo qui non cus|todit sabatum</I>. Amansed beo &thorn;e mon &thorn;e sunne-dei nulle iloken. And for-&thorn;i leofemen uwilc sunne-dei is to locan alswa ester dei for heo is mune&yogh;ing of his halie ariste from de&eth;e to liue. and mune&yogh;eing of &thorn;am hali gast &thorn;e he sende in his apostles on &thorn;on dei &thorn;e is icleped wit-sunne-dei. ec we understonde&eth; &thorn;et on sunne dei drihten cume&eth; to demene al mon-cun; we a&yogh;en &thorn;ene sunne dei swi&thorn;eliche wel to wur&thorn;ien. and on alle clenesse to locan. for 
<PB REF="00000111.tif" N="47"> heo haf&eth; mid hire &thorn;reo wurdliche mihte &thorn;e &yogh;e iheren ma&yogh;en. &eth;et forme mihte is &thorn;et heo on eor&eth;e &yogh;eue&eth; reste to alle eor&eth;e &thorn;relles wepmen and wifmen of heore &thorn;rel weorkes. &thorn;et o&eth;er mihte is on heouene. for-&thorn;i &thorn;a engles hem heom rested mare &thorn;enn on sum o&eth;er dei. &thorn;et &thorn;ridde mihte is &thorn;et &thorn;a erming saule habbe&eth; ireste inne helle <MILESTONE N="18b" UNIT="folio">of heore muchele pine. Hwa efre &thorn;enne ilokie wel &thorn;ene sunne dei. o&eth;er &thorn;a o&eth;er halie da&yogh;es &thorn;e mon beot in chirche to lokien swa &thorn;e sunne dei. beo heo dal neominde of heofene riches blisse; mid &thorn;an ferde<NOTE PLACE="marg">? fedre.</NOTE>. and mid &thorn;an sunne. and mid &thorn;an halie gast abuten ende. amen. <I>Quod ipse prestare dignetur qui uiuit &amp; regnat deus</I>. &thorn;er <I>omnia secula seculorum. Amen.</I></P>
