<DIV2 N="5" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>V. HIC DICENDUM EST DE PROPHETA.</HEAD>
<P><I>[M]issus est ieremias in puteum et stetit ibi usque ad os. Qui cum aliquandiu ibi stetisset; debilitatum est corpus eius. &amp; tandem dimissis funibus subtractus est. Et cum eorum duriciam. quia debilis erat sustinere non posset. allati sunt panni de domo regia et circumpositi sunt funibus ne [e]orum duricia lederetuR.</I> Leofemen we uinde&eth; in halie boc. &thorn;et ieremie &thorn;e prophete stod in ane putte. and &thorn;et in &thorn;e uenne up to his mu&eth;e and &thorn;a he hefede &thorn;er ane hwile istonde. &thorn;a bi-com his licome swi&eth;e feble. and me nom rapes and caste in to him fro<NOTE PLACE="marg">? for.</NOTE> to dra&yogh;en hine ut of &thorn;isse putte. Ah his licome wes se swi&eth;e feble; &thorn;et he ne mihte noht i&thorn;olie &thorn;e herdnesse of &thorn;e rapes. &thorn;a sende me cla&eth;es ut of &thorn;es kinges huse for to bi-winden &thorn;e rapes. &thorn;et his licome &thorn;e feble wes ne sceolde noht wursien. Leofemen &thorn;eos ilke weord &thorn;e ic habbe her iseit<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE> habbe&eth; muchele bi-tacnunge <MILESTONE N="19a" UNIT="folio">and god ha beo&eth; to heren and muchele betere to et-halden. Is hit god for to hiheren godes weordes and heom athalden; &yogh;e fuliwis. for ure lauerd godalmihtin sei&eth; in &thorn;an halie godspelle. <I>Beati qui audiunt uerbum &amp; custodiunt illud.</I> &AElig;die and blessede beon alle &thorn;eo &thorn;e ihere&eth; godes weordes and heom athalde&eth;. Nu &yogh;e 
<PB REF="00000113.tif" N="49"> habbe&eth; iherd wulc hit is for to iheren godes weordes and heom ethalden. Nu we sculen heow sceawen hwilc hit is heom for to heren and nawiht for to ethalden. for seint gregori sei&eth;. <I>Melius est uiam ueritatis non agnoscere; quam post agnitam retroire</I>. Betre hit is &thorn;et mon ne iknawe noht &thorn;e wei to godalmihtin &thorn;e he hine icnawe and seod&eth;e hine for-ho&yogh;ie; and on o&eth;er stude he sei&eth;. <I>Qui obturat aures suas ne audiat legem dei; oratio eius erit execrabilis.</I> &THORN;e mon &thorn;e tune&eth; his eren in halie chirche to|&yogh;eines godes la&yogh;e and nule noht iheren &thorn;e weordes &thorn;e of him beo&eth;. his beoden beo&eth; aweriede and unwur&eth;e gode. <I>Puteus est peccati profunditas. quia quam diu stas in luto; tam diu iaces in mortali peccato</I>. &THORN;es put bitacne&eth; deopnesse of sunne. for alse longe alse we ligge&eth; in heue&eth; sunnen; al &thorn;a hwile we sto[n]de&eth; in &thorn;e putte. and &thorn;et in &thorn;e uenne up to &thorn;e mu&eth;e alse &thorn;eos men do&eth; &thorn;e ligge&eth; inne eubruche and ine glutenerie and ine mana&eth;as. and ine prude. and ine o&eth;re fule sunnen. and &thorn;et beo&eth; riche men <MILESTONE N="19b" UNIT="folio">alremest &thorn;e habbe&eth; &thorn;as muchele prude in &thorn;is worlde. &thorn;e habbe&eth; feire huses. and feire hames. feire wifes. and feire children. feire hors and feire cla&thorn;es. heauekes and hundes. castles and tunes. her uppon heo &thorn;enche&eth; muchele mare &thorn;en uppon godalmihtin &thorn;e al &thorn;is heom haue&eth; isend &thorn;a &thorn;e ligge&eth; inne swilc sunne. and ne &thorn;enche&eth; noht for to arisen; heo delue&eth; deihwamliche heore put deoppre and deoppre. <I>vnde propheta. Non claudit super te puteus os suum nisi clauseris os tuum</I>. &thorn;e prophete sei&eth;. &thorn;et &thorn;e put ne tune&eth; noht lihtliche his mu&eth; ouer us bute we tunen ure mu&eth;. ah &yogh;if we tune&eth; ure mu&eth;; &thorn;enne do &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">? we.</NOTE> alse &thorn;e mon &thorn;e delue&eth; ene put feower da&yogh;es o&eth;er fiue and &thorn;enne he haue&eth; hine alra lengest idoluen; &thorn;enne ualle&eth; he &thorn;er inne. &thorn;et him breke&eth; &thorn;e sweore. &thorn;et. is &thorn;et he ualle&eth; in to helle pine &thorn;er neuer eft ne cume&eth; of bote. Ah leofemen godalmihtin haue&eth; isceawe&eth; us wel muchele grace. &thorn;enne he haue&eth; geuen us to beon mud freo. &thorn;et we ma&yogh;en mid ure mu&eth;e bringen us ut of &thorn;isse putte; &thorn;e bitacne&eth; &thorn;eo deop|nesse of sunne. and &thorn;et &thorn;urh &thorn;reo herde weies &thorn;e &thorn;us beo&eth; ihaten. <I>Cordis contricione. Oris confessione. Operis satisfactione</I>. &thorn;ur&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &thorn;urh.</NOTE> heorte bireusunke. &thorn;urh mu&eth;es openunge. &thorn;urh dede wel endinge. <I>Cordis contritione moritur peccatum</I>. <MILESTONE N="20a" UNIT="folio"><I>oris confessione defertur</I> 
<PB REF="00000115.tif" N="51"> <I>ad tumulum. operis satisfactione tumulatur in perpetuum.</I> &thorn;e we beo&eth; sari in ure heorte &thorn;et we isuneged habbe&eth; &thorn;enne slage we ure sunne; &thorn;ene we to sunbote cume&eth;. &thorn;enne do we bi ure sunne al swa me dea&eth; bi &thorn;e deade. for efter&thorn;an &thorn;et &thorn;e mon bi&eth; dead me lei&eth; &thorn;ene licome in &thorn;ere &thorn;ruh. Al swa &thorn;u leist &thorn;ine sunne in &thorn;are &thorn;ruh; hwenne &thorn;u scrift underuongest of &thorn;e sunnen &thorn;e &thorn;u idon hauest to-geines godes wille. &thorn;enne &thorn;u hauest &thorn;ine sunnen ibet; efter &thorn;ines scriftes wissunge. &thorn;enne buriest &thorn;u &thorn;ine sunnen and bringest heom ut of &thorn;ine on-walde. <I>Per ieremiam notatur quilibet peccator qui in suo peccato moram facit</I>. Bi ieremie &thorn;e prophete we a&yogh;en to understonden ulcne mon sunfulle. &thorn;et li&eth; in heuie sunne and &thorn;urh so&eth;e scrift his sunbendes nule slakien. <I>funiculi amaritudines penitencie sig|nificant.</I> &THORN;e rapes &thorn;e weren icast to him; bitacne&eth; &thorn;e herdnesse of scrifte. for nis nan of us se strong &thorn;e hefde idon &thorn;re hefsunnen &thorn;et his licome nere swi&eth;e feble er he hefde idre&yogh;en &thorn;et scrift &thorn;e &thorn;er to bilimpe&eth;. <I>panni circumpositi funibus; ecclesie sacramenta significant quibus penitencie duricia mitigatur</I>. &thorn;as kinges hus bitacne&eth; hali chirch[e &thorn;a] cla&eth;es &thorn;et weren isende ut of &thorn;[es kinges huse] for to binden &thorn;e rapes <MILESTONE N="20b" UNIT="folio">mid; bitacnet &thorn;e halie ureisuns &thorn;e me singe&eth; in halie chirche. and &thorn;e halie sacramens &thorn;e me sacre&eth; in alesnesse of alla sunfulle. Leofemen nu &yogh;e habbe&eth; iher&eth; of &thorn;is putte &thorn;e bitacninge &thorn;e ic habbe embe ispeken. and &thorn;e bitacninge of &thorn;e prophete. and &thorn;et. &thorn;e rapes bitacne&eth;. and hwat &thorn;a cla&eth;es bi-tacne&eth; &thorn;e &thorn;e rapes weren mide biwunden. Ihere&eth; nu&eth;e whulche &thorn;inges wunie&eth; in &thorn;isse putte. &thorn;er wunie&eth; fower cunnes wurmes inne. &thorn;et fordo&eth; nu&eth;e al &thorn;eos midelerd. &thorn;er wunie&eth; in-ne fa&yogh;e neddren. and beore&eth; atter under heore tunge. Blake tadden and habbe&eth; atter uppon heore heorte. &yogh;eluwe froggen. and crabben. Crabbe is an manere of fissce in &thorn;ere sea. &thorn;is fis is of swulc cunde. &thorn;et. euer se he mare streng&eth;de&eth; him to sw[i]mminde mid &thorn;e watere; se he mare swimme&eth; abac. and &thorn;e alde crabbe seide to &thorn;e &yogh;unge. hwi ne swimmest &thorn;u for&eth;war&eth; in &thorn;ere sea alse o&eth;er fisses do&eth;. and heo seide. Leofe moder swim &thorn;u foren me and tech me hu ic scal swimmen for&eth;ward and [heo] bi-gon to swimmen for&eth;ward mid &thorn;e streme. and swam hire &thorn;er 
<PB REF="00000117.tif" N="53"> a&yogh;en. &thorn;as fa&yogh;e neddre bitacne&eth; &thorn;is fa&yogh;e folc &thorn;e wune&eth; in &thorn;isse weorlde. &thorn;e speket alse feire bi-foren heore euencristene <MILESTONE N="21a" UNIT="folio">alse heo heom walde in to heore bosme puten. and swa sone se hi beo&eth; iturnd awey from heom; heom to-twicche&eth; and to-dra&yogh;e&eth; mid ufele weordes. <I>Hii eciam sunt doctores &amp; falsi christiani.</I> &THORN;os men &thorn;e &thorn;us to-dra&yogh;ed heore euencristene bi-hinden heo habbe&eth; &thorn;e nome of cristene ah &thorn;ah heo beo&eth; cristes unwines and beo&eth; monsla&yogh;en for heo sla&yogh;e&eth; heore a&yogh;ene saule. and bringe&eth; heon<NOTE PLACE="marg">? heom.</NOTE> in to &thorn;are eche pine of helle. &thorn;os blaca tadden &thorn;et habbe&eth; &thorn;et atter uppon heore heorte. bi-tacne&eth; &thorn;es riche men &thorn;e habbe&eth; &thorn;es mucheles weorldes ehte and na ma&yogh;en noht itimien &thorn;ar of to eten ne to drinken ne na god don &thorn;er of for &thorn;e luue of god|almihtin &thorn;e haue&eth; hit heom al geuen. ah ligge&eth; &thorn;er uppon alse &thorn;e tadde de&eth; in &thorn;ere eor&eth;e &thorn;et neure ne mei itimien to eten hire fulle; swa heo is afered leste &thorn;eo eor&eth;e hire trukie. &thorn;eos ilke ehte &thorn;e &thorn;eos &thorn;us ouerligge&eth; heom turne&eth; to swart atter for heo falle&eth; &thorn;er &thorn;urh in to &thorn;er stronge pine &thorn;et na mon ne mei tellen. &THORN;eos &yogh;eolewe cla&thorn;es.<NOTE PLACE="marg">? some|thing omitted here.</NOTE> for &thorn;e &yogh;eolewe cla&eth; is &thorn;es deofles helfter.<NOTE PLACE="marg">? helster.</NOTE> &thorn;eos wimmen &thorn;e &thorn;us luuie&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg">? liuie&eth;.</NOTE> beo&eth; &thorn;es deofles musestoch iclepede. for &thorn;enne &thorn;e mon wule tilden his musestoch he binde&eth; uppon &thorn;a swike chese and bret hine for &thorn;on &thorn;et he scolde<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. sclode.</NOTE> swote smelle. and &thorn;urh &thorn;e <MILESTONE N="21b" UNIT="folio">sweote smel of &thorn;e chese; he bicherre&eth; monie mus to &thorn;e stoke. Alswa do&eth; monie of &thorn;as wimmen heo smurie&eth; heom mid blanchet &thorn;et is &thorn;es deofles sape and cla&thorn;e&eth; heom mid &yogh;eoluwe cla&thorn;e &thorn;et is &thorn;es deofles helfter.<NOTE PLACE="marg">? helster.</NOTE> and seod&eth;an heo lokie&eth; in &thorn;e scawere. &thorn;et is &thorn;es deofles hindene. &THORN;us heo do&eth; for to feiren heom seoluen. and to dra&yogh;en lechurs to ham. ah heo fule&eth; heom soluen &thorn;er mide. Nu leofemen for godes lufe wite&eth; how wi&eth; &thorn;es deofles musestoch and wite&eth; eow &thorn;et &yogh;e ne beo noht &thorn;e foa&yogh;e neddre. ne &thorn;e blake tadde. ne &thorn;e &yogh;olewe frogge. &thorn;e feder. and &thorn;e sune. and &thorn;e halie gast. iscilde us &thorn;er wi&eth;. and wi&eth; alle sunnen a buten ende. <I>per omnia secula seculorum. Amen.</I>
</P>

