<DIV2 N="6" TYPE="homily"><PB REF="00000119.tif" N="55">
<HEAD>VI. PATER NOSTER.</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD><I>[P]Ater noster qui es in celis &amp; cetera.</I></HEAD>
<L>Vre feder &thorn;et in heouene is</L>
<L>&thorn;et is al so&eth; ful iwis.</L>
<L>weo moten to &thorn;eos weordes iseon.</L>
<L N="4">&thorn;et to liue and to saule gode beon.</L>
<L>&thorn;et weo beon swa his sunes iborene.</L>
<L>&thorn;et he beo feder and we him icorene.</L>
<L>&thorn;et we don alle his ibeden.</L>
<L N="8">and his wille for to reden.</L>
<L>Loke weo us wi&eth; him misdon</L>
<L>&thorn;urh beelzebubes swikedom.</L>
<L>he haue&eth; to us muchel ni&eth;.</L>
<L N="12">alle &thorn;a deies of ure si&eth;.</L>
<L>abuten us he is for to blenchen.</L>
<L>Mid alle his mihte he wule us swenchen.</L>
<L>Gif we leorni&eth; godes lare;</L>
<L N="16">&thorn;enne of-&thorn;unche&eth; hit him sare.</L>
<L>Bute we bileuen ure ufele iwune.</L>
<L>Ne kepe&eth; he noht <MILESTONE N="22a" UNIT="folio">&thorn;et we beon sune.</L>
<L>Gif we clepie&eth; hine feder &thorn;enne.</L>
<L N="20">al &thorn;et is us to lutel wunne.</L>
<L>halde we godes la&yogh;e.</L>
<L>&thorn;et we habbe&eth; of his sa&yogh;e.</L>
<L>&thorn;a bodes he beode&eth; &thorn;er inne.</L>
<L N="24">Bute weo hes halden; we do&eth; sunne</L>
<L>and uwilc mon hes undernim.</L>
<L>to halden wel anundes him.</L>
<L>for alswa god hit bit;</L>
<L N="28">and inne &thorn;e godspelle &thorn;e he writ.</L>
<L>Luuien god mid ure mihte
<PB REF="00000121.tif" N="57"></L>
<L>ouer alle cunnes wihte</L>
<L>mid ure saule mid ure deden.</L>
<L N="32">ba&thorn;e luuien him and ec dreden.</L>
<L>&thorn;is is &thorn;e furste bode here;</L>
<L>&thorn;et we a&yogh;en to habben deore.</L>
<L>&thorn;eos beode ofer alle o&eth;er is.</L>
<L N="36">Ne habbe we hit noht onimis.<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. onuius.</NOTE></L>
<L>and &thorn;is o&eth;er efter &thorn;is.</L>
<L>&thorn;is is ilich fuliwis.</L>
<L>Luuien &thorn;i cristen euenling.</L>
<L N="40">Alswa &thorn;e seoluen in alle &thorn;ing.</L>
<L>Mid al &thorn;is haue &thorn;u charite.</L>
<L>and so&eth;feste leaue and trow&eth;e lef.</L>
<L>for god let &thorn;u &thorn;et uuele beon.</L>
<L N="44">Godere hele &thorn;u hit scalt iseon.</L>
<L>Ne beo &thorn;u nawiht monslaht.</L>
<L>ne in hordom dei ne naht.</L>
<L>Ne &thorn;u na&yogh;est for to stele.</L>
<L N="48">ne nan &thorn;ef&thorn;e for to heole.</L>
<L>Prud ne wreiere ne beo &thorn;u noht.</L>
<L>Ne ni&eth;ful in &thorn;i &thorn;oht.</L>
<L>beo buhsum toward gode.</L>
<L N="52">and wel hald &thorn;u his bode.</L>
<L>Do &thorn;u &thorn;is mid gode mune.</L>
<L>&thorn;enne eart &thorn;u godes sune.</L>
<L>&thorn;us &thorn;u maht &yogh;if &thorn;u wulle.</L>
<L N="56">godes heste wel ifulle.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD><I>San[c]tificetur nomen tuum.</I></HEAD>
<L>&THORN;i nome beo iblecced. &thorn;et we segge&eth;</L>
<L>and &thorn;us &thorn;a wordes we bi-legge&eth;.</L>
<L>his name is hali and efre wes</L>
<L N="60">iliche swi&eth;e hit nis noht les.</L>
<L>&thorn;et is and wes and efre scal</L>
<L>beon iblecced ofer al.</L>
<L>&thorn;enne a&yogh;e we to <MILESTONE N="22b" UNIT="folio">understonden us</L>
<L N="64">from alle uuele he scal blecen us.
<PB REF="00000123.tif" N="59"></L>
<L>To blecen &thorn;enne inoh his nome</L>
<L>an&eth; kepen us from hearm and scome.</L>
<L>In &thorn;e font we weren eft iboren</L>
<L N="68">iclensed and to gode icorene.</L>
<L>his halie nome we nomen and beren.</L>
<L>In &thorn;e font &thorn;er we iclensed weren.</L>
<L>Cristen beo&eth; icleped riche and lo&eth;.<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE></L>
<L N="72">efter crist seolf &thorn;et is god.</L>
<L>his nome. &thorn;et. we of him hafen.</L>
<L>he hit hale&yogh;e &thorn;et we crauen.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD><I>Adueniat regnum tuum.</I></HEAD>
<L>Cume &thorn;i riche we segge&eth; hit.</L>
<L N="76">Hercni&eth; alle to &thorn;is writ.</L>
<L>his riche is al &thorn;is middeleard.</L>
<L>Eor&eth;e and heofene and uwilcherd</L>
<L>ofer alle is his muchele mihte.</L>
<L N="80">lauerd he is icleped mid rihte.</L>
<L>Lauerd he is of alle scafte.</L>
<L>In eor&eth;e. in heuene is his mahte</L>
<L>alle &thorn;e scafte &thorn;e he bi-gon.</L>
<L N="84">&thorn;et is &thorn;et sod&eth;e hit wes for mon</L>
<L>alle &thorn;inge he makede &aelig;t<NOTE PLACE="marg">it may be <I>aft</I>.</NOTE> agan.</L>
<L>Er he efre makede mon.</L>
<L>he makede mon i rihtwisnesse.</L>
<L N="88">Onlete on his onlichnesse.</L>
<L>Alle dor and fu&yogh;el ifliht;</L>
<L>lete he makede adunriht.</L>
<L>&thorn;ene Mon he lufede and welbi&thorn;ohte.</L>
<L N="92">and for-&thorn;i his neb upward he wrohte.</L>
<L>&thorn;et wes al mid muchele skile;</L>
<L>&YOGH;if he<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &yogh;e.</NOTE> hit understondon wile.</L>
<L>Neb upwardes he him wrohte.</L>
<L N="96">he walde &thorn;et he of him &thorn;ohte</L>
<L>&thorn;et he lufede him mid &thorn;oht[e].</L>
<L>Al swa &thorn;e lauerd &thorn;et him wrohte.</L>
<L>&thorn;enche&eth; nu men hwilch wur&eth;in[g]
<PB REF="00000125.tif" N="61"></L>
<L N="100">eow haue&eth; idon &thorn;e heouenking;</L>
<L>To bon in heuene fuliwis.</L>
<L>In tou&thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">? In to &thorn;e.</NOTE> sete of para[d]is.</L>
<L>from hwonne &thorn;e engles a-dun follon<NOTE PLACE="marg">? fellen.</NOTE></L>
<L N="104">in to <MILESTONE N="23a" UNIT="folio">&thorn;e &thorn;osternesse hellen.</L>
<L>&thorn;et secle<NOTE PLACE="marg">? setle.</NOTE> swa ho radden &thorn;us;</L>
<L>&thorn;er god scal herber&yogh;en us.</L>
<L>Crist us &yogh;ife &thorn;ider to cumen.</L>
<L N="108">and efre mid him solue to wunen.</L>
<L>and cristes wille bo us bitwon.</L>
<L>neb wi&eth; neb for him to son.</L>
<L>and wunen mid him niht</L>
<L N="112">and dei up in heouene &thorn;e is swa briht.</L>
<L>&thorn;et he beo feder and we beo sunes.</L>
<L>to him is ure al to cumes.</L>
<L>&thorn;et is ure e&eth;ele and ure riche;</L>
<L N="116">Mid him to wunen in heouene riche.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD><I>Fiat uoluntas tua. sicut in celo &amp; in terra.</I></HEAD>
<L>&thorn;in a&yogh;en wille beo for &thorn;et segge we.</L>
<L>In or&eth;e in heuene swa hit beo</L>
<L>Al swa is in heouene &thorn;in a&yogh;en wil.</L>
<L N="120">&THORN;et we<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. &thorn;e.</NOTE> &thorn;eowen lauerd al mid skil.</L>
<L>For to beon lauerd &thorn;ine archangles.</L>
<L>and &thorn;i leoue hali engles.</L>
<L>&thorn;a &thorn;e angles. of heouene uolle</L>
<L N="124">for heore prude in to helle.</L>
<L>&thorn;a o&eth;re weren fulfeste sone.</L>
<L>&thorn;et ho ne mihten nefre mare misdone.</L>
<L>Sod&eth;on ne mihten sunegenen<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE> nan;</L>
<L N="128">ne ut of godes wille gan.</L>
<L>Ne mu&yogh;en heo nefre ufele swinken;</L>
<L>ne for men enes hit bi-&thorn;inken.</L>
<L>God us &yogh;efe in horte to fon;</L>
<L N="132">&thorn;et we ne &thorn;enchen ufel to don.</L>
<L>and &yogh;ife us to him god iwil;</L>
<L>and to alle men; riht and skil.
<PB REF="00000127.tif" N="63"></L>
<L>and &yogh;ife us swa his wil to donne;</L>
<L N="136">&thorn;et we gode likie and monne.</L>
<L>and &thorn;et he fulle us mid his mihte</L>
<L>and mid his halie gast us lihte.</L>
<L>and in cherite to wnien inne;</L>
<L N="140">&thorn;et we ne fallen naut ine sunne.</L>
<L>&thorn;et we nabben wil to sunegen.</L>
<L>&thorn;enne ure unwines us munegen.</L>
<L>Ne mare &thorn;ene &thorn;o engles <MILESTONE N="23b" UNIT="folio">efden</L>
<L N="144">&thorn;et in godes luue heo heom lende.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD><I>Panem nostrum cotidianum da nobis hodie.</I></HEAD>
<L>Gif us to dei ure deies bred.</L>
<L>Lauerd god al ure red.</L>
<L>Gif us ure liuena&eth;;</L>
<L N="148">and to &thorn;e flesce scrud and cla&eth;.</L>
<L>Bred on grikisce is;</L>
<L>Larspel to us fuliwis</L>
<L>for alse me fet &thorn;et fleis wi&eth;-uten</L>
<L N="152">mid mete mid cla&eth;e al abuten;</L>
<L>swa bi-houe&eth; &thorn;e saule fode;</L>
<L>mid godes wordes mid gode mode.</L>
<L>Godes songes beo&eth; alle gode.</L>
<L N="156">to &thorn;ere saule heo senden fode.</L>
<L>We hit a&yogh;en to &yogh;eme.</L>
<L>and god solf &thorn;er mid iqueme.</L>
<L>&thorn;enne mei ure saule lifen.</L>
<L N="160">&thorn;et ure lauerd us haue&eth; i&yogh;euen.</L>
<L>&thorn;e luste nulle&eth; &thorn;esne red</L>
<L>wisliche he scal wur&eth;en ded</L>
<L>for &thorn;e saule of him; is forloren.</L>
<L N="164">and &thorn;e sor&yogh;e is him biforen.</L>
<L>and fere&eth; in to helle mid eche wa;</L>
<L>ut ne cume&eth; he nefre ma.</L>
<L>Ah lauerd god her ure bone.<NOTE PLACE="marg">? bene.</NOTE></L>
<L N="168">of ure sunne make us clene.</L>
<L>&thorn;et he us &yogh;eue alswa he mei;
<PB REF="00000129.tif" N="65"></L>
<L>&thorn;et us bihoue&eth; ulche dei.</L>
<L>To liue and to saule ure fode</L>
<L N="172">and him luuien mid clene mode.<NOTE PLACE="inter"><I>Et dimitte nobis debita nostra sicut et nos dimittimus debitoribus nostris</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Vre gultes lauerd bon us for&yogh;euen</L>
<L>al swa we do&thorn; alle men &thorn;et liuen.</L>
<L>Lauerd for&yogh;ef us ure unskile</L>
<L N="176">and alswa we alle o&eth;re wile.</L>
<L>ure sunnen. and ure misdonning.</L>
<L>and her is a roulich moting.</L>
<L>to gode solf we us wrei&eth;;</L>
<L N="180">hwenne we &thorn;os word segge&eth;.</L>
<L>hwenne we habbe&eth; ni&eth; and onde;</L>
<L><MILESTONE N="24a" UNIT="folio">to eni monne &thorn;et is on londe.</L>
<L>for &yogh;if eni mon mis-de&eth; us oht;</L>
<L N="184">we wulle&eth; him habben to de&eth;e ibroht.</L>
<L>her is swi&thorn;e ufel bone;</L>
<L>&yogh;if we hetie&eth; us bitwene.</L>
<L>&yogh;if eni us misdo&eth; awiht;</L>
<L N="188">and nule us do riht.</L>
<L>for godes luue for&yogh;eue we al;</L>
<L>for he hit wel for&yogh;elden scal.</L>
<L>Wenne scal &thorn;os bode<NOTE PLACE="marg">? beode.</NOTE> us god don;</L>
<L N="192">and god wule hit underfon.</L>
<L>wenne ic for&yogh;eue min hating;</L>
<L>for &thorn;e luue of heuene king.</L>
<L>Wenne ic ileue and wel iso;</L>
<L N="196">&thorn;et no gult me for&yogh;euen bo.</L>
<L>for hwenne ic i-halde &thorn;a ibode;</L>
<L>&thorn;et we habbe&eth; of ure lauerd gode.</L>
<L>luue &thorn;ine euecristene dei and niht;</L>
<L N="200">alswa &thorn;e solue and &thorn;et is riht.</L>
<L>Gif we &thorn;os bode &thorn;us bilegge&eth;;</L>
<L>ful<NOTE PLACE="marg">? for.</NOTE> goderhele we hit segge&eth;.</L>
<L>&thorn;e pater noster bi-halt me noht;
<PB REF="00000131.tif" N="67"></L>
<L N="204">bute ic &thorn;is habbe in mi &thorn;oht.</L>
<L>&thorn;enne mu&yogh;e we wenen and seggen &thorn;us;</L>
<L>&thorn;et o&eth;er swi&eth;e lutel helpe&eth; us.</L>
<L>&thorn;os ilke bode wisliche &thorn;ing;</L>
<L N="208">of o&eth;re is ful festning.</L>
<L>&thorn;enne mu&yogh;e we wel trowen al;</L>
<L>hwa swa wile and hwa swa scal.</L>
<L>&thorn;et wi&eth; gode awiht mis-do&eth;;</L>
<L N="212">Iwis in &thorn;e bode he misfo&eth;.</L>
<L>&thorn;et hetunge habbe&eth; hom bitwone;</L>
<L>hu ma&yogh;en heo bidden eni bene.</L>
<L>for-&yogh;if &thorn;i wre&eth;&eth;e and &thorn;i mod;</L>
<L N="216">for &thorn;enne is &thorn;i bode god.</L>
<L>&thorn;et is so&eth; and god sei&eth; hit;</L>
<L>and in &thorn;e godspelle he hit writ.</L>
<L>hwa swa ne for&yogh;efe&eth; heore hating.</L>
<L N="220">ne god ne for&yogh;eue&eth; him<NOTE PLACE="marg">? heom.</NOTE> na &thorn;ing.</L>
<L>Gode men luste&eth; to me. ower hating</L>
<L>for&yogh;efe &yogh;e &thorn;in sunful efenling;</L>
<L>luue him for godes &thorn;ing.</L>
<L N="224">and &thorn;u a&yogh;est <MILESTONE N="24b" UNIT="folio">to hatien wel his sunne;</L>
<L>&thorn;et &eth;u ne dele noht &thorn;er inne.</L>
<L>for &yogh;ef &thorn;u &thorn;us dost wel iwis;</L>
<L>&thorn;u quemest god to fuliwis.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD><I>Et ne nos inducas in temptationem.</I></HEAD>
<L N="228">Ne led us noht in to costnunga;</L>
<L>&thorn;et is an cum<NOTE PLACE="marg">? cun.</NOTE> of fundunga.</L>
<L>for ure fond nefre ne linnen;</L>
<L>for to fonden us mid sunnen.</L>
<L N="232">he haue&eth; leue to fonden mon.</L>
<L>&thorn;er he mei ful wel he con.</L>
<L>he fondede god solf mid his wrenche;</L>
<L>and walde hine &yogh;orne swenche.</L>
<L N="236">and his apostles riht al swa;</L>
<L>and monie o&eth;re &thorn;ere to.</L>
<L>God us &yogh;efe mihte and deden;
<PB REF="00000133.tif" N="69"></L>
<L>&thorn;et we &thorn;ene fond noht ne adreden.</L>
<L N="240">and &yogh;efe us mihte &thorn;urh his held;</L>
<L>&thorn;et ure leue beo ure sceld</L>
<L>a&yogh;ein &thorn;es fondes fondunge;</L>
<L>&thorn;urh trow&thorn;e and &thorn;urh swincunge.</L>
<L N="244">On o&eth;er wise ic habbe ifunde</L>
<L>hu me mei in sunne bon ibunde.</L>
<L>&thorn;et forme is to beon underling.</L>
<L>and &thorn;et o&eth;er is liking.</L>
<L N="248">&thorn;et &eth;ridde is &thorn;es monnes wil.</L>
<L>and swa us sei&eth; ure skil.</L>
<L>Crist us &yogh;eue of him mihte</L>
<L>betere &thorn;enne we habbe&eth; wrihte.</L>
<L N="252">We ne ma&yogh;en &thorn;e fond from us driue;</L>
<L>ne mid sworde ne mid kniue.</L>
<L>bute hit beo &thorn;urh godes &yogh;ifte;</L>
<L>and he us &yogh;eue strein&eth;e and mihte.</L>
<L N="256">and &yogh;eue us wepne for to boren;</L>
<L>Mid gode werkes for us to weren.</L>
<L>&thorn;et is &thorn;urh trou&eth;e; and &thorn;urh cherite.</L>
<L>vre rihte leue god cume to &thorn;e</L>
<L N="260">&thorn;urh festing and &thorn;urh wacunge.</L>
<L>and ec &thorn;urh ibodenes biddunge.</L>
<L>and wunien efre in clene scrifte;</L>
<L>&thorn;et is godes a&yogh;ene &yogh;eifte.</L>
<L N="264">and halde we us from uniwil;</L>
<L>and habben feir lete and ec skil.</L>
<L>and edmodnesse and &thorn;olemod;</L>
<L>&thorn;et &thorn;unche&eth; gode swi&eth;e god.</L>
<L N="268">Mid elmesse and ec <MILESTONE N="25a" UNIT="folio">mid trowe inhed;</L>
<L>&thorn;e node habbe&eth; &yogh;iuen heom red.</L>
<L>Mid hereber&yogh;e. and mid fode;</L>
<L>and mid &thorn;et &thorn;u miht to gode.</L>
<L N="272">&thorn;os beo&eth; &thorn;a wepne &thorn;et beo&eth; gode;</L>
<L>and beo we swi&thorn;e &thorn;olemode.</L>
<L>&thorn;et we &thorn;enne fond noht ne dreden.
<PB REF="00000135.tif" N="71"></L>
<L>ne he us biswike &thorn;urh his deden.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD><I>Sed libera nos a malo. Amen.</I></HEAD>
<L N="276">ac &thorn;u from alle ufele us ales.</L>
<L>and to &thorn;in a&yogh;en us ches;</L>
<L>and kep us from his waning.</L>
<L>&thorn;at la&thorn;e gast &thorn;et la&eth;e &thorn;ing.</L>
<L N="280">and from uuele men kep us swa;</L>
<L>Al &thorn;et we bidde&eth; ec &thorn;erto.</L>
<L>And from iwilch heued sunne.</L>
<L>&thorn;et he ne bringe us in to unwune.</L>
<L N="284">Ac &yogh;if us eni ufel bitit;</L>
<L>&thorn;onke we gode in ure wit.</L>
<L>We a&yogh;en &thorn;enne ure boden to singe.</L>
<L>&thorn;et god us helpe to gode &thorn;inge.</L>
<L N="288">&thorn;et lif and saule beon ibor&yogh;en.</L>
<L>and ba&eth;e ilesed ut of sor&yogh;en.</L>
<L>and &yogh;efe us his muchele blessunge.</L>
<L>and riht scrift et ure endunge.</L>
<L N="292">&thorn;et we habben him swa wel imune.<NOTE PLACE="marg">? inume.</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;et &thorn;e saule mote to him cume.</L>
<L>Vre de&eth; he do in firste &yogh;et;</L>
<L>swa he &thorn;urh &thorn;e witega bihet.</L>
<L N="296">Ne wille ic noht &thorn;et &thorn;e sunfulle beo ded;</L>
<L>ac libbe and nime godne red.</L>
<L>Lauerd god we bidde&eth; &thorn;us</L>
<L>mid edmode heorte &yogh;if hit us.</L>
<L N="300">&thorn;et ure saule beo to &thorn;e icore.</L>
<L>Noht for &thorn;e flesce for-lore.</L>
<L>&thorn;ole us to bi-wepen ure sunne;</L>
<L>&thorn;et we ne steruen noht &thorn;er inne.</L>
<L N="304">And &yogh;if us lauerd &thorn;et ilke &yogh;ifte;</L>
<L>&thorn;et we hes ibeten &thorn;urh halie scrifte. Amen.
</L>
</LG>

