<DIV2 N="7" TYPE="homily"><PB REF="00000137.tif" N="73">
<HEAD>VII. [CREDO.]</HEAD>
<P><I>[T]ria sunt hominum saluti nescessaria. fides. baptissmus. mundicia uite.</I></P>
<P>&THORN;ro &thorn;ing bod &thorn;et ech .Mon. habbe mot &thorn;et wile his cristindom<MILESTONE N="25b" UNIT="folio"> fole&yogh;e. &thorn;et an is rihte ileue. &thorn;et o&eth;er; fulluht. &thorn;et &eth;ridde; feir lif to leden on &thorn;isse liue. he nis noht fulliche cristene mon &thorn;et is awiht wone of &thorn;isse &thorn;reo &thorn;ing. of ileue spek ure drihten ine &thorn;e hali godspel and sei&eth;. <I>Qui non crediderit condempnabitur</I>. &thorn;e mon. &thorn;et naue&eth; rihte ileue mid him. he wurh<NOTE PLACE="marg">? wur&eth;.</NOTE> idemed to &thorn;olien wawe mid douelen in helle. on o&eth;er stude of rihte ileue spec &thorn;e apostle and sei&eth;. <I>Inpossibile est hominem sine fide posse deo placere</I>. Ne mei na man do &thorn;ing &thorn;et beo god iqueme. bute he habbe rihte ileue mid him. of &thorn;e halie fulht spec ure drihten on o&eth;er stude and sei&eth;. <I>Nisi quis renatus</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">Much rubbed in MS.</NOTE> <I>fuerit ex aqua &amp; spiritu sancto non potest introire in regnum celorum.</I> Ne mei na .Mon. cume in to godes riche bote he beo ifulhted. of clene liflade spec &thorn;e prophete isaias and &thorn;us sei&eth;. <I>Lauamini mundi estote</I>. wasche&eth; ou; and wonie&eth; clene. and dauid &thorn;e prophete speke&eth; in an salm of clene lif and sei&eth;. <I>Asperges me domine isopo &amp; mundabor</I> bi-spreng me lauerd mid buhsum|nesse; &thorn;enne wur&eth;e ic clene. <I>&amp; alibi. Delicto meo munda me domine.</I> and on o&eth;er stude he sei&eth;. lauerd clense me of alle mine fule sunnen. and &thorn;eh alle men beon of hore sunnen iclensed <MILESTONE N="26a" UNIT="folio">et<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. ec.</NOTE> &thorn;e fulht; no&thorn;eles heo a&yogh;en for to cumen<NOTE PLACE="marg">? cunnen.</NOTE> heore bileue. onforward &thorn;os cristendomes ech man leornede his bileue er he fulht underfenge. Ah &thorn;a weren monie childre dede fulhtles. and forlorne. &thorn;er fore hit wes iloked bi godes wissunge ine halie chirche. &thorn;et mon scule childre fulhten and heore godfaderes and heore godmoderes scullen onswerie for hem et &thorn;e chirche dure and beo in bor&yogh;es et &thorn;e fonstan &thorn;et heo sculen beon bi-lefulle .Men. and heore bileue cunnen; wenne heo lorne mu&yogh;e. and &thorn;is ne mei &thorn;e godfadres ne &thorn;e 
<PB REF="00000139.tif" N="75"> godmodres don; buten heo cunnen heore bileue. &thorn;et is. pater noster. and credo. Ne na .Mon. nah him solue wernen henne<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &thorn;enne.</NOTE> .Mon. him for node &thorn;er to bide. &thorn;er fore we willen biginne ure larspel of bileue. &thorn;et rihte ileue setten &thorn;e twelue apostles on write er heo to-wenden in to al &thorn;is middelerd. and ec of heom wrat &thorn;er of his uers. and sancte peter wrat &thorn;et ereste. and &thorn;e salm &thorn;et heo alle &thorn;us writen wes ihaten. Credo. efter &thorn;an formeste word of &thorn;e salm. Alle &yogh;e kunnen leste &thorn;et ich wene ower credo. &thorn;eh &yogh;e nuten nawiht alle hwat hit sei&eth;. Nume&eth; nu &yogh;eme &thorn;erto and ic ou wile seggen word efter word and &thorn;ermide hwat &thorn;et word bi-que&thorn;. &THORN;is word. credo. Mon mei understonden. on &thorn;ro wise. &thorn;et on is; Credo deo. Ih ileue gode. &thorn;et o&eth;er is; Credo deum. ich ileue &thorn;et god is. &thorn;os twa &thorn;ing do&eth; alle he&eth;ene men. ah &thorn;et [&thorn;ridde] ne leue&eth; nan; bute &thorn;e gode cristene .Mon. and &thorn;e godfurhte and &thorn;e lefulle <MILESTONE N="26b" UNIT="folio"><I>qui credit in deum</I>. &thorn;e bileued in god. and to luuene<NOTE PLACE="marg">? leuene.</NOTE> ine god; mote fif &thorn;ing. <I>Silicet. eum dominum omnium cognoscere. super omnia diligere. pre omnibus timere. &amp; uenerari eique per omnia obedire.</I> &THORN;et an is iknawen him to lauerd ouer alle &thorn;ing. &thorn;et o&eth;er is luuien him ouer alle &thorn;ing. &thorn;et &thorn;ridde is; habben heie of him ouer alle &thorn;ing. &thorn;et for&thorn;e is; wur&thorn;en him ouer alle &thorn;ing. &thorn;et fifte is; beon him ibucsum ouer alle &thorn;ing. &THORN;e .Mon. &thorn;et haue&eth; &thorn;is ilke fif &thorn;ing mid him; he is leful .Mon. and if him is eni &thorn;er of wane; he nis nawiht alse leful alse him bi-houede. <I>Credo in deum</I>. Ic ileue in god. <I>patrem omnipotentem</I>. &thorn;e fede[r] almihti. <I>Creatorem celi &amp; terre.</I> scuppende and weldende of heouene and of or&eth;e and of alle iscefte <I>&amp; in ihesum christum.</I> and ich ileue on &thorn;e helende crist. <I>filium eius unicum</I>. his enlepi sune. <I>dominum nostrum.</I> ure lauerd he is ihaten helende for he moncun helede of &thorn;an de&thorn;liche atter. &thorn;et &thorn;e alde deouel blou on adam. and on eue. and on al heore ofsprinke. swa &thorn;et heore fif-falde mihte<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. inihte,?<I>for</I> imihte.</NOTE> hom wes al binumen. &thorn;et is hore lust. hore loking. hore blawing. hore smelling. heore feling wes al iattret. ac he hom helde mid his halie fif wunden &thorn;a he &thorn;olede for us ine &thorn;e halie rode. and gef hom eche frechipe alle &thorn;a &thorn;et hit alde<NOTE PLACE="marg">? walde.</NOTE> cunnen. he is his enlipi sune. nawiht efter &thorn;o&thorn;nunge. ac efter istrone. 
<PB REF="00000141.tif" N="77"> for &thorn;an he him alse &thorn;e sunne streon&thorn; &thorn;e lome &thorn;et ho spret in to al &thorn;is wide <MILESTONE N="27a" UNIT="folio">worlde. and &thorn;e fader is ine &thorn;e sune on &thorn;re wise. On wacste; for he is muchel and mihti ouer alle &thorn;ing. On wlite; for sunne and mone &thorn;ostre&thorn; for his fairnesse. On &thorn;ewe. for he is ful of alle godnesse. and &thorn;e&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &thorn;eh.</NOTE> he beo alle ichefte lauerd for he alle &thorn;ing iscop. no&thorn;eles he nis nawiht alle monne lauerd. &thorn;ech alle men bon on his onwald; but lefulle monne lauer&eth;. and &thorn;e godfurhte. and gode cristene .Monne. lauerd; &thorn;et on god bileue&eth;. for alle o&eth;re .men. &thorn;et heuie sunnen dreche&eth;. and nulle&eth; heore sunnen forleten; bo&eth; on &thorn;e doules on-walde. and &thorn;et hwile ne studed hom nawiht &thorn;et ho singe pater noster. and credo. God &yogh;efe gode leue alle &thorn;a &thorn;et hit nabbet. and ihalde hit us. and alle o&eth;re &thorn;a hit habbe&eth; to hore liues ende. <I>Qui conceptus est &amp; cetera.</I> We habbe&eth; bigunnen ou to seggen on englisch hwat bi-qu[e]&thorn; &thorn;e crede. and habbe&eth; ou isei&eth; twa uers. and wule nu&thorn;e &thorn;et &thorn;ridde. and ic ileue on &thorn;ene helend &thorn;e &thorn;et halie meide in hire likame underfeng. nawiht efter flesces wille. ne efter likames ikunde; ah alswa alse &yogh;e nime&eth; &thorn;e worde &thorn;et iho<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE> speke to ou of mine mu&thorn;e swa ho ifeng ure drihten. &thorn;a &thorn;e engel hire brohte &thorn;e blisfulle tidinge. &thorn;us que&thorn;ende. <I>Ecce con|cipies in utero &amp; paries filium.</I> &thorn;u scald underfon an child in &thorn;i wombe and bere knaue child; and haten hit helend and hit scal king bon on &thorn;et endelese kineriche. and &thorn;et hali meiden onswerede and seide. <I>quomodo fiet istud &amp; cetera.</I> <MILESTONE N="27b" UNIT="folio">hu scal &thorn;at bon so&thorn;&thorn;en na .Mon. mine likame irine&eth; ne mid me flesliche nefde to donne. &THORN;a onswerede &thorn;e engel and seide. <I>spiritus sanctus &amp; cetera.</I>
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="8" TYPE="homily"><PB REF="00000143.tif" N="79">
<HEAD>VIII. [DE NATALE DOMINI.]<NOTE PLACE="foot">For the probable commencement of this discourse, see homily "In die natalis Domini," in Second Series of this Collection.</NOTE></HEAD>
<P><I>[H]omo quidam descendebat ab ierusalem in ierico. &amp; cetera.</I> Godalmihti sei&eth; an forbisne to his folk in &thorn;e halie godspel and sei&eth;. A mon lihte from ierusalem in to ierico. and fol imong &thorn;oues. ho him bireueden. and ho him ferwundeden and letten hine liggen half quic. and wenden for&eth;. &THORN;er com a prost bi &thorn;e weie and him nawiht ne help; and wende for&eth; &thorn;er com an diacne. <I>et cetera.</I> &thorn;a com &thorn;er an helendis .Mon. and heuede rou&thorn;e of him. and wesch his wunden mid wine. and smerede mid oli and bond his wunden. and brohte him huppen his werue. and brohte him to an hors huse. and bitahte hine &thorn;e hors horde; to witene. A &thorn;e mar&yogh;en bitahte him twa pene&yogh;es to spenen on him and seide. and &yogh;if &thorn;u mare spenest of &thorn;ine hwan ic a&yogh;en cherre; al ic &thorn;e &yogh;elde. Nu hit iburd breke &thorn;as word; alse me breke&eth; &thorn;e nute for to habbene &thorn;ene curnel. &THORN;es .Mon. &thorn;het a lihte from ierusalem in to ierico. &thorn;et his bitacned adam ure forme feder; &thorn;et alihte from hehe in to lahe. Ierusalem bitacne&eth; gri&thorn;es sih&thorn;e. and ierico; trukinge of lihte. her me mei understonde &thorn;et he <MILESTONE N="28a" UNIT="folio">alihte from hehe to lahe from derewur&eth; wuninge; in to wone of blisse. He uol imong &thorn;eues. hwet bo&eth; &thorn;as &thorn;eues; &thorn;et bo&eth; &thorn;o &thorn;et weren imakede engles in houene. and fellen ut for hore wrechede. &thorn;e he uel imong hom and fole&yogh;ede hore lare; and brec cristes heste. &thorn;a ho hine bireueden of &thorn;ere muchele mihte. &thorn;et crist him hefde i&yogh;efen of al &thorn;er or&thorn;e scrude of &thorn;e uisces i&thorn;e wetere. and fu&yogh;eles i&thorn;e lufte. and alles cunnes wilde dor; and alles cunnes wurmes. Al adam him mihte to clopie. and al walde him to cume. Al se hwat se he forgulte wes; al hit him ulel<NOTE PLACE="marg">? uleh.</NOTE> and scunede; &thorn;et him er luuede ho him for wundeden; &thorn;a &thorn;e he heuede scome a&yogh;eines his scuppende. &thorn;a he hefde &thorn;urst and hunger and chele and alle wreche si&thorn;e; ho hine bilefde liggen 
<PB REF="00000145.tif" N="81"> half quic. half quic ho wes; &thorn;a &thorn;e he sarinesse heuede wi&eth;-innen him; for his sunnen. Her me ah to understonden for-whi hit sei&eth; alf quic. and noht alf ded. her of me mei ane forbisne of twa brondes. hwanne &thorn;e an is aquenched al to gederes. and &thorn;e o&eth;er is aquenched al buten a gnast &thorn;ene &thorn;et haued &thorn;ene ene gnast upen him. me mei blauwen. and he wule aquikien and al &thorn;e brond tenden. &thorn;e brond &thorn;e is al aquenched &thorn;ah me blouwe efre; ne quike&eth; he neure. &thorn;as twa brondes bitacne&eth; twein men. &thorn;e an sunege&eth;. and is sari for his sunne. ah he ne mei his flesc awelden. &thorn;is monne me mei sermonen <MILESTONE N="28b" UNIT="folio">mid godes worde. for hwat he scal his sunne uor-saken and bileuen and bon itent of &thorn;en hali gast. Alse is &thorn;e brond of &thorn;e lutle fure. &THORN;es o&eth;er .Mon. &thorn;et sunege&eth; and luue&eth; his sunnen alse de&eth; &thorn;et fette swin &thorn;et fule fen to liggen in. &thorn;es ilke .Mon. is strong to sermonen; ah crist hine tende mid holde mode &thorn;er we mu&yogh;en understonde &thorn;et adam wes sari uor &thorn;e sunne &thorn;et he heuede idon. and for &thorn;isse sarinesse hit is iseid; &thorn;et he wes half quic bileued. Nu cume&eth; &thorn;e prest &thorn;et him nawiht ne help. &thorn;is bitacne&eth; &thorn;e world &thorn;et wes from biginnegge and eue; &thorn;at cume to moises &thorn;e prophete. In &thorn;isse worlde nas na la&yogh;e ne na lar&thorn;eu. and &thorn;ah &thorn;es patriarches alse abel and noe and abraham and ysaac. gode men weren &thorn;urh &thorn;et ho weren itende of &thorn;an halie gast. and al &thorn;os godnesse hom ne mihte werien. &thorn;et ho ne wenden alle in to helle. and al &thorn;os world wende for&thorn; and efre lei &thorn;es wreche for-wunden. Nu is &thorn;es prest uor&thorn;e. and him naue&thorn; nawiht iholpen. Nu cume&eth; &thorn;es diakne; &thorn;et bitacne&eth; moyses &thorn;e prophete. he brohte &thorn;e la&yogh;e; &thorn;et me sculde in &thorn;e ehtu&thorn;e dei &thorn;et knaue child embsni&thorn;en mid ane ulint sexe. and sette imong monkunne la&yogh;e and lare hu me sulde godalmihti serue. and his wille wurche in or&eth;e. and al &thorn;is hom helpe ne mihte; &thorn;et ho ne wenden alle in to helle. Nu is &thorn;es deakne for&thorn;e. Nu kume&eth; &thorn;es helendisse .Mon. and haue&eth; reunesse of &thorn;isse forwundede <MILESTONE N="29a" UNIT="folio">.Mon. elelendis<NOTE PLACE="marg">? elendis.</NOTE> he is icleped for he is of unku&thorn;e &thorn;ode. &thorn;e king of heuene &thorn;e com in to her&thorn;e and auenede<NOTE PLACE="marg">? awende.</NOTE> him in to his iscefte. her of seid; seint Iohan &thorn;e ewan|geliste in apocalipsi. A vuhel com flon from houene into or&eth;e. her he uette fe&thorn;er-home and wenge mid &thorn;isse fluhte he fleh into 
<PB REF="00000147.tif" N="83"> houene &thorn;er he uatte &thorn;et he nes and nawiht ne lefde of &thorn;et he wes. &thorn;is is to understonden &thorn;et hit wes &thorn;es liuiendes godes sune &thorn;e muchele lauerd; &thorn;et al &thorn;e world fulle&eth; of him solue. bitunde him solue in ane meidenes inne&thorn;e alse &thorn;e sunne scine&eth; &thorn;urh &thorn;e glesne eh&thorn;url. &thorn;et gles ne breke&eth; ne chine&eth; and &thorn;e sunne schine&eth; &thorn;er &thorn;urh. and ho nime&eth; al swuch hou alse ho &thorn;er on uint. &yogh;if &thorn;et gles is red; ho schine&eth; red. Alse &thorn;e liuendes godes sune in to &thorn;e meidene com. and ho of hire meiden-had nawiht ne wemde. &yogh;ef ho awemmed were of hire meiden-had; &thorn;enne ne mihte noht hire sune habbe &thorn;ene nome &thorn;et him wes i&yogh;efen at circumcisiun &thorn;et wes helend. and &yogh;ef he hefde on his moder ibroken hire meiden|had; ne mihte nawiht brekere bon icloped helere. for-&thorn;i he com and bette &thorn;e ne brec nefre. for-&thorn;i he is icleped elelendis. for-&thorn;i &thorn;e here he is; and honen he nis. &thorn;es .Mon. &thorn;et com &thorn;us from houene in to hor&eth;e and uppen him nom monnes icunde for monnes node. Hwet node efde moncun &thorn;et he .Mon. were; Mon hefde uorloren <MILESTONE N="29b" UNIT="folio">efre stephne bi-uore gode. &THORN;a com &thorn;es .Mon. he nefre ne gulte. &thorn;es mihte speken ouer al &thorn;es .Mon bi-com uorspeker. he isehtnede god and man. he com bi &thorn;is forwundede mon. Wel he com bi him; &thorn;a he bicom alswich alse he; wi&thorn;|ute sunne ane. He wes iwunde mid wine. and smirede mid oli. We a&yogh;en to understonden hwet bo&eth; &thorn;e wepne &thorn;et adam wes mide forwunded. mid &thorn;a ilke wepne we bo&eth; forwunded. mid spere of prude. of &yogh;itcunge. of &yogh;ifernesse. of eorre. of hordome. mid onde. mid aswolkenesse. &thorn;is bo&eth; &thorn;a wepne &thorn;et adam was mide for|wunded. Nu bihoue&eth; &thorn;e forwunded wreche &thorn;et he habbe leche. we bo&eth; forwunded us bi-houed leche. Adam wes ilechned &thorn;urh god almihti solf. and us bi-houe&eth; leche &thorn;urh prestes mu&eth;. he weis his wunde mid wine. hwet is win in wunde; Win make&eth; wunde smerte. Ah &thorn;e smertinge clense&eth; &thorn;e wunde; swa &thorn;et ho ne scal of &thorn;ere wunde habbe nan o&eth;er uuel. Al so hali scrift bi&eth; in mine [ure]<NOTE PLACE="marg">The words in brackets are written above the others.</NOTE> wunde hwan we scale<NOTE PLACE="marg">? scule.</NOTE>festen. and fleis bileuen and muchel of ure [mine] wille for ure [mine] wrechede. Hwet is &thorn;et oli; Oli haue&eth; huppen him lihtnesse and softnesse and hele. Alse &thorn;u scalt habben hwenne &thorn;u hauest idon &thorn;i scrift of &thorn;ine misdede &thorn;enne &thorn;u scalt habbe lihtnesse and softnesse and 
<PB REF="00000149.tif" N="85"> hele. &thorn;is is &thorn;et oli &thorn;e muchele mede &thorn;et <MILESTONE N="30a" UNIT="folio">&thorn;u scalt habben hwenne &thorn;u hauest ibet &thorn;ine misdeden. &thorn;enne he brohte hine uppen his werue &thorn;et is unorne mare. &thorn;et bitacne&eth; ure unorne fleis. hwense we habbe&eth; imaked &thorn;ene licome to &thorn;er saule bihoue. he hine brohte to ane hors-huse. and bitahte hine &thorn;an hors|horde. and bed hine witen &thorn;ene forwundede .Mon. H[w]et is &thorn;is hors-us; &thorn;et is hali chirche. hali chirche hwet is; al cristene folc. for hwon; In halie chirche bo&eth; betere and wurse. Alse in hors-huse bo&eth; fule and clene. he &thorn;et haue&eth; &thorn;et hors-hus te witene; scal &thorn;er. &thorn;er hit is ful; makien hit clene. &thorn;et bitakne&eth; &thorn;e prost &thorn;et scal among cristene monkun &thorn;ene sunfulle of sunne clensen. he haue&eth; o&thorn;e mar&yogh;en &thorn;a twein pene&yogh;es &thorn;e &thorn;e helelendisse.<NOTE PLACE="marg">? helendisse.</NOTE> Mon. bitahte. &thorn;et bo&eth; &thorn;a twa la&yogh;en &thorn;e alde and &thorn;e nowe &thorn;et prost scal spenen among al his under&thorn;ede. &yogh;ef he mare spene&eth; of his; hwense he a&yogh;ein cherre&eth; al he hit him wule &yogh;elden. hwet is &thorn;et he mei mare spenen of his a&yogh;en; feire forbisne of his a&yogh;ene liflade. Alse alle &thorn;o &thorn;et him bo&eth; under&thorn;ede. &thorn;et nime&eth; mare uppen hom &thorn;en &thorn;e heste of hali chirche. &thorn;et is to understonden. Meiden &thorn;et hire meiden-hat wit. and halde&thorn; so se hit nis noht heste of hali chirche. and widewe of hire widewe-had <MILESTONE N="30b" UNIT="folio">ne .Mon. &thorn;e worlde to forsaken. In &thorn;e deie of liureisun hwense god al|mihtin wule windwin &thorn;et er wes i&thorn;or[s]chen. he wile ison hwiche bo&eth; &thorn;o. &thorn;et mu&yogh;e stonden a&yogh;ein &thorn;es fleisces lust and wernen his a&yogh;ene fleisces iwille. &thorn;et bitakne&eth; &thorn;et corn &thorn;et &thorn;urle&eth; &thorn;e wind. &thorn;et smal chef &thorn;et flid ford mid &thorn;e winde; bicume&eth; wur&thorn;inge &thorn;et corn me de&eth; in to gerner. &thorn;et bitakene&eth; &thorn;e gode men &thorn;e scule bon idon in to heuene. &thorn;e ilke &thorn;e fole&yogh;e&eth; &thorn;es fleisces lust. Alse de&eth; &thorn;et smalchef &thorn;e winde; &thorn;o scule bileuen in &thorn;osternesse. God almihtin iscilde us &thorn;et we ne bo noht of &thorn;e smalcheue. Ah &thorn;et we moten bon of &thorn;e corne &thorn;e me scal don in to &thorn;e gernere &thorn;et is in to heuene; &thorn;e feder and &thorn;e sune and &thorn;e halie gast. <I>per omnia secula seculorum. Amen.</I>
</P>

</DIV2>
