<HEAD>IX. [IN DIE PENTECOSTEN.]</HEAD>
<P>[F]ram &thorn;an halie hester dei; bo&eth; italde. fifti da&yogh;a to &thorn;isse deie and &thorn;es dei is ihaten pentecostes &thorn;et is &thorn;e fiftu&eth;a dei fram &thorn;an ester tid. &thorn;es dei wes on &thorn;ere alde la&yogh;e iset and ihalden. God het Moyses on egipte londe &thorn;et he and al &thorn;et israelisce folc &thorn;et he &thorn;ider iled hefde; &thorn;et heo sculden offrien of elchan hiwscipe gode an lomb of ane &yogh;eres and merki mid &thorn;an blode hore duren. and hore ouersleaht. &thorn;a on &thorn;ere ilke nihte; iwende godes engel to and acwalde on elche huse of &thorn;am egiptiss|en folche &thorn;et frumkenede childe and &thorn;et lefeste; and &thorn;et israelisce folc ferde on &thorn;ere ilca nihte of &thorn;am londe. for&eth;on muchele wawen &thorn;et hi &thorn;er i&eth;oleden. <MILESTONE N="31a" UNIT="folio">and god hom ledde ofer &thorn;a rede se; mid dru&yogh;e fotan. &thorn;a iwende pharaon &thorn;e kin[g] of &thorn;am londe efter heom ledde<NOTE PLACE="marg">? mide.</NOTE> muchele ferde. &thorn;a &thorn;e heo comen on midden &thorn;ere se. &thorn;a wes &thorn;et godes folc<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. focl.</NOTE> up of &thorn;ere se agan. and god bisencte &thorn;a &thorn;e pharaon; and al his genge. &ETH;a het god moyse and &thorn;an folce &thorn;et heo heolden &thorn;a tid mid muchlere blisse ewilche &yogh;ere &thorn;a wes &thorn;on folce iset &thorn;o tid to estertide; for &thorn;on god heom aredde wi&eth; heore ifan and heom fordude. &ETH;a fram &thorn;am ester tid fifti da&yogh;a isette god &thorn;am folke la&yogh;e. and wes ise&yogh;en godes fortacne uppon ane dune &thorn;at is &thorn;e mont of synai. for &thorn;et<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &thorn;er.</NOTE> com muchel liht. and eislic swei and blawende beman. &thorn;a cleopede god &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. &thorn;e.</NOTE> ner Moyses him to. and he wes mid gode fowerti da&yogh;es and awrat &thorn;a alde e bi godes wissunge. &thorn;a wes &thorn;e dei pentecostes ihaten on &thorn;ere alde isetnesse. &thorn;et i-offrede lomb &thorn;et &thorn;e engel het offrian bitacne&eth; cristes de&eth;&thorn;e &thorn;et wes milde. and wi&eth;utan gulte his feder i-offrad; for ure alesendnesse. Nu is his &thorn;rowunge and his ariste ure ester tid; for&eth;on &thorn;et he us alesde from deofles &thorn;ewdome alswa he alesde &thorn;et israelisce folc of pharaones &thorn;ewdome and ure ifan &thorn;et beo&eth; &thorn;a deofles beo&eth; bisencte in to helle &thorn;urh &thorn;e halie fullht 
<PB REF="00000153.tif" N="89"> &yogh;if we hit ariht halde&eth; alswa pharaon wes mid his ferde on &thorn;are rede se. &ETH;as fifti da&yogh;es fram &thorn;an esterliche <MILESTONE N="31b" UNIT="folio">deie beo&eth; alle ihal|&yogh;ode to ane herunge; and &thorn;es dei is ure pentecostes dei. &thorn;et is ure witte sunnedei &thorn;et is &thorn;e fifteo&yogh;a&eth;e dei fram &thorn;am ester deie. on &thorn;am ealdan pentecoste god sette .e. &thorn;am israelisce folce hu heo sculden heore lif leaden; on &thorn;isse deie com &thorn;e halie gast on fures heowe to godes hirede. for&eth;i alswa &thorn;et lomb bitacnede cristes &thorn;rowunge; Swa ec &thorn;eo alde .e. on moyses da&yogh;en bitacne&eth;e god|spelles bodunge; under godes &yogh;ife. &ETH;reo tide beo&eth; on &thorn;issere worlde. An is &thorn;et wes buten .e. and o&eth;er is &thorn;e &thorn;et wes under &thorn;ere .e. &thorn;e &thorn;ridde is nu efter cristes to-cume. &THORN;eos tide iset under godes &yogh;ife. we ne beo&eth; na buten .e. ne we ne moten. halden moyses .e. licamliche. Ac godes &yogh;ife us wissa&eth; to his willen. &yogh;if we imundie beo&eth; godes bibode and &thorn;era apostla lare. Hit is ireht on &thorn;es pistles redinge; hu &thorn;e halia gast on &thorn;isse deie com to &thorn;an ileaufullen hirede. Lucas &thorn;e godspellere awrat on &thorn;ere boc &thorn;et is inemned actus apostolorum. and cwe&eth;. <I>Cu com|plerenturdies pentecostes erant omnes discipuli pariter in eodem loco. Et factus est repente de celo sonus tanquam aduenientis spiritus uehementis &amp; repleuit totam domum ubi erant sedentes.</I> &ETH;at halie hired cristes apostles weren wuniende edmodliche<NOTE PLACE="marg">? anmod|liche.</NOTE> on heore ibeoden on ane upflore <MILESTONE N="32a" UNIT="folio">efter cristes upsti&yogh;e onbodinde his bi-hates. &thorn;a on &thorn;isse deie &thorn;et is pentecostes and wittesunnedeie on ure speche; com ferliche muchel swei of heofne and fulde al &thorn;a upfleunge<NOTE PLACE="marg">? upfler|unge.</NOTE> mid fure. And wes ise&yogh;en biforan heore elche swilc hit were furene tungen. and heo weren &thorn;a alle ifullede mid &thorn;an halie gast. and on-gunnen to speoken mid mislichen spechen bi &thorn;am &thorn;et &thorn;e halie gast him tahte. &thorn;a weren &thorn;er igedered wi&eth;inne &thorn;ere buruh of ierusalem trowfeste men of elchere &thorn;eode &thorn;et under heofene erde|den. and &thorn;e apostles speken to &thorn;es folkes igederunge. and heor eclicnew<NOTE PLACE="marg">? elc icnew.</NOTE> his ah&yogh;ene speche. &thorn;a iwar&eth; &thorn;at folc swi&eth;e abluied;<NOTE PLACE="marg">? ablicged.</NOTE> and mid wundrunge cwe&eth;en. <I>None ecce omnes isti galilei sunt; &amp; quomodo nos audiuimus unusquisque linguam nostram in qua nati sumus.</I> La hu ne bea&eth; &thorn;a &thorn;et here speca&eth; galileisce; and ure elc iherden hu hi spechen ure speche on &thorn;an &thorn;et we akenned weren; Lahwet scal &thorn;is beon; &thorn;a seiden &thorn;a iudeiscen men a 
<PB REF="00000155.tif" N="91"> bismer. &thorn;as men beo&eth; mid miste fordrencte. &ETH;a and-wurde petrus. hit is undertid hu mihte we on &thorn;issere tide beon for|drencte; Ac &thorn;es wite&yogh;an cwide ioheles is ifulled. God cwe&eth; &thorn;urh &thorn;es wite&yogh;an mu&eth;. &thorn;et he walde his gast asenden ofer men|nesc flesc. and monna bern sculen wite&yogh;an. and ic sende min tacna &yogh;eond <MILESTONE N="32b" UNIT="folio">&thorn;a eor&eth;e. petrus cwe&eth; &thorn;a. wite &yogh;e so&eth;liche &thorn;et crist aras of dea&eth;e and on ure iwitnesse astah to heofene. and sit on his feder riht alfe; alswa daui&eth; bi him wite&yogh;ede &thorn;us cwe&eth;inde. <I>Dixit dominus domino meo sede a dextris meis</I>. Drihten cwe&eth; to mine drihtene. site to mine riht alfe. for&eth; &thorn;et ic alegge &thorn;ine feond under &thorn;ine fot-sceomele. &thorn;a &thorn;et folc &thorn;is iherde &thorn;a iturne<NOTE PLACE="marg">? iturnde.</NOTE> heore mod and seden to &thorn;an apostlan. Leofemen hwet is us to donne; &ETH;a and-wrde petrus. Bi-reowsia&eth; eo[w]re sunnan and under|fo&eth; fuluht on cristes nome. &thorn;enne beo&eth; eowre sunnen aleide and &yogh;e underfo&eth; &thorn;ene halie gast. &thorn;a underfengen heo his lare and bu&yogh;en to fulehte on &thorn;on deie; &thorn;reo &thorn;usend monna. and &thorn;a weren alle mid sibsumnesse; and fuleden &thorn;am apostles. and salden heore ehte and &thorn;et feh bitahten &thorn;am apostles and heo hit delden elcan alswa heo neode hefde. eft on ane o&eth;re bodunge &yogh;e-lefden fif &thorn;usend monna on criste. &thorn;a iweorden alle &thorn;os ilefede men swulche hi alle hefden ane heorte and ane sawle ne heore nan nefden sunderlich ehte ac heom alen wes imene heore &thorn;ing ne &thorn;er nas nan wone bi-twuxan heom and &thorn;a &thorn;et lond hefden he hit sealden; and &thorn;et wur&eth; brohten to &thorn;es apostlas fotan and heo hit delden elchun alswa heo neode hefden. &thorn;a warhte god feole tacne on &thorn;an folke &thorn;urh &thorn;ere apostlan hondan <MILESTONE N="33a" UNIT="folio">swa &thorn;et ileiden &thorn;a untrummen men bi &thorn;ere stret &thorn;ere petrus for&eth;-eo&eth;e and swa re&eth;e swa his sceadu<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>It may be</I> sceada.</NOTE> heom on gla&eth; heo weren iheled. from alle untrumnesse. heo setten heore honden ofer ilefde men; and heo underfengen &thorn;ene halian gast. &THORN;a wes &thorn;ere an mon ananias ihaten and his wif saphira. Heo bispeken heom bitweonen; &thorn;et heo walden ibu&yogh;en to &thorn;ere apostlan fereden and swa duden. Heo nomen heom to &thorn;am rede &thorn;et heo walden sum of heore ehte etholdan. &thorn;am apostlan; for heo nusten hwet heom ilumpe. &thorn;a com &thorn;e mon mid his gersume to &thorn;an apostolum. &thorn;a cwe&eth; petrus. Ananias &thorn;e deofel bipehte &thorn;ine heorte and &thorn;u hauest ilo&yogh;en &thorn;an halie gaste; 
<PB REF="00000157.tif" N="93"> hwi woldest &thorn;u swikian on &thorn;ine a&yogh;ene &thorn;inge; Ne lu&yogh;e &thorn;u na monnum; ac dudest gode. &thorn;a he &thorn;a worde iherde; &thorn;a feol he adun and iwat and &thorn;a he iburied wes; &thorn;a com his wif saphira and nuste hwet hire were ilumpen wes. &ETH;[a] cwe&eth; petrus hwi iwear&eth; hinc swa &thorn;et &yogh;it dursten fondian godes; &thorn;a heo &thorn;is iherde; &thorn;a feol heo &thorn;er adun and iwat and me buriede heo mid hire fere. &ETH;a iwear&eth; &thorn;er muchel eie on godes folke. and on alle &thorn;am &thorn;et &thorn;eos ti&eth;inge iherdon. &ETH;a apostoli si&eth;&eth;an er &thorn;on &thorn;et heo to|ferden isetten iacob &thorn;et wes ihaten rihtwis on cristes selt and alle &thorn;eo ileafulle la&eth;unge him ihersummede; efter godes <MILESTONE N="33b" UNIT="folio">tecunge. he &thorn;a iset &thorn;et seld .xxx. &yogh;era and efter him simeon &thorn;es h[e]lendes mei. and efter &thorn;issere bisnunge weren arerede munechene lif mid. mid &thorn;ere annesse and sibsumnesse &thorn;et heo sculen &thorn;olien; bi heore abbodes iwissunge. &yogh;e iherden a lutel er. on &thorn;isse redunge. &thorn;et &eth;e halie gast com ofer &thorn;a apostlas mid furene tungen; and heom &yogh;ef &thorn;o mihte &thorn;et heo cu&thorn;en alle spechen; for&eth;on &thorn;et &eth;eo edmode isomnunge iernade et gode; &thorn;et muchel er &thorn;e engles of eofene for heore modinesse forluren. hit itimode efter noes flode &thorn;et eontas walden areran ane buruh and anne stepel swa hehne; &thorn;et his Rof asti&yogh;e up to heofena. and &thorn;a wes an speche on al moncun. and &thorn;et weorc wes bigunnen on-&yogh;en godes iwillan. God ec for&eth;on heom to drefde swa &thorn;et he &yogh;ef ewilcum of &thorn;an wurhtan selcu&eth;e speche; and heore nan ne icnew o&eth;res speche. &thorn;i<NOTE PLACE="marg">? for &thorn;i.</NOTE> bileafden heo heore timbr|unge and to dreofden &yogh;eond al middeleard. and &thorn;e&eth;&eth;an<NOTE PLACE="marg">? se&eth;&eth;an.</NOTE> weren swa felen spechen swa &thorn;ere wurhten weren, &thorn;et weren twa hun manna. Nu eft on &thorn;isse deie &thorn;urh &thorn;es halie gastes to-cume; weren alle ispechen a&yogh;ein inumen. and isome; for&eth;on &thorn;et cristes apostlas weren specende mid alle spechen. and ec &thorn;et wunderluker for&eth;on &thorn;et &thorn;a an of &thorn;on apostlum bodeden mid ane speche; elche men wes i&thorn;uht &thorn;et &thorn;a bodunge iherde; swilche heo spechen mid heore speche <MILESTONE N="34a" UNIT="folio">weren heo ebreisce. weren heo grekisce. o&eth;er romenisce. o&eth;er egiptisse. o&eth;er of hwulche londe swa heo weren &thorn;et &thorn;e lare iherden. On &thorn;issere ifereden iemede<NOTE PLACE="marg">? iernede.</NOTE> &thorn;ere apostlan admodnesse &thorn;as mihte. and &thorn;ere eontan modinisse iarnede iscendnesse. &thorn;e heolia<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE> gast wes ise&yogh;en ofer &thorn;a apostlas on fures heowe. and ofer crist on hi[s] fuluhte on ane culfre 
<PB REF="00000159.tif" N="95"> onlicnesse. Hwi ofer criste on culfren heowe. and hwi ofer cristes hirede on fures ilicnesse; for&eth;on &thorn;e &thorn;et fu&yogh;el-cun is swi&eth;e bilehwit. and wit-utan la&eth;e and isibsum. &thorn;e helend is alles moncunnes dema. Ac he ne com na to demane moncun swa se heo him seolf cwe&eth;; ac to helenne. Gif he walde &thorn;a deman moncun &thorn;a &thorn;e he erest to middelearde com. hwa weren &thorn;anne ihalden; Ac he nalde mid his to-cume &thorn;a sunfullen fordemen; ac he walde to his riche heom igederian. Erest he walde us mid li&eth;nesse isteoren &thorn;et he mihte seo&eth;&eth;an on his dome us ihalden. and for&eth;on we[s] &thorn;e halia gast on culfren onlic|nesse bufan criste. for&eth;on &thorn;et he wes dreihninde on &thorn;issere worlde mid bilehwitnesse. and mid nane la&eth;nesse and mid sib|sumnesse. for he ne remde ne of bitere speche nes. ne he sake ne asterde; ac forbere monna hufelnesse &thorn;urh his li&eth;nesse. Ac &thorn;e &thorn;et on &thorn;am ercan<NOTE PLACE="marg">erran.</NOTE> to-cume li&eth;egedde &thorn;an <MILESTONE N="34b" UNIT="folio">sunfullen to &thorn;ere godnesse; he dema&eth; sti&eth;ne dom &thorn;am forsunegede on his efter to-come &thorn;et is on domes deie. &thorn;e halia gast wes ise&yogh;en on fures heowe bufan &thorn;am apostlas. for&eth;on &thorn;e he dude &thorn;et heo weren birnende on godes willan. and bodiende umbe godes riche. Furen tungen heo hefden &thorn;a &thorn;e heo mid lufe godes murh&eth;e bodeden. &thorn;et &eth;ere he&eth;ene monnan heortan &thorn;et calde weren &thorn;urh ilefleaste and flescliche iwilnunge; muhten beon atende to &thorn;an heofenliche biboden. &yogh;if &thorn;e halia gast ne lear&eth; &thorn;es monnes heorte and his mod wi&eth;-innan; on idel beo&eth; &thorn;es budeles word wi&eth;-utan icleopde. &thorn;es fares<NOTE PLACE="marg">? fures.</NOTE> icunde is &thorn;et hit for&eth;nime&eth; swa hwet him neh bi&eth;. Alswa scal &thorn;e lar&eth;eu don &thorn;e &eth;et bi&eth; mid &thorn;en<NOTE PLACE="marg">? MS. &thorn;et.</NOTE> halia gast itend. Erest he scal hine seolfne wi&eth; sunnan isteoran. and seo&eth;&eth;an his heorde. On culfre onlicnesse and on fures heowe wes godes gast isceawed. for&eth;on &thorn;et he de&eth; &thorn;a &thorn;e beo&eth; bilehwite. and wi&eth;-utan ufelnesse. and birnende on godes willan. &thorn;et he mid his &yogh;if ifulle&eth;. Ne bi&eth; &thorn;eo bilehwitnesse godes icwime butas<NOTE PLACE="marg">? butan.</NOTE> sno<NOTE PLACE="marg">sno <I>at first, but altered to</I> sne.</NOTE>ternesse ne sneternesse butan bile|hwitnesse. hwet bi&eth; bilehwitnesse butan rihtwisnesse; and hwet <MILESTONE N="35a" UNIT="folio">bi&eth; sneternesse bute so&eth;e lufe to gode and to monnen; for&eth;on &thorn;e halia gast &thorn;e &thorn;et tec&eth; riht-wissnesse and bilehwitnesse scule<NOTE PLACE="marg">? sculde.</NOTE> beon isceawed ei&eth;er &yogh;e on fure. &yogh;e on culfren. for&eth;on &thorn;et heo de&eth; 
<PB REF="00000161.tif" N="97"> &thorn;ere monnan heortan &thorn;et he onlihte&eth; mid his &yogh;ife. &thorn;et heo beo&eth; li&eth;e &thorn;urh un-cladnesse<NOTE PLACE="marg">unla&eth;nesse.</NOTE>. and iten&eth; &thorn;urh lufe and snoternesse. God is swa paul cwe&eth;. &thorn;et niminde fur and he is un-asecgliche fur. and unisewenlich fur. Bi &thorn;am fure cwe&eth; &thorn;e helende. Ic com for&eth;on &thorn;et ic walde sendan fur on eor&eth;an. and ic wile &thorn;at hit berne. he sende &thorn;ene halia gast to eor&eth;an and he mid his bleade on-ealde eor&eth;lichen monnan heortan &thorn;enne birne&eth; &thorn;a eor&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg">? eor&eth;e.</NOTE> &thorn;enne &thorn;es eor&eth;liche monnes heorte bi&eth; itend to godes lufe. &thorn;a &thorn;et er wes cald &thorn;urh flescliche lustes. Ni<NOTE PLACE="marg">? nis.</NOTE> na &thorn;e halia gast wuniende on his icunde. swa se he ise&yogh;en wes; for&eth;on &thorn;et he is unise&yogh;enlic. Ac for &thorn;ere itacnunge swa &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">? we.</NOTE> er seiden. &thorn;et he wes ise&yogh;en on culfre and on fure. He is ihate on grekisc paraclitus. &thorn;et is &thorn;e frofre gast. for&eth;on &thorn;et he ifrefra&eth; &thorn;a drori&yogh;an. &thorn;a &thorn;et heore sun|nan bireusia&eth;. and &yogh;if&eth; heom for&yogh;ifnesse. and huht. and heore &yogh;eomerinde mod ili&eth;ega&eth;. heo for&yogh;ife&eth; sunna. and he is &thorn;e wei to <MILESTONE N="35b" UNIT="folio">alre sunnen for&yogh;ifenesse. he &yogh;if&eth; his &yogh;efe &thorn;an &thorn;et he wule. Summe Men he &yogh;if wisdom and speche. Summe god i&eth;onc. Summe muchele ileafe. Summe mihte to helene un-trume men. Summe witegunge. Summe iscead godra gast. and ufele. Summe he &yogh;if&eth; misliche irord. Summen man irecednesse of misliche spechen. Ealle &thorn;as &thorn;ing and moni&yogh;e o&eth;re de&eth; &thorn;e hali&yogh;a gast; to delende uwilchen bi &thorn;an &thorn;et him iwur&eth;; for&eth;on &thorn;et he is almihtin wurhte. for swa re&eth;e swa he &thorn;es mannes heorte and his mod on-lihte; hit iwende&eth; from ufele to gode. he on-lihte daui&eth;es heorte &thorn;a &thorn;e he on &yogh;eo&yogh;o&thorn;e herpan lufede. and warhte hine; to salm wurhtan. Amos het a reo&eth;er heorde &thorn;ene aw[e]nde &thorn;e hali&yogh;a gast to ane gode witege. petrus wes fixere &thorn;ene iturnde &thorn;e &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE> ilcan godes gast to apostle. paul &thorn;et hermede cristene men; &thorn;ene he iches to lar&eth;ewe alle &thorn;eoden. Matheus &thorn;et wes cachepol &thorn;ene he iwende to god-spellere. &ETH;a apostlas ne dursten bodian &thorn;a so&eth;en ileafen for &thorn;on eie of &thorn;on he&eth;ene. Ac &thorn;a si&eth;&eth;an heo weren itend of &thorn;an halia gaste. hi neren aferede of nane licamliche pinunge. and &thorn;erfore wi&eth;-utan fore godes blisse bodedan. &ETH;isses dei&yogh;es hehnesse is to heriane. for&eth;on &thorn;et &thorn;e almihti god hine seoffimede<MILESTONE N="36a" UNIT="folio"> mede<NOTE PLACE="marg">? seolfne imedemede.</NOTE> &thorn;et he walde monna cun on &thorn;isse deie isundian. on cristes akennednesse iwear&eth; &thorn;e almihti&yogh;a 
<PB REF="00000163.tif" N="99"> godes sune to monnesce men ibroht. and on &thorn;isse deie iweorden ileafulle men godes and swa se crist cwe&eth;. Ic cwe&eth;e &yogh;e beo&eth; godes bern &thorn;a icorene men beo&eth; godes bern; na icun&eth;liche; ac &thorn;urh &thorn;es hal&yogh;an gastes &yogh;ife. And<NOTE PLACE="marg">? An.</NOTE> god is icundeliche on &thorn;reom. Hadan feder. and sune. &thorn;et is his wisdom. and &thorn;e hal&yogh;e gast; &thorn;e &thorn;et is heore beire wille. Heore cunde is unto-deledlich efer<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. efter.</NOTE> wuniende on ane godnesse. &thorn;e ilca cwe&eth;. bi his icorene &yogh;e beo&eth; godes. &THORN;uruh cristes menniscnesse men weren alesde from deofles &eth;eowdome. and &thorn;urh &thorn;es hal&yogh;e gastes to-cume mennen saule were ibroht to gode. Crist underfenc meniscnesse on his to-cume. and men underfengen god; &thorn;urh &thorn;es hal&yogh;an gastes isundunge. &thorn;e mon &thorn;et naf&eth; godes gast on him nis he na godes. Elches monnes weorc cu&eth;an hwilc gast hine wissa&eth;. Godes gast wissa&eth; efre to hali&yogh;nesse. and to godnesse. Deofles gast wissa&eth; to sunnan; and to mandeden. &thorn;e hal&yogh;a gast bicom twa ofer &thorn;a apostlas. Crist ableow &thorn;ana<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE> hal&yogh;a gast ofer &thorn;a apostlas; er his upst[i]&yogh;e &thorn;us cwe&eth;inde onfo&eth; haline gast. eft on &thorn;isse deie he sende &thorn;e almihtin feder and &thorn;e sune heore<MILESTONE N="36b" UNIT="folio"> beire gast to &thorn;am apostli; &thorn;a &yogh;et wuniende on &thorn;issere weorlde. &thorn;e helende ableu his gast on his apostlas for &eth;ere itacnunge. &thorn;et heo and alle cristen men scullan lufian heore nehstan; al swa he heom er bihet &thorn;ene ilca gast of heofne. for&eth;on &thorn;et we sculen lufian god ofer alle o&eth;er &thorn;ing. An is &thorn;e halie gast &thorn;ah &thorn;et he twa bicome ofer &thorn;a apostlas. Al swa ec is an lufe; and twa biboden. &thorn;et we sculen lufian god; and. Men. Ac we sculen leornian on mannen hu we ma&yogh;en bicuman to godes lufe. Al swa Iohan &thorn;e godspellere cwe&eth;. &thorn;e &thorn;et ne lufe&eth; his bro&eth;er &thorn;ene &thorn;et he isih&eth;. hu mei he lufian god &thorn;ene &thorn;et he ne isih&eth; licomliche; we wur&eth;ia&eth; &thorn;es hal&yogh;en gastes to-cume mid loft|songe<NOTE PLACE="marg">? lof-.</NOTE> seofen da&yogh;es. for&eth;on &thorn;et he onlihte ure mod mid seofanfald &yogh;ife. &thorn;et is mid wisdom. and an&yogh;ite mid i&eth;ohte. and streinde mid gode dedan; and trewfestnesse. and he us iful&eth; mid godes ei&yogh;e. &thorn;e &thorn;et &eth;urh gode iearnunge<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE> bi-cum&eth; to &thorn;issan seof&aelig;nfalden &yogh;efan of &thorn;am<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &thorn;an.</NOTE> hal&yogh;an gaste; he haue&eth; alle blisse. Ac &thorn;e &thorn;et wule to &thorn;are blisse bicumen; he scal ileafan on &thorn;a hal&yogh;a &thorn;reomnesse. and on so&eth;re annesse. &thorn;et is &thorn;e feder. and his sune and heore beira gast heo beo&eth; &thorn;reo on hadan and an god unto-<MILESTONE N="37a" UNIT="folio"> delendlich on 
<PB REF="00000165.tif" N="101"> ane drihtnesse and godnesse wuniende &thorn;eos ileafan itacneden &thorn;a &thorn;reo &thorn;usend men. &thorn;et erest bu&yogh;en to ileafan efter &thorn;es hal&yogh;a gastes to-cume. and alswa &thorn;eo &thorn;reo &thorn;usend weren an iferende<NOTE PLACE="marg">? iferedene.</NOTE>. alswa is &thorn;eo hal&yogh;e &thorn;reomnesse an god. and &thorn;et iferende is swa anmod swulc heom alle an weren on heorte. and an sawul; for&eth;on &thorn;et &thorn;ere hal&yogh;an &thorn;remnesse is an godnesse. and an icunde. and an iwille. and an worc un-to-delendlich. &ETH;a ileaffullen brohton heore gersum and leiden heo et &thorn;ere apostlan fotan. Mid &thorn;an is itacned &thorn;et cristene men ne sculen heore bileafe bisettan on &thorn;ere weordliche eahte; ac on heore god ane. &thorn;e &yogh;itsere &thorn;e biset his i&thorn;onc on his ehte; he bi&eth; &thorn;es deofles bern buten he hit iswike; for&eth;on heo &thorn;et &thorn;a &yogh;itsunge heolden heore eahte unwur[&eth;]liche nefde nenne stude; on heore heortan<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>The proper order is</I>&mdash;heo heolden heore eaht unwur|liche for&eth;on &thorn;et &thorn;a &yogh;itsung nef de, &amp;c.</NOTE>. and for &thorn;i heo dudan heore &thorn;ing heom &yogh;emene; &thorn;et heo so&eth;re sibsumnesse butan &yogh;itsunge beon mihten, &thorn;a apostlas setten here hondan ofer ileaffulle men; and heom com to &thorn;e hal&yogh;a gast. &thorn;urh heore bisceopunge. Bisceopas &thorn;es ilcan hades on godes ila&eth;unge. and halda&eth; &thorn;a isetnesse on heore bisceopunge swa &thorn;et heo sette&eth; heoran <MILESTONE N="37b" UNIT="folio">handan ofer iful&yogh;ede men. and bidda&eth; &thorn;et &thorn;e almihti welden[de] heom sende &thorn;a seofenfalde &yogh;ife of &thorn;am hal&yogh;an gaste. <I>Qui uiuit &amp; Regnat, &amp;c.</I></P>
