<DIV2 N="10" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>X. DE OCTO UICIIS &amp; DE DUODECIM ABUSIUIS HUIUS SECULI.</HEAD>
<P><I>[O]mnia nimia nocent. &amp; temperancia mater uirtutum di|citur</I>. &thorn;et is on englisc. alle ofer done &thorn;ing dena&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg">? deria&eth;.</NOTE>. and imetnesse is alre mihta moder &thorn;e oferlifa on hete and on wete maca&eth; &thorn;ene mon un-halne. and his saule gode la&eth;e&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. lade&eth;.</NOTE> and swa ure drihten on his godspelle seide. &THORN;Et &thorn;er to&yogh;eines unimete festen and to michel forhefednesse on hete and on wete maca&eth; &thorn;ene mon un-halne and on michelere sarinesse bringe&eth; swa swa us segge&eth; bec. &thorn;et sume men festen swa &thorn;et hi swencten swi&eth;e 
<PB REF="00000167.tif" N="103"> heom seolfe. and nane mede nefden for &thorn;a michele iswinche. ac &thorn;es &thorn;e fir weren fram godes milce [E]a&eth;e mei &thorn;e mon fundan hu he hine seolfe amerre. ac we scole witan. &thorn;et nan seolf cwale &thorn;et is a&yogh;en-scla&yogh;a ne cume&eth; to godes riche. Nu beo&eth; .viii. heofod sunnan &thorn;e rixa&eth; on us to swi&eth;e. On is icwe&eth;en. <I>Gula.</I> &thorn;et is &yogh;ifernesse on englisc. &thorn;eo de&eth; &thorn;et mon et er timan. and drince&eth;. o&eth;er eft to muchel nime&eth; on ete o&eth;er on wete. &ETH;eos sunne forde&eth; ei&eth;er &yogh;e saule. &yogh;e lichoma. for <MILESTONE N="38a" UNIT="folio">heo mace&eth; &thorn;an men muchele untrumnesse and to de&thorn;e bringe&eth; mid unmete drunche. and heo forde&eth; ec &thorn;es monnes saule for heo scal sune&yogh;an oft. &thorn;enne he nat hu he fer&eth; for his feondlichan drunche. &THORN;a o&eth;er sunne forliger and unimete galnesse. &thorn;et is ihaten <I>fornicatio</I>. He bule&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg">? befule&eth;.</NOTE> &thorn;ene mon and mace&eth; of cristes leoman heoranna leoman; and of godes husa gromena wuniunge. &thorn;a &thorn;ridde sunne is. <I>Aua|ricia</I>. &thorn;et is &thorn;eo ufele &yogh;itsunge. heo is more of elchere wohnesse heo maca&eth; reaflac and unrihte domes. stale and lesunge. and forsworenesse. heo is helle iliche. for&eth;on &thorn;et hi ba habbe&eth; un|afillendliche gredinesse; &thorn;et hi nefre ne beo&eth; fulle. &thorn;eo feor&eth;[e] sunne is ihatan. <I>Ira.</I> &thorn;et is on englisc wemodnesse. heo de&eth; &thorn;et &thorn;e mon ne ah his modes iwald and heo maca&eth; monslehtas. and monies cunnes ufel. &THORN;eo fifte sunne is. <I>Tristicia.</I> &thorn;et is &thorn;issere worlde sarinesse &thorn;enne &thorn;e mon sor&yogh;e&eth; alles to swi&eth;e for his hehte lure. &thorn;e he luuede to swi&eth;e. and chit &thorn;enne wi&eth; gode. and his sunnen eche&eth;. Twa sarinesse beo&eth;. an is &thorn;eos uuele o&eth;er is halwende. &thorn;et is &thorn;et mon beo sari her on worlde for his sunnen. &THORN;eo sixte is ihaten. <I>Desidia.</I> &thorn;et is slew&eth;e on englisc &thorn;enne &thorn;an mon ne lust on his liue nan god don. and bi&eth; eure un&yogh;earu to elchere du&yogh;e&eth;e. <MILESTONE N="38b" UNIT="folio">&THORN;e seofe&eth;e sunne is icwe&eth;en. <I>Iactancia.</I> &thorn;et is idel&yogh;elp on englisc. &thorn;enne mon bi&eth; lof-&yogh;eorn. and mid fikenunge fear&eth; and de&eth; for &yogh;elpe mare &thorn;enne for godes luue. &yogh;if he awiht delan wule. and for&eth;on bi&eth; &thorn;e lesse<NOTE PLACE="marg">? <I>for</I> hlisse.</NOTE> his edlen &thorn;ere dede, and his wite abide&eth; on &thorn;ere o&eth;re weorlde. &THORN;e ehtu&eth;e sunne is ihatan. <I>Superbia.</I> &thorn;et is on englisc, modinesse. Heo is|ord and ende of alle uuele. heo macode englas to ateliche deoflan and &thorn;ene mon make&eth; ec &yogh;if<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. &yogh;is.</NOTE> heo modiga&eth; to swi&eth;e &thorn;es deofles ifere; &thorn;e feol er ut of heouene &thorn;urh modinesse. Nu beo&eth; .viii. 
<PB REF="00000169.tif" N="105"> heafod mihtan. &thorn;e ma&yogh;en ouercumen alle &thorn;as sunnan &thorn;urh drihtnes fultum. An is [<I>Temperantia</I>] &thorn;et is metnesse on englisc. &thorn;et mon beo imete on alle &thorn;ing and to muchel ne &thorn;igge on ete and on wete. ne er timan to his borde ne sitte. Nutenu eta&eth; swa er<NOTE PLACE="marg">? ec.</NOTE> swa hi hit habbe&eth;. ac &thorn;a iscead-wise mon scal kepan his meles and &thorn;enne mid isceade his isetnesse halden. &thorn;enne mei he ouercuman swa &thorn;a &yogh;iue[r]nesse. &THORN;e o&eth;er mihte is <I>Castitas.</I> &thorn;et is clenesse on englisc. &thorn;et &thorn;e leawde mon hine halde butan for|li&yogh;ere on rihte la&yogh;e. and mid isceadwisnesse. &thorn;eo ihadode godes &thorn;eowa halde eure his clenesse ouer alle &thorn;ing. and &thorn;enne bi&eth; ouer|cumen swa ec &thorn;a fule galnesse. &THORN;e &thorn;ridde mihte is. <I>Largitas.</I> &thorn;et is custinesse on englisc &thorn;et mon wisliche <MILESTONE N="39a" UNIT="folio">spene &thorn;a &thorn;ing &thorn;e him god lene on &thorn;isse liue to brukene. and noht for world &yogh;elpe. God nele &thorn;et we beon gredie &yogh;itseras. ne ec for weorld &yogh;elpe for|worpan ure ehtan ah dele we ure ehtan mid wisdome. swa &thorn;et hit drihtne likie. and &yogh;if [we] almesse do&eth;; don hi butan &yogh;elpe &thorn;enne ma&yogh;e we fordon swa &thorn;a deofliche &yogh;itsunge. &THORN;e feor&eth;e mihte is. <I>paciencia.</I> &thorn;et is on englisc i&thorn;uld. &thorn;et &thorn;e mon beo i&thorn;uldi. and &thorn;olemod for godes luue. and lete elchur<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &aelig;fre.</NOTE> his iwit weldre &thorn;ene his wre&eth;&eth;e. for&eth;on &thorn;e helend cwe&eth; &thorn;us on his godspel. <I>In paciencia uestra possidebitis animas uestras.</I> &thorn;et is on englisc. on eower i&thorn;ulde &yogh;e habbe&eth; eower saulen ihaldene and eft &thorn;e heouenlich[e] wisdom cwe&eth;. <I>Ira requiescit in sinu stulti.</I> &thorn;et is wre&eth;&eth;e haf&eth; wununge on &thorn;es dusian bosme. &thorn;et is &thorn;enne &thorn;e mon bi&eth; to red|mod. and &thorn;e al weldenda dema deme&eth; eou mid rihtwisnesse. and we sculen mid i&thorn;ulde ouercuman &thorn;a wre&eth;&eth;e. &THORN;e fifte mihte is. [<I>Spiritalis laetitia</I>] &thorn;et is gastliche blisse &thorn;et &thorn;e mon on god blissie bitwuxe &thorn;a sorinessen &thorn;issere sterke worlde. swa &thorn;et we<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. &thorn;e.</NOTE> on unilimpan to ormode ne beon; ne eft on iselh&eth;an to swi&eth;e ne blissian. and &yogh;if we forleosa&eth; &thorn;as lenan world-&thorn;ing; &thorn;enne we sculan witan &thorn;et ure wununge nis nauht her; ac is on heuene; &yogh;if we hopia&eth; to gode swa &thorn;e apostel seide bi him and bi o&eth;ran rihtwise. [<I>Nostra autem conversatio in celis est.</I>] &thorn;et is ure wununge is on heuene. &thorn;ider we sculen <MILESTONE N="39b" UNIT="folio">hih&yogh;en of &thorn;issere erfe&eth;|nesse mid gastlichere blisse. &thorn;enne bi&eth; &thorn;a ufele sarinesse mid alle ouercuman mid ure gode i&thorn;ulde. &THORN;e sixte mihte is. [<I>Instantia</I> 
<PB REF="00000171.tif" N="107"> <I>boni operis.</I>] &thorn;et is anrednesse godes werkes. for &yogh;if weo beo&eth; anrede on ure gode werckan; &thorn;enne ma&yogh;e we swa ouercumen &thorn;a slau&eth;e. for hit bi&eth; lonsum bismer &yogh;if al ure life bi&eth; on unnet her. &THORN;e seofe&eth;e mihte is. [<I>Caritas</I>.] &thorn;et is so&eth; luue to gode and to monnen. &thorn;et weo on gode weorcas godes luue kepan; and naut idel&yogh;elp &thorn;e is him ansete. ac uten don elmessen swa he us tehte gode to luue. and naut for herunge. ac &thorn;et ure drihten beo eure ihered on ure godan weorcan. and &thorn;e idele &yogh;elp us beo eure un|wur&eth;. &THORN;e eahtu&eth;e mihte is ihaten. [<I>Humilitas</I>.] &thorn;et is so&eth; edmodnesse to gode and to monnen. mid modes lusternesse.<NOTE PLACE="marg">? hlutter|ness.</NOTE> for &thorn;e &thorn;e bi&eth; [wis] he neme<NOTE PLACE="marg">? ne wur&eth; neure.</NOTE> modi. On hwan mei &thorn;e mon modegian &thorn;eh he beo wel i&thorn;o&yogh;en and i&thorn;ungen. for he mei findan fele &thorn;e beo&eth; bet i&thorn;o&yogh;en and isto&yogh;en &thorn;ene he. Ne eft he ne mei on his welan. ne on his ehte modegian. for&eth;on &thorn;et he nat &thorn;ene dei ne &thorn;ene time &thorn;e hit al forletan scal. Ne on nane &thorn;inge ne ah &thorn;e mon to modegian. &yogh;if he wis bi&eth;. nu<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. hu.</NOTE> &yogh;e habbe&eth; iherd hu &thorn;es halie mihten ouercuma&eth; <MILESTONE N="40a" UNIT="folio">&thorn;a sunnan &thorn;e deouel bisawe&eth; on us. and &yogh;if we nelle&eth; heom ouercuman. hi bisenche&eth; us on helle. [W]e ma&yogh;en &thorn;urh godes fulste &thorn;a fondliche sunnan mid icompe ouercuman. &yogh;if we kenliche fehta&eth; and habban<NOTE PLACE="marg">? <I>originally</I> habbe&eth;.</NOTE> us on ende &thorn;ene eche wur&eth;ment a mid gode seoluan. &yogh;if we swinca&eth; nu her. Nv beo&eth; .xii. un&thorn;eawes. &thorn;e we sculen eou seggan erest on bocleden; and si&eth;&thorn;an on englisc. <I>Duodecim abusiua sunt seculi. Hoc est. Sapiens sine operibus bonis. Senex sine religione. Ado|lescens sine obediencia. Diues sine elemosina. Femina sine pudicitia. Dominus sine uirtute. Christianus contenciosus. Pauper superbus. Rex iniquus. Episcopus negligens. Plebs. sine disciplina. Populus sine lege &amp; sic suffocatur iusticia dei</I>.</P>
<P>[T]welf un&thorn;eawes beo&eth; on &thorn;issere weorlde to hermen alle monnen. &yogh;if hi moten rixian and hi alegga&eth; rihtwis|nesse. and &thorn;ene ileafan amerra&eth;. and moncun bringe&eth; &yogh;if hi motan to helle. &THORN;et is &yogh;if &thorn;e wisa mon bi&eth; butan [gode wercan. and &yogh;if &thorn;e alde bi&eth; butan<NOTE PLACE="marg">See p. 109, l. 3.</NOTE>] treuscipe. and &yogh;if &thorn;e &yogh;unge bi&eth; butan hersumnesse. and &thorn;e richen butan elmesdedan. wif butan clenesse. and &thorn;e lauerd butan mihte. and &yogh;if &thorn;e cristene mon 
<PB REF="00000173.tif" N="109"> bi&eth; sacful. and &yogh;if &thorn;e wrecche bi&eth; modi. and &yogh;if &thorn;e king <MILESTONE N="40b" UNIT="folio">bi&eth; unrihtwis. and &yogh;if &thorn;e biscop bi&eth; &yogh;emeles. and &thorn;et folc butan steore eft<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE> butan la&yogh;e. Nu &yogh;if &thorn;e wisa mon bi&eth; butan gode wercan. &thorn;e &thorn;e o&eth;er monnen scolde sullan gode bisne. hu ne bi&eth; sone his lare &thorn;an lewede monnen unwur&eth;. &yogh;if he seolf nule don swa swa he heom teche&eth; to donne; Ne bi&eth; naut his lare fremful ne icweme &thorn;an ileweden; &yogh;if he mid wercan to-werpe&eth; his bodunge. Eft &yogh;if &thorn;e lar&eth;eu dwela&eth;. hwa bi&eth; si&eth;&eth;an his lar&thorn;eu; Gif &thorn;et e&yogh;e ablinda&eth;; ne bi&eth; naut &thorn;e hond wel lokinde. &THORN;e alde mon &thorn;e bi&eth; butan treowscipe. bi&eth; iliche &thorn;an treo &thorn;e bere&eth; lef and blosman. and nane westmas ne bere&eth;. and bi&eth; unwur&eth; his lauerde. Hwet is eure swa dusi and swa stuntlic swa is &thorn;et &thorn;e alde mon nule his mod to gode awendan mid gode huhte. &thorn;enne his leoman him cu&thorn;a&eth; &thorn;et he ne bi&eth; quic longe; &YOGH;unge monnan mei tweonian hwe&eth;er hi moten alibban. ac &thorn;e alde mei him witan iwis &thorn;one de&eth;. &ETH;an alden his to warniene wi&eth; uuele i&thorn;ohtas for &thorn;eo heorte ne alde&eth; naut ne &thorn;a tunge. ac &thorn;as twa &thorn;ing deria&eth; oft &thorn;an alden. Wite for &thorn;i &thorn;e alde alde<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE> hwet is elde bihouige. and &thorn;a &eth;ing for|seo &thorn;at his saule deria&eth;. &THORN;e &thorn;ridde un&thorn;eau is on &thorn;issere worlde. &thorn;et &yogh;ung mon beo butan ihersumnesse. <MILESTONE N="41a" UNIT="folio">vnwur&eth;e bi&eth; &thorn;e on elde &thorn;et him o&eth;er men &thorn;enien<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. we|nien.</NOTE> &thorn;e on his &yogh;uhe&eth;e nule his eldian<NOTE PLACE="marg">? eldran.</NOTE> her|sumian. Vre helend on his &yogh;uhe&eth;e wes ihersum his cunne. and his heouenlich federe he hersumede to &eth;a de&eth;e. Swa swa &thorn;an alden bihoua&eth; du&yogh;ende &thorn;ewas and [t]riwe treofestnesse; swa birise&eth; &thorn;an &yogh;ungan &thorn;et he abbe ihersumnesse and ibuhsumnesse. Godes la&yogh;e bit ec mon wur&eth;ie efre his feder and his moder mid muche|lere wur&thorn;unge. and &yogh;if he heom werie&eth;; he bi&eth; de&eth;es wur&eth;e. &THORN;e feor&eth;e un&thorn;eu is &thorn;et &thorn;e riche mon [beo] butan elmesdedan. and bihude his feh. and &yogh;eornliche halde hit him to helle wite. vniseli bi&eth; &thorn;e &yogh;itsere &thorn;e &thorn;urh his iselh&eth;e leosa&eth;. and &thorn;urh his ah&yogh;ene ehte forwur&eth; a on echnesse. ac iselie beo&eth; efre &thorn;a mildheortan. for &thorn;i heo imeta&eth; &thorn;a mildheortnesse. Eft &thorn;e &eth;e dele&eth; elmessan for his drihtnes luuan; &thorn;e bihut his gold hord on heouene riche. &thorn;er nan &thorn;eof ne mei [his] ma&eth;mas forsteolan. ac heo beo&eth; bi hundfalde ihalden him &thorn;er. On monie wisen mon mei wurchen elmessan. on ete and on wete. and ec on iwedan. and &thorn;et mon gistas 
<PB REF="00000175.tif" N="111"> underuo. and to seke monan ga. o&eth;er sarine frefra&eth;. o&eth;er blindne mon let. o&eth;er bere&eth; unhalne. o&eth;er unhalne lechna&eth; &yogh;if he leche|dom con. <MILESTONE N="41b" UNIT="folio">o&eth;er &yogh;if he miltsa&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. nult|sa&eth;.</NOTE> &thorn;an men &thorn;e hine abelh. o&eth;er &yogh;if he &yogh;eher-godne<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>? insert here</I> efter neode ide&eth;.</NOTE> mon fere&eth; to buriene. Al &thorn;is bi&eth; almesse and ec &thorn;et mon biswinke &thorn;ene stunte lichome for steore &thorn;e &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE> steoran scal for &thorn;et is mildheortnesse. &thorn;et &thorn;e wisa mon mid steore &thorn;ene unwisan irihleche. Ne ligge nefre on &thorn;ine heorde. &thorn;et hauelese monnam meie fremian. for &thorn;u ane ne brukest naut &thorn;inra welena; &thorn;ah &thorn;u hi demliche<NOTE PLACE="marg">? dernliche.</NOTE> halde. &ETH;u gederast mare and mare. and men cwela&eth; on hungre. and &thorn;ine welan forrotia&eth; biforan &thorn;ine eh&yogh;an. Ne don we nauht &thorn;us. ac uten don al swa ure drihten cwe&eth;. he seide on his godspelle. <I>Date elemosinam; &amp; omnia munda sun[t] uobis.</I> &thorn;et is. dele&eth; elmesse and alle &thorn;ing eou beo&eth; clene. &THORN;e fifta un&thorn;eu is &thorn;et wif beo buten clenesse. Vnclene wif &thorn;ole&eth; scome on weorlde. and unclene wif bi&eth; unwur&eth; on liue. and efter &thorn;isse liue nane blisse naf&eth; mid gode. Wisdom birise&eth; weran. and clenesse birisa&eth; wifan. for &thorn;e clenesse iscilt heo wi&eth; u[n]&thorn;eawes. &ETH;er &thorn;a clenesse bi&eth;; &thorn;er beo&eth; ec &thorn;a gode &thorn;eawes and &thorn;et clene wif scuna&eth; &yogh;itsunge and cheste ne stura&eth;. ac heo gestil&eth; groman and forsih&eth; galnesse and gredinesse for|ho&yogh;a&eth;. heo hi werna&eth; wi&eth; drunkenesse and idele weord <MILESTONE N="42a" UNIT="folio">ne luua&eth;. Iwisliche &thorn;a clennesse iwelt alle un&thorn;eawes and halt gode &thorn;eawes &thorn;e gode likia&eth; and monnan. [&THORN;]e sixte un&thorn;eau is &thorn;et &thorn;e&eth;e to lauerde bi&eth; iset. &thorn;et he for modleste ne mei his monnan don stere ac bi&eth; swa mihtles on his modes streche. &thorn;et he his men eisian ne der ne to nane wisdome heom nule wissian. Summe lauerdes inehleche&eth; gode &thorn;urh heore lauer[d]scipe swa Moyses &thorn;e hereto&yogh;a dude &thorn;e to &thorn;an almihti&yogh;an gode spec. and summe lauerdes on heore onwalde god gremia&eth;. swa saul &thorn;e king dude &thorn;e forsech godes heste. &ETH;e lauerd scal beon li&eth;e &thorn;an godan and eisful &thorn;an dusian &thorn;et he heore dusi alegge. and he scal beon weordfeste. and wise lare lusten. Hine scule &thorn;a gode men lufie for his li&eth;nesse. and &thorn;a dusian him sculen efre adredan. elles ne bi&eth; his rixlunge ne fest ne lonsum. he scal beon swa iweorht &thorn;et him mon mote wi&eth; speken and his neode menan. and swa hwet swa &thorn;e lauerd speke to his men sterliche; do hit for rihtwisnesse 
<PB REF="00000177.tif" N="113"> and for godes e&yogh;e and noht for wre&eth;&eth;e. hit is awriten on boken. &thorn;et &thorn;e bi&eth; al swa sculdig &thorn;e &thorn;et uuel i&thorn;eua&eth;; swa &thorn;e &thorn;e hit de&eth;. &yogh;if he hit betan mei; and umbe &thorn;e bota[ne] ho&yogh;a&eth;. he scal hine mid rih[t] wisnesse ibu&yogh;an to gode. for he ne mei habben nane mihte <MILESTONE N="42b" UNIT="folio">to rihte butan godes fulste swa god cwe&eth;. &ETH;e lauerd scal bihoh&yogh;ian &thorn;et he habbe godes fultum and he ne scal nohwer ortrowian bi godes fultum. Gif god bi&eth; his ifulsta; ne bi&eth; his mehte nohwer for-se&yogh;en. for &thorn;on &thorn;e nan mihte nis bute of gode. <I>Qui suscitat de puluere egenum. &amp; de stercore erigit pauperem.</I> &thorn;et is. God ahef of mexe &thorn;ene mon &thorn;e he wule &thorn;au he were er wreche and maca&eth; hine to lauerde and eft &thorn;e witega sei&eth; bi gode. <I>Deponit potentes de sede &amp; exaltat humiles.</I> &thorn;et is. Drihten aworpe&eth; &thorn;a modian of heore heh setle and on-hef&eth; &thorn;a mildan and eft &thorn;et writ cwe&eth;. <I>Deus superbis resistit; humilibus dat gratiam.</I> &thorn;et is. Drihten widset &thorn;an prudan and &yogh;eue&eth; &thorn;an ed|meodan strein&thorn;e &thorn;et al middel eard beo him ibuhsum; and his nome heri&yogh;e. &THORN;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">The &thorn; is by a later hand.</NOTE> seofe&eth;e un-&thorn;eaw is &thorn;et &thorn;e cristene mon beo sacful. of cristes noman. is cristianus icwe&eth;en. &thorn;et is &thorn;e cristene mon &thorn;e is on criste ifuleh&yogh;ad. &thorn;enne &yogh;if he bi&eth; sacful; so&eth;liche ne bi&eth; he noht wel cristene. So&eth;liche nis nan mon wel cristene; butan &thorn;e &thorn;e criste euenleche&eth;. Crist nalde flitan ne chidan. swa swa his feder stefne cwe&eth; bi him. Her is min child &thorn;e me is swi&eth;e leof and ic sette minne gast ouer him. He ne flit mid cheste. ne he sake ne stura&eth;. ne on strete ne ihere&eth; nan mon his stefne. Drihten sei&eth; ec on his godspelle &thorn;et &thorn;a beo&eth; godes bern &thorn;e beo&eth; isibsumme ac sake ne sturia&eth;. and swa swa [&thorn;a] isibsumma <MILESTONE N="43a" UNIT="folio">beo&eth; so&eth;liche godes bern; swa beo&eth; ec &thorn;a sacfulle so&eth;liche deofles bern. Alle we cleopia&eth; to gode; and cwe&eth;a&eth;. pater noster. &thorn;et is. &thorn;u ure feder &thorn;e ert on heuene ac we ne ma&yogh;en habben &thorn;ene heouenlichen e&thorn;el; butan we beon clene from alle sake. [&THORN;]e ehtu&eth;e un&thorn;eau is &thorn;et &thorn;e wrecche mon beo modi. Moni mon naf&eth; ehta. and &thorn;eh haue&eth; modinesse and is erm for worlde. and uniseli for gode. &thorn;enne he arere&eth; his mod mid modinesse on&yogh;ein god. and nule on his erm&eth;e; edmodnesse halden. Crist cwe&eth; on his godspelle bi &thorn;an gastliche wrecchan. <I>Beati pauperes spiritu; quoniam ipsorum est regnum celorum.</I> &thorn;et is. eadi&yogh;e beo&eth; &thorn;a wrecchan &thorn;e on gaste beo&eth; wrecchan; for 
<PB REF="00000179.tif" N="115"> heore is heouenriche murh&eth;e. &ETH;a beo&eth; wrecchan on gaste &thorn;e for godes luue beod milde and admode. for &thorn;on &thorn;e &thorn;es modes edmodnesse mei bi&yogh;etan godes riche re&eth;er &thorn;en &thorn;e haueleste &thorn;e of hen&eth;e cume&eth;. Gewisliche &thorn;a richan &thorn;e rihtliche libba&eth; ma&yogh;en beon bitwixen godes wrecchan &yogh;if heo edmodnesse habbe&eth; and ouerflowendnesse forleta&eth; swa swa &thorn;e king dauid cwe&eth; bi him seoluen. <I>Ego egenus &amp; pauper sum; deus adiuua me.</I> &thorn;et is. Ic em &thorn;arua and wrecche. ac god fulst &thorn;u me. &ETH;e modie wreccha for his modes upahefednesse is to richan itald rihtliche on boken and &thorn;e edmeda riche &thorn;ah he ehte habbe mei beon godes wrecche. &yogh;if he gode icweme&eth;. [&THORN;]e nih&yogh;e&eth;e un&thorn;eau is &thorn;et &thorn;e king beo unrih[t]wis. &ETH;e king bi&eth; icoren to &thorn;an &thorn;e him cu&eth; his noma. <MILESTONE N="43b" UNIT="folio">King is ihaten <I>rex</I>; &thorn;et is wisegend for he scal wissian mid wisdome his folke and unriht aleggen and &thorn;ene ileaue areren. &thorn;enne bi&eth; hit ermlic. &yogh;if he bi&eth; unrihtwis. for he ne mei nenne irihtlechan; &yogh;if he bi&eth; him seolf unrihtwis. &ETH;es kingges rihtwisnesse arere&eth; his kine setle and his sodfestnesse ista&thorn;ele&eth; &thorn;es folkes stere. &ETH;et is kinges rihtwisnesse &thorn;et he mid woh&yogh;e ne of-sitte ne ermne ne eadine. ac elche men deme riht. He scal biwerian widewan and steopbern and stale aleggen and heordom for-beodan. and &thorn;eouas addriuan. of his erde mid alle and he scal wicche creft aleggan and wi&yogh;elunge ne geman wise men him scule readan and he ne scal beo nefre wemod godes minist[re]<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>The con|traction is scarcely legible;? read</I> minstre.</NOTE> he scal mundian efre. and fedan wrecchan. and festliche winnan wi&eth; onsi&yogh;end-ne here. and haldan his e&thorn;el. He scal so&eth;feste men setten him to irefen. and for godes eie libban his lif rihtliche and beon on erfe&eth;nesse anred and edmod on stilnesse. and his of[s]pringe ne i&thorn;auie &thorn;et hi beon unrihtwise. he scal hine ibidan on a-sette tidan<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. ridan.</NOTE>. and er meltiman metes ne arinan. for hit is a|writen &thorn;et wa &thorn;ere &thorn;eode &thorn;er &thorn;e king bi&eth; child. and &thorn;er &thorn;a aldor|men eta&eth; on erne mar&yogh;en ula&yogh;eliche<NOTE PLACE="marg">? unla&yogh;e|liche.</NOTE>. Gif &thorn;e king wule mid carfulnesse haldan &thorn;as bebodan; &thorn;enne bi&eth; his riche isundful on liue. and efter &thorn;isse liue he scal faran to &thorn;an eche liue for his treowscipe. And &yogh;if he forsih&eth; &thorn;as isetnesse<MILESTONE N="44a" UNIT="folio"> and &thorn;as lare; &thorn;ene bi&eth; his erd ihened oft and ilome ei&eth;er &yogh;e on her&yogh;unge. &yogh;e on hungre. &yogh;e on cwalme. &yogh;e on uniwidere. &yogh;e on wilde deoran. 
<PB REF="00000181.tif" N="117"> Wite ec &thorn;e king hu hit is icwe&eth;en on boken. &yogh;if he rihtwisnesse ne halt. &thorn;et swa swa he is on heuene<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>read</I> on|houen.</NOTE> on his kine setle to-foran o&eth;er mennen; swa he bi&eth; eft ini&thorn;ered on &thorn;an neo&thorn;emeste pinan under &thorn;an unrihtwise deoule &thorn;e he er iherd and icwemde. [&THORN;]e teou&eth;e un&thorn;eau is &thorn;et biscop beo &yogh;emeles. Episcopus is gerkisc noma &thorn;et is on boc leden speculator. and is on englisc scawere. for he is iset to &thorn;on &thorn;et he scal ouerscawian mid his &yogh;eme &thorn;a lewedan. swa god seolf cwe&eth; to ezechiele &thorn;an witegan. <I>Specula|torem dedi te domui israel.</I> &thorn;et is. Ic &thorn;e &yogh;ef to scawere mine folke israeles hirede. &thorn;et &thorn;u ihere mine word and of mine mu&eth;e mine speche heom cu&eth;e. and &yogh;if &thorn;u &thorn;an unrihtwisan nult his unriht|wisnesse seggan; &thorn;enne swelt &thorn;e unrihtwise on his unrihtwis|nesse. and ic of-ga et &thorn;e mid groman his blod and &yogh;if &thorn;u wernast &thorn;ane unrihtwise mon and he nule icherran from his sunnan &thorn;urh &thorn;e; he swelt on his unrihtwisnesse and &thorn;ine saule bi&eth; alesed. &ETH;us speked ure drihten to biscopan. Nu &yogh;if &thorn;e biscop bi&eth; &yogh;emeles &thorn;enne he godes budel is and to lar&thorn;eawe iset &thorn;an leawede folke; &thorn;enne losia&eth; fele saulen and he seolf for&eth; mid for his &yogh;emeleste. ac &thorn;et folc bi&eth; iseli &thorn;urh snoterne biscop &thorn;e heom sei&eth; godes lare. and halt heom under gode swa god heo&yogh;te<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>read</I> heorde.</NOTE> &thorn;et heo beon ihaldene and he habbe<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>originally</I> habbenen.</NOTE> &thorn;e mede. [&THORN;]e endleofte un&thorn;eau is folc beo butan steore. fela stuntnesse beo&eth;; &thorn;er <MILESTONE N="44b" UNIT="folio">nan steore ne bi&eth;. and &thorn;er &thorn;e dusie mon bi&eth; &thorn;riste. and &thorn;er &thorn;e dwolunge rixa&eth;; &thorn;ere bi&eth; uuel to wunienne eni wise men. and for &thorn;on cwe&eth; &thorn;e salmwurhta mid &thorn;ise<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. wise</NOTE> wurden cleopiende. <I>Apprehendite disciplinam nequando irascatur dominus &amp; pereatis de uia iusta.</I> &thorn;et is on englisc. Vnderfo&eth; steore &thorn;i les &eth;e god iwur&eth;e wra&eth; wi&eth; eou and &yogh;e &thorn;enne losian of &thorn;an rihtan weie. Ec &thorn;e apostel paulus cwe&eth; on his pistel &ETH;ur&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &ETH;urh.</NOTE>-wunia&eth; on steore and &yogh;e beo&eth; swilche forli&yogh;eres. &yogh;if &yogh;e libba&eth; butan steore. Eft &thorn;e witega ysaias bi &thorn;an ilcan cwe&eth;. <I>Quiescite agere peruerse. discite bene facere.</I> &thorn;et is iswike&eth; unrihtwisra dedan; and leornia&eth; god to wurchenne. and dauid cwe&eth; ec. <I>Declina a malo &amp; fac bonum.</I> &thorn;et is. Buh from uuele and do god. Gif &thorn;u uuel were; iwend &thorn;e from uuele. &thorn;i les &thorn;e &eth;u steorles losie on ende. [&THORN;e] twelfta un&eth;eau is. &thorn;et folc beo butan la&yogh;e. we ne moten halden nu Moises la&yogh;e on &thorn;a alde 
<PB REF="00000183.tif" N="119"> wisan efter ure helendes to-cume. ac we sculen &yogh;efullan swa we best mu&yogh;en &thorn;es helendes biboda. and &thorn;a beo&eth; us for la&yogh;e for we beo&eth; efre butan gode; &yogh;if we godes bibodan ne halde&eth;. Monie &thorn;ewas<NOTE PLACE="marg">? we&yogh;es.</NOTE> beo&eth; swa swa &thorn;e wisdom cleopa&eth;. &thorn;e monnen &thorn;unche&eth; rihte. ac hi &thorn;ah leda&eth; to de&eth;e on ende &thorn;a &thorn;e heom duseliche fol&yogh;ia&eth;. &ETH;e &thorn;e godes la&yogh;e forlet &thorn;e is ure wei; he scal misliche faran on monie gedwil&thorn;an. Crist seolf is &thorn;e weie; swa he seide bi him <I>Ego sum uia ueritas &amp; uita.</I> &thorn;et is. Ic em &thorn;e wei and &thorn;a so&eth;festnesse and &thorn;et eche lif ne mei nan man bicuman to mine heouenliche federe butan &thorn;urh me. ac we beo&eth; &thorn;urh crist to heouene ibroht; &yogh;if we his bigenge halda&eth;. <MILESTONE N="45a" UNIT="folio">&ETH;a &thorn;e butan godes la&yogh;e and godes isetnesse libbe&eth;; &thorn;a beo&eth; butan gode efre wuni|ende. Drihten seolf bihat &thorn;is alle &thorn;on &thorn;e halde&eth; his biboden. <I>Ecce ego uobiscum sum omnibus diebus usque ad consummacio|nem seculi</I>. &thorn;et is. ic seolf beo mid eow alle da&yogh;en a&thorn;et endunge &thorn;issere weorlde. &ETH;e helen[de] us iwissie to his willan efre &thorn;et ure saule moten eft-si&eth;ian to him efter ure liue to &thorn;an eche liue. &thorn;et he ure saule underfo &thorn;e he er asende to &thorn;an lichoman. <I>Quod</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. quo&eth;.</NOTE> <I>ipse prestare dignetur qui uiuit &amp; regnat deus per omnia secula seculorum. Amen.</I></P>
