<DIV2 N="11" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XI. [DOMINICA V. QUADRAGESIM&AElig;.]</HEAD>
<P><I>[F]actus est filius dei omnibus sibi obtemperantibus causa salutis eterne; apellatus a deo pontifex iuxsta ordinem Melchisedech.</I></P>
<P>Vre drihtnes halie passiun. &thorn;et is his halie &thorn;rowunge &thorn;e he for moncunne underfeng. is nu icumen in. and &thorn;e halie writ us mune&yogh;a&eth; and hat. &thorn;et we beon imundie of &thorn;ere pine &thorn;e ure drihten &thorn;olede for us on &thorn;isse timan. and for-&thorn;i we sculen hine efre mid alle ure heorte. and mid alle ure mode herian and swi&thorn;est on &thorn;issere halie tide &thorn;e is nu icumen to us. and we 
<PB REF="00000185.tif" N="121"> sculan &thorn;onkian him &thorn;ere muchele mildheortnesse &thorn;e he dude on us &thorn;a he na sparede na ihesu crist his a&yogh;ene sune ac salde hine to de&eth;e for moncunne al swa we singe&eth; on boken. <I>proprio filio suo non pepercit deus. Sed pro nobis omnibus tradidit illum.</I> &ETH;et is. God ne sparede na his a&yogh;ene berne; ac &yogh;ef hine to cwale for us alle. eft &thorn;e apostel sei&eth; on his pistel. <I>Cristus factus est pro nobis obediens patri usque ad mortem mortem autem crucis</I>. Crist godes sune wes ibuhsum &thorn;an heuenliche federe to &thorn;a de&eth;e. and &thorn;et to swulche <MILESTONE N="45b" UNIT="folio">de&eth;e swa &yogh;e ma&yogh;en iseon on &thorn;ere rode tacne to-foren eou. Mid irenen neilen he wes on &thorn;ere rode ifestned. and mid speres orde to &thorn;ere heorte istungen. and mid &thorn;ornene crune his heaued wes icruned. swa &thorn;et &thorn;et rede blod seh ut on iwulche half. and &thorn;et folc &thorn;e hine &thorn;us makede knewede to-foren him on bismer and hine greite and cleopede king on bismer. Summe &thorn;er weren &thorn;et his e&yogh;an bundan and hine on &thorn;et neb mid heore hondan stercliche beoten and hehten hine aredan; hwa hit were &thorn;et hine smite. &ETH;as pine and monie o&eth;re ure drihten &thorn;olede of &eth;an he&eth;ene folke in &thorn;isse timan. al swa &thorn;e prophete heffede iboded &thorn;a he seide bi him. <I>O uos omnes qui transitis per uiam; attendite &amp; uidete si est dolor similis dolori meo.</I> &thorn;et is Ge alle &thorn;e fera&eth; &thorn;ene wei; abida&eth; and understonda&eth; and lokia&eth; hew&eth;er enies monnes sar beo iliche mine sare. Imong alle &thorn;ere pine &thorn;e he for us &thorn;olede; ne undude he nefre ene his mu&eth; mid uuele to-&yogh;eines nan of heom al swa &thorn;et writ seide bi him muchel to-foran. <I>Dominus tanquam ouis ad uictimam ductus est; &amp; non aperuit os suum.</I> Vre drihten wes iled to sle&yogh;e al swa me dede a scep and he nefre &thorn;a ne undude his mu&eth;. His ah&yogh;enes &thorn;onkes he &thorn;rowede for us and binom ure sunnan. for &yogh;if hit his willa nere; ne mahte him nan de&eth; ne nan pine denan<NOTE PLACE="marg">? <I>for</I> derian.</NOTE>; al swa &thorn;e boc sei&eth;. <I>Oblatus est quia ipse uoluit; &amp; peccata ipse por|tauit.</I> &thorn;et is ure drihten wes ioffred for-&thorn;i &thorn;e he hit walde and aber ure sunnan. and &thorn;ah ne nedde he na &thorn;et he&eth;ene folc to his cwale ac &thorn;e deofel heom tuhte to &thorn;an werke and god i&thorn;eafede &thorn;et to <MILESTONE N="46a" UNIT="folio">alesendnesse alles ileffulles moncunnes. and &thorn;e deofel ablende heore heortan &thorn;et heo ne cunnan icnawen ure helend &thorn;e wes imong heom. <I>Quia si principes mundi huius Christum 
<PB REF="00000187.tif" N="123"> cognouissent nunquam illum crucifixissent.</I> &ETH;et is to seggane. Gif &thorn;a hefdmen of &thorn;issere worlde hefden icnawen crist; nefden heo nefre ifestned hine on rode for ure hele. Cristes rihtwis|nesse is swa muchel &thorn;et he nolde niman moncun nedunga of &eth;an deofle butan he hit forgulte. ac he hit forgulte eteliche &thorn;a &thorn;e he tuhte and spuhte &thorn;et folc to cristes cwale; &thorn;es almihtie godes sune. and &thorn;a &thorn;urh his deorewur&eth;e de&eth;e we weren alesede from &thorn;an eche dea&eth;e. &YOGH;if we us seolue nu ne fordo&eth; &thorn;urh sunnan. &ETH;a itimede &thorn;an deofle alswa de&eth; mah&yogh;e fisce &thorn;e isi&eth; &thorn;et es. and ne isih&yogh; na &thorn;ene hoc &thorn;e stica&eth; on &thorn;an ese. &thorn;enne bi&eth; he gredi &thorn;es eses and forswole&yogh;e&eth; &thorn;ene hoc for&eth; mid &thorn;an ese. Swa wes &thorn;on deofle. He iseh &thorn;a monnisnesse on criste and nauht &thorn;a god|cunnesse. &ETH;a tuhte he &eth;et he&eth;ene folc to his sle&yogh;e and ifelde &thorn;a &thorn;ene hoc &thorn;et wes cristes godcumnesse<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE>. &thorn;e ferde to helle and iwra&eth; &thorn;ene alde deouel and nom of him adam &thorn;ene frumscepene mon. and his wif euan and alle &thorn;a &thorn;e of heore cunne on &thorn;is liue gode icwemden. Ne nom he na alle &thorn;a &thorn;e &thorn;er inne weren ah ane dale alswa me bit of ane epple; for hit wes awriten &thorn;urh &thorn;an prophete. <I>O mors ero mors tua morsus tuus ero in|ferne.</I> &thorn;et is. &ETH;u dea&eth; ic wulle beon &thorn;in de&eth;; and &thorn;u helle ic wulle beon &thorn;in bite. and &thorn;a ifelde &thorn;e deofel &thorn;ene hoc. &thorn;e he er gredliche forswealh for ure drihten <MILESTONE N="46b" UNIT="folio">aras of dea&eth;e on &thorn;ene sunnen dei &thorn;e we hate&eth; easter dei. &thorn;e nu bi&eth; to dei on fowertene niht. and alesde us &yogh;if we wulle&eth; of &thorn;an eche dea&eth;e &thorn;e is on helle &thorn;e we weren in bifolen &thorn;urh ure eldra gult. ah we sculen don nu al swa &thorn;e mon &thorn;e bi&eth; efter criste selue cristene mon inemned &thorn;et wit and &thorn;ene wisdom &thorn;e ure drihten us sende aspenen we hit on godes willan and on godes wercan. and us seluan to helpe herien we ure drihten &thorn;e us alesde and makede us freo of &thorn;eowan and of &thorn;relan his ah&yogh;ene bern. Luuian we hine mid alre heorte. mid alre saulen. mid alle mode. mid alle meine alswa &thorn;e apostel Sancte Iohannes us muna&eth;. <I>Diligamus deum quia ipse prior dilexit nos.</I> &ETH;et is luuian we ure drihten. for &thorn;on &thorn;e he luuede us er we hine. Muchele luue he us cudde &thorn;a he us alesde. Nefde he nane neode to us ac we hefden muchele neode to him. Git we sculen mare. we sculan luuian ure nehstan 
<PB REF="00000189.tif" N="125"> &thorn;et is al cristene folc alswa us seoluan. for alle we beo&eth; ibro&eth;ran. Alle we habbe&eth; enne feder on heouene and alle we cleopia&eth; to him and segga&eth;. <I>Pater noster qui es in celis</I>. Vre feder &thorn;e ert in heouene. Ne sei&eth; ure nan min<NOTE PLACE="marg">n is partly erased.</NOTE> feder ne &thorn;in feder ah ure feder &thorn;e ert in heouene alswa baldeliche mei &thorn;e wrechesta mon clepian drihtan him to federe swa &thorn;e richeste mon of &thorn;an londe for-&thorn;i ah nan mon to beoran ni&eth; ne onde to nane cristene monne; al swa Sancte iohan sei&eth; in his pistelle. <I>Qui odit fratrem suum manet in morte</I>. &ETH;e mon &thorn;e heta&eth; his bro&eth;er he wuna&eth; in dea&eth;e and ef(t) &thorn;e ilca apostel sei&eth;. <I>Qui dicit se diligere dominum &amp; fratrem suum odit; mendax est</I>. &ETH;e mon &eth;e sei&eth; &thorn;et he luua&eth; <MILESTONE N="47a" UNIT="folio">god. and hate&eth; his bro&thorn;er he is lih&yogh;are. for &thorn;e mon &thorn;e ne luua&eth; na his bro&eth;er &thorn;e he isi&eth;. hu mei he luuian wel ure drihten &thorn;e he naut ne isih&eth;; Imong &thorn;an muchela wisdoma &thorn;e ure drihten lerde his apostles he tahte heom. &thorn;is swulche to|foran o&eth;ran &thorn;ingan; and cwe&eth;. <I>Hoc est preceptum meum ut diligatis inuicem sicut dilexi uos</I>. &ETH;is is min bibode and min heste. &thorn;et &yogh;e luuian eou bitwixan alswa ic luuede eou. and for-&thorn;i scal iwilc mon o&eth;erne luuian. <I>Non uerbo neque lingua sed opere &amp; ueritate</I>. &thorn;et is naut one mid worde ne mid tunge; ac ec mid worke and mid so&eth;festnesse. and ure drihten and ure alesend iunne us allen &thorn;et we swa on &thorn;isse liue ma&yogh;en his hest and his biboden halden; &thorn;et we moten habben to mede heouenariches blisse. <I>Auxiliante domino nostro ihesu Christo qui uiuit &amp; regnat per omnia secula seculorum. amen.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="12" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XII. [DOMINICA SECUNDA POST PASCHA.]</HEAD>
<P><I>Christus passus est pro nobis uobis relinquens exemplum. ut sequimini uestigia eius &amp; cetera.</I> Al &thorn;et me ret and singe&eth; on &thorn;isse timan in halie chirche. al hit bilimpe&eth; to godes luue; and to godes herunge. &ETH;a songes &thorn;a we nu singe&eth; beo&eth; blisfulle for heo bo&eth; makede of &thorn;ere heouenliche blisse &thorn;e us wes 
<PB REF="00000191.tif" N="127"> iopenad on &thorn;isse timan &thorn;e ure drihten aras of dea&eth;e and alesde us of &thorn;an eche de&eth;e and wule us bringan to eche liue. Muchele luue ure drihten us cudde &thorn;a &thorn;e he &thorn;e is and eure wes butan biginnunge so&eth; god bicom for ure helpe so&eth; mon. <I>In simili|tudinem hominum factus &amp; habitu inuentus ut homo.</I> &thorn;et is he wes imacad to monne ilicnesse and iwunden mid flesce al swa mon and muchele <MILESTONE N="47b" UNIT="folio">mare luue he scawede us &thorn;a &thorn;e he us alesde for hit is awriten. <I>Nichil nobis nasci profuit; nisi redimi pro|fuisset.</I> &ETH;et is. Ne fremede us na &thorn;ing &thorn;et he<NOTE PLACE="marg">? we.</NOTE> were iboren; buten he us alesde. Mid swi&eth;e muchele wur&eth;e we weren alesde al swa. Sancte peter us seide and cwe&eth;. <I>Non ex coruptibili auro uel argento redempti estis de uestra uana conuersatione; sed pre|cioso sanguine agni inmaculati &amp; incontaminati ihesu Christi filii dei</I>. &ETH;et is to seggen. Ge ne beo&eth; ne alesde of deofles anwalde mid golde ne mid seolure; ac beo&eth; mid &thorn;an deorewur&thorn;e bleode of &thorn;an clenan and of &thorn;an unwemmedan lombe &eth;et is godes sune. He is &thorn;et so&eth;e lomb alswa. Sancte Iohan &thorn;e baptist cwe&eth;. <I>Qui tollit peccata mundi.</I> &thorn;e binime&eth; middanerdes sunne. his deorewur&thorn;e blod wes asced on stude &thorn;e is ihaten. <I>caluarie locus</I>. al swa &thorn;e godspellere us sei&eth;. &ETH;er hit wes agoten <I>In remissionem peccatorum nostrorum.</I> &ETH;et is alesendnesse of ure sunnan. Mid his blode we sculen deihwanliche<NOTE PLACE="marg">? deihwam|liche.</NOTE> &thorn;a postles and &thorn;et ouerslaht of ure huse &thorn;et is of ure heortan gastliche bispren|gan. &thorn;et is to understondan &thorn;et we sculen ure forheafod and &thorn;a. vii. &yogh;eade ures lichomes mid &thorn;ere halie rode tacne seinian &thorn;et ure wi&eth;erwinna. <I>Qui tanquam leo rugiens circuit querens quem deuoret.</I> &thorn;et is &thorn;et &thorn;e deofel &thorn;e ge&eth; abutan alswa &thorn;e gredie leo sechinde hwen he ma&yogh;e fordon &thorn;et he neure ne ma&yogh;e cuman wi&eth;-innan us. hwet beo&eth; &thorn;as .vii. &yogh;eate; &ETH;et beo&eth; ure e&yogh;an and ure neose and ure mu&eth; and ure earan. vppon heom alswa we er seiden we sculen markian &thorn;et tacne of &thorn;ere halie rode. <I>In qua triumphauit rex angelorum.</I> &thorn;et is of &thorn;ere rode of <MILESTONE N="48a" UNIT="folio">hwem englan king ouercom &thorn;ene deofel. for &thorn;et inseil &thorn;e &thorn;e deofel ne mei nefre to breocan. &thorn;et is &thorn;et [loc] &thorn;e&eth;e deofel ne con unlucan. &thorn;et is &thorn;et scutles &thorn;e&eth;e deofel ne mei nefre to-cysan. Bi &thorn;isse tacne seide sum wis mon. <I>Hec est scala peccatorum per quam Christus rex</I> 
<PB REF="00000193.tif" N="129"> <I>celorum ad se traxit omnia</I>. &ETH;is is sunfulla monna leddre &thorn;urh hwam<NOTE PLACE="marg">? hwan.</NOTE> ure drihtan teh to him al moncun. &thorn;urh &thorn;is tacne &thorn;e king constantinus ouer com al &thorn;et folc &thorn;e feiht to-&yogh;eines him. &ETH;urh &thorn;isse tacne makede Moyses &thorn;et &eth;et weter of egipte wes li&eth;e and swete &thorn;an folce of israel. &thorn;e wes sur and bitere alle &thorn;on monnen of &thorn;an londe. Eft &thorn;urh &thorn;isse tacne Moyses werp ut &thorn;et welle weter of &thorn;an herda flinte and &yogh;ef &thorn;an folke drinken uppan &thorn;an hulle synai. On o&eth;er wise ure drihten us mehte alesan &yogh;if his wille were. ac him &thorn;uhte bicumelic &thorn;et we &thorn;e weren &thorn;urh &thorn;e treo forgult in to helle; weren. eft &thorn;urh &thorn;et treo of &thorn;ere rode alesede. Of &thorn;issere alesednesse and of &thorn;an icompe &thorn;e ure drihten hefde wi&eth; &thorn;ene feond; dauid &thorn;e prophete seide &thorn;o he wes on eor&eth;e. <I>Liberauit pauperem a potente &amp; pauperem cui non erat adiutor</I>. &ETH;et is on englisc. Drihten alesde &thorn;ene wrechan of &thorn;an mehti&yogh;an and &thorn;en werchan &thorn;e wes al helples. &ETH;es wrecche &thorn;e he of spec wes ure feder adam. &thorn;e bicom wreche and helples swa sone swa he to-brec godes bibode and godes heste. vre drihten &thorn;e hine iscop ne macode hine na wrecche. alswa hit is awriten. &thorn;et ure drihten hine crunede mid blisse and mid wur&eth;scipe. and sette hine ouer his hondiwerc. and eft hit is awriten bi him on &thorn;an ilcan psalme. <I>Omnia</I> <MILESTONE N="48b" UNIT="folio"><I>subiecisti sub pedibus eius</I>. &ETH;et is al eor&eth;lic &thorn;ing ure drihten dude under his fotan. Alle &thorn;a deor and alle &thorn;e nutenu &thorn;e on eor&eth;e weren. and alle &thorn;e fu&yogh;elas &thorn;e flu&yogh;en bi &thorn;an lufte. and alle &thorn;e fiscas &thorn;e swummen in &thorn;ere se; alle heo weren adame ibuhsume and naut ane under his hond; ac under his fet. Ac swa sone swa he forseh his scuppend &thorn;urh his wifes red; heo forluren ba &thorn;a murie wununge &thorn;e heom bitaht wes; &thorn;et wes eor&eth;liche para[d]is. &ETH;a anan heo weren iscouen; alswa &thorn;e boc sei&eth;. <I>Expulsi sunt nec potuerunt stare</I>. heo weren ipult ut of paradise; and ne mehten &thorn;er naleng etstonden. and hwer bicomen heo &thorn;a; So&eth;liche on &thorn;issere worulde. <I>vbi omnis homo cum dolore nascitur &amp; cum dolore moritur.</I> on &thorn;issere weorlde heo bicomen &thorn;er iwilch mon bi&eth; iboren mid muchele sara. and mid muchele sor&yogh;e his lif ienda&eth;. her heo leueden al heore lifda&yogh;es on kare and on pine and on unimete iswinche. and efter &thorn;isse liue heore saulen ferden to helle and &thorn;er wuneden. 
<PB REF="00000195.tif" N="131"> iiii. &thorn;usend &yogh;eran and &thorn;erto iiii. hundred &yogh;eran and alle &thorn;a men &thorn;e comen of heom gode and uuele swa sone swa heore saulen and heore licoma to-delden heo ferden to helle. Ne mihte &thorn;er nan wi&eth;stonden. ne prophete. ne patriarche. ne hure. Sancte iohannes baptiste. &thorn;e ure drihten ber iwitnesse and seide. Bitwuxe were and wife nes nefre mare mon &thorn;enne he. ac &thorn;ah hwe&eth;re his saule wes in helle. a &eth;et &thorn;a streonge leo &thorn;et wes &thorn;es liui&yogh;endes godes sune. <I>Et contriuit portas ereas. &amp; uectes fereos confregit.</I> &ETH;et is he to-&thorn;ruste &thorn;a stelene gate. and to brec &thorn;a irene barren of helle. and nom ut alle &thorn;a ilcan &thorn;e on &thorn;isse <MILESTONE N="49a" UNIT="folio">liue his bibode heolden. <I>Et eduxit eos de tenebris &amp; umbra mortis</I>. He ledde heom of &thorn;eostran and of scadewe. and of dea&eth;e into heouena riche. <I>ad quod et nos perducat Christus filius dei uiui. qui uiuit et regnat per omnia secula seculorum. Amen.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="13" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XIII. [SERMO IN EPIST. 2 AD CORINTH. IX. 6.]</HEAD>
<P><I>[Q]vi parce seminat; parce &amp; metet</I>. vre lauerd seinte paul he&yogh;es[t] lar&eth;ewen. efter ure helende seolfe; spece&eth; on &thorn;e halie pistle &thorn;e me ret to dei ine halie chirche and munege&eth; ei&eth;er ihadede and ileawede to godes worde and to weldede and &thorn;us sei&eth;. <I>Spiritualiter quidem monens hos ut ait gregorius ad sancte predicationis officium. Generaliter uero hos &amp; illos ad salutarem obedienciam mandatorum.</I> Ihadede men he munege&eth; wel to lerene ilewede men. Ihadede and lewede feier lif and clene to leden in &thorn;isse liue. and sei&eth; &thorn;et euric mon scal auon mede; and &thorn;us sei&eth;. <I>Qui parce seminat et cetera.</I> &ETH;e mon &thorn;et lutel sewe&eth; he scal lutel ma&yogh;e. and &thorn;e &eth;e sawe&eth; on blescunge he scal mawen of blescunge &thorn;et is to suggen. &ETH;e mon &thorn;e wel de&eth;; he wel ifeh&eth;. <I>Sacra scriptura nomine seminis appellat tria. scilicet hominis progenituram. dei uerbum. opus bonum</I>. Halie boc nemne&eth; iwuneliche &eth;reo &thorn;ing to sede. an is monnes istreon. &thorn;et 
<PB REF="00000197.tif" N="133"> o&eth;er is godes word. and &thorn;et &eth;ridde is weldede. vre drihten cleop|ede monnes streon sed; &thorn;a &thorn;e he spec wi&eth; &eth;ene halie mon abraham of his istreone and seide. &thorn;et swa muchel moncun sculde springen of him &eth;et na man ne mihte itellen a mare &thorn;e me mei &eth;eo steorren of heuene; and &thorn;us seide. <I>Suspice celum &amp; numera stellas si potes; Sic erit semen tuum</I>. Bihald he <MILESTONE N="49b" UNIT="folio">seide up to heouene and tel &thorn;eo steoren &yogh;if &thorn;u miht swulc scal beon &thorn;in of|spring. <I>Sed obseruandum est quod prudens sator obseruat &amp; glebe aptitudinem &amp; temporis opportunitatem</I>. hit is to witene &thorn;et alrihtes swa alse &thorn;e wise teolie &thorn;enne he wule sawe nime&eth; &yogh;eme of twam &thorn;ingen. an is hwe&eth;er &thorn;et lond beo bicumelic to &thorn;e sede. Alswa ahte eurec cristene mon; wepmon and wifmon. &thorn;enne heo fundie&eth; to teoliende; efter istreone nimen muchele &yogh;eme &thorn;et heo hit<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. bit.</NOTE> don on bicumeliche stude and on rihte time. Nis na stude to istreone bicumelic butan &eth;a &thorn;e istreonie&eth; beon bispused rihtliche to gedere. ne neaure nis riht time &thorn;er to; &thorn;enne me scal ueste o&eth;er al freos&yogh;e. Eft-sone godes word is icleoped sed; on &thorn;ere feire forbisne &thorn;e ure helend seide mid his a&yogh;ene mu&eth;e to his apostlen; and &thorn;us seide. <I>Exiit qui seminat et cetera.</I> A riche mon ferde ut; and seow and sum of &thorn;e sede feol an uppe &thorn;e stane and &thorn;er adru&yogh;ede and sum among &thorn;eornen and &thorn;er aswond and sum bi &thorn;e weie and wer&eth; to-treden and fu&yogh;eles hit freten. and sum on gode eor&eth;e; and &thorn;et com wel for&eth;. &ETH;eo apostles hine beden &thorn;et he scalde suggen hwet &thorn;eo sa&yogh;e bicwe&eth;e and he seide. <I>Semen est uerbum dei sator autem Christus omnis qui audit eum manebit ineternum.</I> Godes word is sed and crist is &thorn;e sawere and euric mon &thorn;e luste&eth; luueliche godes wordes and lede&eth; his lif rihtliche &thorn;er efter; he scal habben eche lif and blisse abuten ende. <I>Sed est diligenter attendendum quod hoc semen spargitur tum ore proprio tum</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. cum.</NOTE> <I>ore ministrorum.</I> ah &thorn;et is to understonde &thorn;et ure helend sawe&eth; <MILESTONE N="50a" UNIT="folio">his halie word hwile &thorn;urh his a&yogh;ene mu&eth;e and hwile &thorn;urh &eth;ere apostlene mu&eth;e. hwile &thorn;urh &eth;ere clerkene mu&eth;e &thorn;e cunnen &thorn;e lare of halie boke &thorn;e rade&eth; and teche&eth; godes la&yogh;e in to &thorn;es monnes heorte. and alswuche wise speke&eth; &eth;e eor&eth;liche<NOTE PLACE="marg">? heofen|liche.</NOTE> king wi&eth; iwilche cristene monne &thorn;e he to sende&eth; his halie iwriten. <I>In hac eciam satione diligenter obserua agri competentiam; &amp; temporis</I> 
<PB REF="00000199.tif" N="135"> <I>congruenciam.</I> &ETH;enne &thorn;e&yogh;s folkes lar&thorn;ew his sed wule sawen he ahte to nimene muchele &yogh;eme &thorn;et he hit sawe on bicumeliche eor&eth;e; and on rihte time. On &eth;ere monne heorte &thorn;e luuelich[e] luste&eth; godes wordes summe heo ere&eth;on gode weoren summe heo &eth;ere &thorn;urh gode iwur&eth;e&eth;. and &thorn;et bi&eth; bicumelic eor&eth;e godes wordes on to sawen. Ah &thorn;a &eth;e sunnen luue&eth; and for-leten heom nulle&eth; ne nane bileafe under-fo; heo beo&eth; unbicumelic eor&eth;e to &thorn;e sede of godes weorde. <I>Vnde diuina scriptura. Nolite spargere Margaritas ante porcos.</I> and &thorn;ere for seide &thorn;e heouenliche lar&thorn;ew. Ne sculen &yogh;e nawiht &yogh;imstones leggen swinen to mete. &AElig;uriche sunen deie. and o&eth;re he&yogh;e da&yogh;en is time to sawene &thorn;et halie sed &thorn;et is godes word. and &eth;et in halie chirche &thorn;er alle cristene men a&yogh;en to beon isomned to gedere. <I>Bonum opus nomine seminis dicitur. tum quum nunc seritur in futuro metetur. tum quum more frugum multiplicabitur.</I> Weldede is icleoped sed; for twam &thorn;ingen. An is &eth;et alrihtes swa alse me sawe&eth; sed on ane time and gedere&eth; &thorn;et frut on o&eth;er time; al swa mon de&eth; nu&eth;e his dede in &thorn;isse liue. and on &eth;ere eche weorlde <MILESTONE N="50b" UNIT="folio">he scal hafon &eth;er of his mede. &ETH;et o&eth;er is. Alswa of ane sede cume&eth; feole folde weste. Alswa of ane e&eth;eliche dede mon scal afon eft feole folde mede and muchele. <I>Multa quidem genera sunt bonorum operum. sed hic de uno eorum agitur. scilicet de elemosinarum largitione. vnde prophetam inducit dicentem. Dispersit dedit pauperibus. et cetera.</I> feole cunne beo&eth; of weldede. Ah &thorn;e apostel us munege&eth; here to one of heom &thorn;et is elmasdele and sei&eth; &thorn;et me heo scal &yogh;efen hafelesen monne monne<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE>. Ah alse &eth;e halie salmwurhte dauid. seide delen heo &thorn;et euric neodi &eth;e heo bisece&eth; sum &thorn;ing &eth;er of afo. Gif &thorn;an biha&yogh;e&eth; &eth;e h&eacute;o dele&eth; and neng<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE> sullen heom &eth;eo elmesse ah &yogh;efen. Alle weldede beo&eth; freomfulle to sun-bote<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. sum|bote.</NOTE>. ah nan mare freomful denne elmes idal. <I>Quia sicut aqua extinguit ignem ita elemosina peccatum</I>. for alswa weter acwenche&eth; fur; alswa elmesdede acwenche&eth; sunne. Ah &yogh;if me sulle&eth; &thorn;eo elmesse heo feorleose&eth; hire nome and hire mihte alswa. <I>Quatuor modis uenditur elemosina. &amp; tunc inde populi fauor euertitur</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">? emitur.</NOTE>. <I>aut pudoris molestia deprimitur. aut re|compensatio rei temporalis adquiritur. aut debiti beneficii solucio</I> 
<PB REF="00000201.tif" N="137"> <I>inpenditur.</I> An fower cunne wise mon sulle&eth; his elmesse. An is &thorn;enne he bi&yogh;ete&eth; hereword &eth;ere mide. <I>Et hoc animi morbo laborat fere omnis homo.</I> and &thorn;esne lehter habbe&eth; mest hwet alle men. &eth;e &yogh;efe&eth; heore elmesse ei&eth;er for godes luue and ec for here|word to habbene and beon iwur&eth;egede fir <MILESTONE N="51a" UNIT="folio">and neor &eth;er &thorn;e heo icnawene beo&eth;. An o&eth;re wise mon sulde<NOTE PLACE="marg">sul&eth;e = sulle&eth;.</NOTE> his elmesse &thorn;enne he heo &yogh;efe&eth; swulche monne &eth;e he for scome wernen ne mei for ne&yogh;eburredde o&eth;er elles freonde and &thorn;ere mide hine alese&eth; of scome; &thorn;e he habben sculde. &yogh;if he heo ne &YOGH;ef. On &eth;ridde wise mon sull&eth;e his elmesse &eth;enne he heo &yogh;efe&eth; sulche monne &thorn;e him de&eth;. o&eth;er haue&eth; idon. o&eth;er don scal wiken and cherres and &eth;enche&eth; mid his elmesse for&yogh;elden him &eth;eo hwile. &eth;enne bi&eth; &thorn;es monnes wile ibeht mid &thorn;ere elmisse. On feor&eth;e wise mon sulle&eth; his elmesse. &thorn;enne he heo &yogh;efe&eth; swulche monne &thorn;e he ahte mid rihte helpe to fodne&eth;e and to scrude bi his bi-ha&yogh;e. alse de&eth; monimon &eth;e &yogh;efe&eth; his elmesse feader o&eth;er moder bro&eth;er o&eth;er suster o&eth;er o&eth;re swa isibbe &eth;e he ne mei mid rihte wi&eth;teon. Al &eth;e almisse &thorn;e mon de&eth; sunderlipe for to quemen ure drihten; alle &thorn;eo cwenche&eth; sunnen and erni&eth; sunbote at ure helende seolfe. and alle goddede &thorn;e mon de&eth; on odre wise and beo&eth; ec idone for godes luue. Neo&eth;eles he heom sulle&eth; and underueh&eth;e here &eth;er of his mede alswa ure drihten sei&eth; in &thorn;e godspelle. <I>amen dico uobis; receperunt mercedem suam</I>. to so&eth;e ic eow sugge &thorn;et &thorn;a &eth;e do&eth; god for to habben &eth;er of a&yogh;en in &thorn;isse liue; nabbe&eth; heo nenne &thorn;onc on eche weorlde. Ah al &thorn;et mon de&eth; sunderlipe <MILESTONE N="51b" UNIT="folio">for godes luuen; he scal auon &eth;er of his mede. and beon &thorn;enne ifunde alse hit bi&eth; nu&eth;e ierned here. for ure drihten hit sei&eth; in &thorn;e halie godspelle. <I>Eadem mensura qua mensi fueritis remecietur uobis.</I> Bi&eth;on ilke imet &eth;e &yogh;e mete&eth; nu&eth;e; eower weldede scal eft beon imeten eower mede. and bi hunderfalde mare; alswa we er seiden. <I>Qui parce seminat &amp; cetera.</I> &AElig;uric mon scal eft mowen bi &thorn;on &thorn;e he nu sawe&eth;. and &thorn;e &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE> sawe&eth; nu on blescunge. he scal eft mowen of blescunge. &ETH;et is &aelig;uric mon &thorn;e lede&eth; feir lif and clene. and bi al his biha&yogh;e dele&eth; his elmesse and &thorn;ere mide ierned &thorn;et alle men hine blesce&eth;. and for him bidde&eth;. and ure lauerd god almihten for heore bene &yogh;eue&eth; 
<PB REF="00000203.tif" N="139"> him his blescunge. &ETH;et is &eth;eo echeliche riche &thorn;et he haue&eth; i&yogh;arwed to alle &eth;on monnen &thorn;e his iwille wurche&eth; her on [&thorn;isse] liue. <I>Ad quam gloriam nos perducere dignetur dominus noster ihesus christus qui uiuit et regnat per omnia secula seculorum. amen.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="14" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XIV. IN DIE DOMINICA.</HEAD>
<P><I>[R]euerenda est nobis hec dies sancta que dicitur dominica. &amp; ideo dicitur dominica quoniam hec dies sola dies domini est.</I> Muchel man ach to wur&thorn;en &thorn;is halie dei &thorn;at is sunnen dei icleoped. for hit is godes a&yogh;en dei. Alle o&eth;er da&yogh;es of &thorn;e wike beo&eth; to &thorn;reldome to &thorn;is dei. <MILESTONE N="52a" UNIT="folio">&thorn;is dei is &thorn;et halie dei &thorn;et blescede dei &thorn;e blisfulle dei &thorn;e murie dei. &thorn;e dei seouensi&thorn;e brictere &thorn;ene &thorn;e sunne. &thorn;e fo[r]meste dei &thorn;et eauer &yogh;iete was ise&yogh;en buuen eor&eth;e. <I>In qua uisa est lux</I>. Sunnen dei was ise&yogh;an &thorn;et formeste liht buuen eor&eth;e for ure drihten seide &thorn;is dei. <I>Fiat lux &amp; facta est lux</I>. beo liht and hit wes liht. <I>Ex hac enim die; relique dies sumpserunt exordium</I>. Of &thorn;isse dei nomen alle o&eth;er heore biginni[n]ge. <I>Dies in qua conuenit plebs ad ecclesiam ad pre|dicandum &amp; ad celebrandum.</I> Sunnedei ah efri cristenne. Mon. nomeliche to chirche cume &thorn;e ahte for to techen &thorn;e folke godes hesne to done. &thorn;e lewede godes hesne for to heren. and hom to gode bidden. <I>Dies in qua letantur agmina celi &amp; terre.</I> Sunne dei blisse&eth; to-gederes houeneware and hor&eth;e ware. alse &thorn;e halie gast sei&eth; &thorn;urh daui&eth;es mu&eth; &thorn;e prophete. <I>Hec est dies quam fecit dominus exultemur &amp; letemur in ea.</I> &thorn;is is &thorn;e dei &thorn;et god makede. beo we bli&eth;e and glade on &thorn;is dei. <I>In hac die multa &amp; magna mirabilia fecit dominus pro salute nostra.</I> Monie wundre and muchele dude ure drihten. for ure hele on &thorn;isse dei. <I>In die dominica creati sunt angeli ab ore dei</I>. sunnendei; weren engles makede of godes mu&eth;e. <I>In die dominica resedit archa post diluuium</I>. sunnendei fond noe lond efter &thorn;et ure drihten 
<PB REF="00000205.tif" N="141"> hefde &thorn;et folc adreint. <I>In die dominica pluit dominus manna filiis israel.</I> sunnedei god sende manna from houene &thorn;am<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. &THORN;et.</NOTE> is|raelisce folc. <I>In die dominica</I> <MILESTONE N="52b" UNIT="folio"> <I>percussum est mare rubrum in uirtute dei per manum moysi &amp; transierunt filii israel siccis pedibus per mare rubrum.</I> Sunnedei smat<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. siriat.</NOTE> Moyses &thorn;e rede s&eacute;&eacute;. and &thorn;e see to-eode and &thorn;et iraelisce folc wende ouer. <I>Et stetit illis murus in dextera atque in sinistra.</I> and &thorn;er stod a richt halue and a luft; alse an castel wal. <I>&amp; iterum percussit Moyses mare &amp; reuersum est in locum suum &amp; mersus est pharao cum curribus &amp; equitibus eius.</I> and eft sone Moyses smat<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. siriat.</NOTE> &thorn;e see. and heo wende to gederes. and adreinte pharao. and al his ferede mid him. swa &thorn;et nes &thorn;ere nefre an bileued un-dreint. <I>In die dominica percussit moyses petram in heremo &amp; fluxerunt quatuor flumina que diuisa sunt in duodecim partes ut traxerint sitim populo.</I> Sunnedei smat<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. siriat.</NOTE> Moyses &thorn;ene stan ine &thorn;e wastine; &thorn;a &thorn;et folc wes welnech for-faren drinkeles alse ure drihten him het. and &thorn;e stan to-chan; and fouwer walmes of watere sprungen ut &thorn;er of. and &thorn;a fouwer weren ideled a twelue. for &thorn;a twelf kun|reden sculden &thorn;er mide heore &thorn;urst kelen. <I>In die dominica natus est Christus ex Maria uirgine pro salute nostra.</I> Sunnen|dei wes ure drihten iboren of &thorn;e halie Maiden Marie for ure hele. <I>In die dominica baptizatus est dominus noster in iordane.</I> Sunnendei wes ure drihten ifulchted ine flum iordan. <I>&amp; spiritus sanctus uenit super eum in specie columbe.</I> and &thorn;e halie gast com uppen ure drihten in ane culfre liche. and iherde his fadre stefne of heouene and seide. <I>Hic est filius</I> <MILESTONE N="53a" UNIT="folio"> <I>meus dilectus. in quo michi bene complacitum.</I> &thorn;is is min loue sune &thorn;et me wel like&eth;. <I>In die dominica resurexit Christus a mortuis.</I> Sunnedei aras ure drihten from de&eth;e to liue. and makede arisen mid him alle &thorn;a &thorn;et him efden er ihersumed. <I>In die dominica post dies octo uenit ad dicipulos per clausas ianuas. &amp; stetit in medio eorum dicens. pax uobis.</I> and on &thorn;e twelftu&yogh;e&thorn;e dei efter &thorn;et he wes arisen. he com among his disciples &thorn;er &thorn;e &yogh;eten weren ilokene. &thorn;et wes a sunnedei. and seide to heom setnesse beo mid eou. Sunnedei makede ure drihten pes bitweone heouene and eor&eth;e. bi-tweone engles and monne. bi-tweone gode and monne. 
<PB REF="00000207.tif" N="143"> bi-tweone licome and saule. bi-tweone &thorn;e alde la&yogh;e and &thorn;e neowe. bi-tweone he&eth;ene and cristene. <I>Ipse enim est qui facit utraque unum.</I> he is &thorn;et make&eth; twa to an. <I>In die dominica misit dominus spiritum super apostolos.</I> Sunnedei sende ure drihten &thorn;ene halie gast his apostlen in fures liche. <I>In die do|minica uenturus est in maiestate sua cum sanctis angelis &amp; arcangelis in iudicium uiuorum &amp; mortuorum.</I> Sunnedei wile ure drihten cumen ine his muchele stren&eth;e mid alle heouenware for to deme ba&thorn;e &thorn;e gode and &thorn;e uuele. and alle Men sculen beon igedered bi-foren him. and ech eor&thorn;e scal hwakien on his ecsene<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE>. alse deo&eth; &thorn;e see in storme. <I>tunc montes liquescent sicut cera a facie ignis.</I> &thorn;enne uch dune scal berne. and al folc alse &thorn;e p[ro]phete sei&eth;. <I>Ignis ante ipsum precedet &amp; inflammabit in circuitu in|imicos eius.</I> &thorn;et fur scal gan biforen and <MILESTONE N="53b" UNIT="folio">forbernen abuten him fon. <I>et iterum. Dominus noster cum uirtute ueniet. &amp; cetera.</I> Vre drihten wile cumen dredliche in fures liche and wile for-berne alle his fon. and heom &thorn;et beo&eth; iwunede uuel to done. <I>Tunc cantabunt angeli magna tuba &amp; mortui resurgent</I>. &thorn;enne sculen engles mid beme blauwen on fower halue &thorn;e world. and alle dede arisen and steorren sculen &thorn;eostren. and &thorn;e sunne hire liht for|leose. and steorren sculen from heouene falle. <I>Et tunc iudi|cabit iudicia nouissima. &amp; reddet unicuique iuxta opera sua.</I> &thorn;enne wille god deme his leste dom. and wile &yogh;elden eche men his mede efter his werke. &thorn;e sunfulle .Men. &thorn;et spushad breke&eth;. &thorn;a feste .Men<NOTE PLACE="marg">? Mon.</NOTE>. &thorn;a &thorn;et mei lutel to wreche. &thorn;e &thorn;oues. &thorn;e &thorn;et speke&eth; faire bi-foren and false bi-hinden. &thorn;e ni&eth;fulle. &thorn;e prude. &thorn;e fordrunkene. &thorn;e chidinde. &thorn;e forsworene<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. for|sporene.</NOTE>. &thorn;e he&eth;ene. &thorn;e erites. <I>eicientur cum fletu &amp; lamentatione in penam sempiternam sine ablutione &amp; misericordia.</I> sculen beon iwarpen ine eche pine. wi&thorn;-uten alesinge and wi&eth;-uten milce. Ach &thorn;e richtwise men. &thorn;e treowe men. &thorn;e munekes. &thorn;e meidene. &thorn;e weddede wiues. &thorn;e gode .Men. &thorn;e softe .Men. and &thorn;e .Men. ful of milce. and &thorn;e large. Men. and &thorn;e milde .Men. &thorn;e herbe[r]gers. &thorn;e &thorn;olemode. &thorn;e elmes|fulle. &thorn;a &thorn;e heom wi&eth;-teo&eth; of flesliche lustes. <I>uocabuntur in dextra dei patris omnipotentis.</I> sculen beon icleoped on &thorn;e fader riht halue. &thorn;er scal beon worldwunne; wi&eth;-uten <MILESTONE N="54a" UNIT="folio">pouerte. 
<PB REF="00000209.tif" N="145"> fulle; wi&eth;-uten hungre. hele; wi&eth;-uten unhele. reste; wi&eth;|uten swinge<NOTE PLACE="marg">? swincunge.</NOTE>. blisse; wi&eth;-uten sarinesse. Iv&yogh;e&eth;e; wi&eth;-uten elde. Lokinge; wi&eth;-uten winkunge. song; wi&eth;-uten lisse. smellinge; mid swetnesse. and dunge<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &eth;enunge.</NOTE>; wi&eth;-uten prikunge. <I>defectio omnis mali. Habundancia omnis boni.</I> wone of alle uuele; wole; and alle gode<NOTE PLACE="marg">? and wole of alle gode.</NOTE>. Amen.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="15" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XV. [SERMO IN MARCUM VIII. 34.]</HEAD>
<P><I>[Q]vi uult uenire post me. abneget semet ipsum &amp; tollat crucem suam &amp; sequatur me.</I> wa is &thorn;an<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. &thorn;et.</NOTE> .Mon. &thorn;et wa is and me him mare bihat. and mei and wile hit him ileste. Ach him is wel &thorn;et is ila&eth;ed from lutel weole to muchele. and him is ec muchele bet; &thorn;et is ila&eth;ed from muchele wowe; to muchele wele. Alle we beo&eth; in monifald wawe ine &thorn;isse wreche liue. hwat for ure eldere werkes. hwat for ure a&yogh;ene gultes. ach god almihtin us freure&eth; mid his milde word and teche&eth; us bi hwiche weie we ma&yogh;en to him cume and sei&eth;. <I>Qui uult uenire post me et cetera.</I> Hwa se wile cume efter me; for-sake him seolf. and bere his rode. and folege me. &THORN;os word he seide et sumtime to|&yogh;eines &thorn;et he walde &thorn;is lif forleten. he munegede alle &thorn;a &thorn;et &thorn;o weren o&eth;er seo&thorn;&eth;en habbe&eth; ikumen. o&eth;er to kumene beo&eth; to endeles blisse. ach heom &thorn;ing&eth; uuel to forleten &thorn;et heo muchel luue&eth;. <I>Alii quidem amant peccata sua. alii parentes. alii pos|sessiones. alii uoluptatates</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE> <I>&amp; uicia</I>. Summe men luuie&eth; heore sunnen. summe heore kun. summe world wunne. summe; gal|iche<MILESTONE N="54b" UNIT="folio"> lectres and lu&eth;ere lastes &thorn;a &thorn;et luuie&eth; heore sunne; he mune&yogh;e&eth; &thorn;us and sei&eth;. <I>penitenciam agite appropinquabit enim regnum celorum.</I> Cume&eth; to sunbote and forlete&eth; eower sunne. for domes dei nehlechet &thorn;a &thorn;et luue&eth; heore kun; he mune&yogh;e&eth; and sei&eth;. <I>Omnis qui reliquerit patrem aut matrem. fratrem aut sororem. aut ceteros amicos propter nomen meum; centuplum. &amp; uitam eternam possidebit.</I> Alle &thorn;a &thorn;et forlete&eth; fader o&eth;er moder. 
<PB REF="00000211.tif" N="147"> suster o&eth;er bro&thorn;er. o&eth;er o&eth;re freond. for mine nome; heo sculen underfon hundfalde mede. and lif buten ende. &thorn;et luue&eth; world wunne; he mune&yogh;e&eth; and sei&eth;. <I>Qui non renunciauerit omnibus que possidet non potest meus esse dicipulus.</I> Ne mei na .Mon. me fol&yogh;en; bute he forlete al &thorn;et he iwald ach. <I>Duobus modis renunciatur possesis desinendo habere &amp; desinendo amare.</I> On twa wise .Mon. mei forlete world winne. an is &thorn;et he hit do for him; &thorn;et he hit nabbe. an o&eth;er is &thorn;et he telle swa lutel tale &thorn;er of; &thorn;et he hit nawicht ne luuie. hit nis nawicht sunne muchel; if .Mon. echte habbe. ach hit is muche sunne; if .Mon. echte luuie&eth;. for he ne mei nawiht luuie god; and ec his ehte. &thorn;a &thorn;et luue&eth; galiche lectres; he mune&yogh;e&eth; &thorn;us and sei&eth;. <I>Qui uult uenire et cetera.</I> hwa se wule cume efter me; forsake him solf. and bere his rode. and fole&yogh;e me. Ach hit is uuel to understonden on hwulche wise .Mon. mei him solf forsake <MILESTONE N="55a" UNIT="folio">nime&eth; &yogh;eme &thorn;er to; and ic hit weo<NOTE PLACE="marg">? eow.</NOTE> wile sugge b[i] godes leue. <I>Duo sunt in homine. aliud per naturam conditum. aliud per culpam illatum.</I> Twa &thorn;ing beo&eth; ine &thorn;e .Mon. &thorn;et an is &thorn;et brochte icunde. and &thorn;et faire icunde &thorn;et is igedered bi-twene saule and licame. &thorn;et o&eth;er is &thorn;e fule on-kume &thorn;a &thorn;e douel haue&eth; &thorn;eron ibroht. &thorn;erfore ne mei na .Mon. to gode cume; bute he forlete &thorn;e fule on-cume &thorn;e &eth;e douel haued on him ibroht of sunne. and het halde &thorn;et faire ikunde. &thorn;et god haue&eth; on him idon of saule and of likame. and wunie ine &thorn;et clenesse; &thorn;et he haue&eth; et<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. ec.</NOTE> his fulluhte ifet. <I>tres cruces sunt de quibus hic agitur. due corporis una mentis.</I> &thorn;reo roden beo&eth; &thorn;a ich umbe speche. twa licamliche; and an gastliche. <I>Crux corporis est; quando corpus distensum menbratim punitur.</I> &thorn;e likameliche rode is; hwenne &thorn;e likame &thorn;ole&eth; pine ine &thorn;is liue ine rode and bi&eth; &thorn;er on to-spred; alse ure helende wes ine &thorn;e halie rode for ure gultes. &thorn;et nefde him solf nane. &thorn;a &thorn;e he hefde uppen his hefde &thorn;ornene helm. and weren his side mid speres orde iopened. and his fet mid irnene neiles &thorn;urhstungen. ach .Mon. mei to gode cume &thorn;ach his likame swiche pine ne &thorn;ole. Ac he munege&eth; us an o&eth;er rode to berene; &thorn;et is inemned. <I>Carnis maceratio.</I> fleises lensing. Mon. lense&eth; his fleis; hwenne he him &yogh;efe&eth; lutel to etene. and lesse to drinke. <MILESTONE N="55b" UNIT="folio"> and ofte for 
<PB REF="00000213.tif" N="149"> his sunne swinge&eth; him mi&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. nu&eth;.</NOTE> smele twige. <I>Et hec est scala pecca|torum.</I> and &thorn;is is alle sunfulle monne leddre &thorn;et heo sculen in to heouene sti&yogh;en. <I>Crux mentis est cordis contritio &amp; proxumi com|passio.</I> &thorn;e gastliche rode is inemned; heorte sar for &thorn;e monnes a&yogh;ene sunne. and row&eth;e for his emcristenes wawe. horte sar haue&eth; &thorn;e .Mon. [hwenne] him bi&thorn;eng&thorn; &thorn;et he isuneged haue&eth;. and &thorn;et sare bi-murne&eth; and to scrifte kimet. and bi his prostes wissunge his sunne bete&eth;. Reu&thorn;e for his emcristenes wawe haue&eth; &thorn;e .Mon. &thorn;et isich his emcristene in sunne bi-falle. o&eth;er mid sicnesse bi-gan. and ne mei buten helpe &thorn;er cume. If he ne mei mid worldliche echte his neode ibete; &thorn;et him sare rowe&thorn;. and his emcristenes wawe sare bi-murne&eth;. eft sone hwenne .Mon. him bi-&thorn;enche&eth; &thorn;et he haue&eth; sunful ibeon. and to fele sunne idon. &thorn;enne wule his heorte ake alse his heued wolde; if he hefde &thorn;er uppon &thorn;ornene helm. Eft sone hwenne &thorn;e .Mon. him bi&thorn;ench&thorn; &thorn;et he haue&eth; on galiche dede to muche god iwre&thorn;ed. and naue&eth; inume &yogh;eme hwe&eth;er heo bi-wedded were &thorn;e nere; &thorn;et he hefde mid to donne; bute his fule lust were ikeled. &thorn;enne &thorn;e .Mon. him bi|&thorn;eng&thorn; &thorn;et he haue&eth; to selde igan to chirche. and ilome mid his honde idon &thorn;et he don ne sculde; &thorn;enne wule his heorte ake alse his fet and his honde; if heo &thorn;urh irnene neile were &thorn;urh-stunge. and if we &thorn;us us solue willeliche pine&eth;; &thorn;enne ma&yogh;e we beon godes lornigkinchtes<NOTE PLACE="marg">? leorning|knichtes.</NOTE>. &thorn;enne <MILESTONE N="56a" UNIT="folio">we ma&yogh;e him folege. and mid him bileue. Bidde&eth; ure drihten &thorn;et &yogh;e moten efter him kume and &thorn;ene fule onkume for-lete &thorn;a &thorn;e douel haue&eth; in ow ibroht of sunne and edhalde &thorn;et brihte ikunde; &thorn;et god haue&eth; in ow ibroht of saule and of likame. and &thorn;e klennesse of ower fulluhte &thorn;et &yogh;e habbe&eth; et &thorn;e fonstan underfonge. and &thorn;et &yogh;e moten &thorn;e rode bere. &thorn;e god ow to munege&eth;. and him folege and mid him bileue. <I>Quod nobis prestare dignetur qui uiuit &amp; cetera. Amen.</I>
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="16" TYPE="homily"><PB REF="00000215.tif" N="151">
<HEAD>XVI. [ESTOTE FORTES IN BELLO.]</HEAD>
<P><I>[E]stote fortes in bello &amp; pugnate cum antiquo serpente. &amp; accipietis regnum eternum dicit dominus.</I> &THORN;is word &thorn;e ich nu &thorn;e for-tech<NOTE PLACE="marg">? for&eth;-teah.</NOTE>; seide ure drihten et sume time &thorn;a he wunede ine &thorn;e londe of ierusalem. and munegede alle &thorn;et weren to stronge fechte. and for &thorn;on &thorn;e &thorn;et fecht wes strong to ouer-cumen. and uuel to underfone; he bi-het hom muche mede wi&eth; &thorn;an &thorn;et heo walde &thorn;is fecht underfon and sei&eth;. <I>Estote fortes &amp; cetera.</I> beo&eth; stronge on fihte. and fihte&eth; wi&eth; &thorn;e alde neddre. and if &yogh;e beo&eth; strengre &thorn;e heo; &yogh;e sculen habben to me[de] eche blisse <I>Quia diuersa genera hominum sequebantur eum. &amp; ipse dixit sermones suos. tum ad dicipulos. tum ad hos. tum ad illos. aperiendum est et quibus. et de qua fortitudine et de quo bello. et de qua serpente hoc dixerit.</I> Monie kunnes men fole&yogh;eden ure drihten ine &thorn;isse liue; summe to fechen heore bileue et him. summe to fechen heore deis fode. summe to kunnen if heo mihten him mid sunne undernime <MILESTONE N="56b" UNIT="folio">&thorn;er fore hit is god &thorn;et Mon ow segge hwiche he munege&thorn; to &thorn;is fehte. Summe men luueden heore sunne. and nalden heom forleten. he ne munege&eth; noht heom to &thorn;is fiht. ne for &thorn;on &thorn;a &thorn;e hefden heore sunne forleten. and nawiht ibet. Ah &thorn;a he munege&eth; to &thorn;is feht; &thorn;et hefden heore sunne ibet. o&thorn;er on bote bifongen. and nomeliche &thorn;e twelf apostles. and among heom &thorn;e lauerd. N. hwas dei hit is to dei. of &thorn;e strein&thorn;e &thorn;et god us to munege&eth; spech liber sapientie. &thorn;et is &thorn;e boc of wisdom and sei&eth;. <I>fortitudo simplicis est uia domini.</I> Godes wei is strein&eth;e &thorn;e anfalde monne. Anfald o&eth;er twafald is ech mon &thorn;et kimed<NOTE PLACE="marg">? kunne&eth;.</NOTE> &thorn;e lauerd saint Iame. and sei&eth;. <I>Vir duplex animo inconstans est in omnibus uiis suis.</I> &THORN;e twafalde .Mon. is unsta&thorn;elfest; on alle his weies. Ah Iob wes anfald rihtwis .Mon. and swa godmon; &thorn;et ure drihten him solf hine herede. and seide &thorn;et under houene ne nan his ilike. <I>Via domini qua uenit ad nos &amp; nos ad eum</I> 
<PB REF="00000217.tif" N="153">  <I>misericordia &amp; ueritas.</I> &thorn;e wei &thorn;et god com in to monne. and mon kume&eth; in to him; is ihaten mildheortnesse, and so&eth;fest|nesse. Mildheortnesse God kudde monne; &thorn;a &thorn;e he sende his patriarken and propheten; for to bodien his tokume. So&eth;fest|nesse he kudde mon; &thorn;a &thorn;e he him solf com alse he hefde bihaten. and us alesde ut of eche wawe. I&thorn;onked wur&eth;e him. Mildheort|nesse me ku&eth; him soluen; henne<NOTE PLACE="marg">? hwenne.</NOTE> he him bi-&thorn;eng&eth; &thorn;et he isuneg|ed haue&eth;. and &thorn;et sare bimurne&eth;. and milce bit. So&eth;festnesse <MILESTONE N="57a" UNIT="folio">me ku&eth; him solue; hwenne he his sunnen unde&eth; to his proste. alswa alse he heom haue&eth; idon and to-&yogh;eines hwiche fan we a&yogh;en to fechte &thorn;e apostel sei&eth;. <I>Non est nobis colluctatio aduersus carnem et sanguinem. sed aduersus rectores tenebrarum.</I> We ne a&yogh;en naut to fihten to-&yogh;eines fleis and blod; ah to-&yogh;eines &thorn;a awariede gastes &thorn;et welde&eth; &thorn;osternesse. <I>sed ab hoste inuisibili dificile cauetur.</I> Ah uuel hit is to werien to-&yogh;eines &thorn;ene fa; &thorn;e .Mon. ne mei naut ison. and &thorn;e duntes bo&eth; uuel to kepen; &thorn;et mon nat nefre on hwilche halue ho wilen falle. Ach for-hwi nemne&eth; ure drihten &thorn;is fa to neddre. <I>Diabolus nominatur hic serpens; propter tria. Inuidia; tabescit. sine strepitu; serpit. quod pungit; ueneno afficit.</I> [ned]dre de&thorn; &thorn;reo &thorn;ing licamliche; &thorn;et &thorn;e douel de&eth; gastliche. Nedre haue&eth; ni&thorn; and onde. Nedre smu&yogh;e&eth; derneliche. nedre attre&eth; al &thorn;et heo priked. Swa haue&eth; &thorn;e douel nih<NOTE PLACE="marg">? ni&eth;.</NOTE> and onde to monne. and &thorn;olede<NOTE PLACE="marg">? wolde.</NOTE> &thorn;et Mon ded were; &thorn;eh him solf &thorn;e betre nere. alse &thorn;e boc sei&eth;. <I>Per inuidiam in|trauit mors in orbem terrarum.</I> &thorn;urh ni&eth; and onde com de&eth; in to &thorn;e worlde. Eft sone smu&yogh;e&eth; derneliche; swa de&eth; &thorn;e douel ine &thorn;e monnes e&yogh;en; if ho bo&eth; opene to bihalden idel and unnet. Ine &thorn;e; eren; if ho bo&eth; opene to lusten hoker. and spel. and leow. and o&eth;er &thorn;ing &thorn;et bo&eth; to-&yogh;eines godes heste. Ine &thorn;e nose; hwenne &thorn;e nose bi&eth; open to smelle unlofne bre&eth;. Ine &thorn;e mu&eth;e. hwenne &thorn;e <MILESTONE N="57b" UNIT="folio">mu&eth; is open for to li&yogh;en. o&eth;er sune&yogh;e&eth; on muchele ete and on ouer drinke. Et &thorn;e schape &thorn;e douel smu&yogh;e&eth; in derneliche; hwenne hit bi&eth; &yogh;aru to galiche deden. <I>Hee sunt quinque porte mortis per quas ingreditur auctor mortis ut afferat mortuos.</I> &THORN;is beo&eth; &thorn;e fif &yogh;eten &thorn;urh hwam kim&eth; in de&eth;es wurhte. and &thorn;er ine de&eth; alse &thorn;e lof-songere sei&eth;. <I>Per mille meandros</I> 
<PB REF="00000219.tif" N="155"> <I>agitat quieta corda.</I> Mid &thorn;usend falde wrenche he to-drefe&eth; &thorn;e &thorn;onk &thorn;et erre weren to-gedere. and wunde&thorn; &thorn;e saule. Ah ure drihten &thorn;et munege&eth; us to fechten te-&yogh;eines &thorn;et<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &thorn;e.</NOTE> alde neddre; &yogh;eue us mihte and strein&eth;e to habben &thorn;et<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &thorn;e.</NOTE> ilke wepne &thorn;a &thorn;e apostel spek&eth; of and sei&eth;. <I>Induite uos armaturam dei sumentes loricam fidei. Galeam spei. scutum caritatis. gladium spiritus; quod est uerbum dei.</I> Scrude&eth; ow mid godes wepne. and nime&eth; gode ileue to burne. To hope to helme; so&eth;e luue to scelde. godes word to sworde. <I>His armis munitus uicit dauid Goliam.</I> Mid &thorn;is wepne wes dauid iscrud &thorn;a he goliam &thorn;e fond ouer-com. swa wile god &thorn;et we moten her mide &thorn;e alde neddre ouercume. and habbe to mede endelese blisse. <I>Quod nobis prestare dignetur qui uiuit et regnat deus, et cetera. Amen.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="17" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XVII. [SERMO IN PS. CXXVI. 6.]</HEAD>
<P><I>[E]untes ibant et flebant. mittentes semina sua. Venientes autem uenient cum exultatione portantes manipulos suos.</I> &THORN;e halie prophete dauid spec&eth; on ane stude in &thorn;e sauter. and de&thorn; us to understonden on hwiche wise &thorn;e halie .Men. hersumden ure drihten <MILESTONE N="58a" UNIT="folio">ine &thorn;isse liue. and hwiche mede heo sculen habben for hore feire seruise and &thorn;us sei&eth;. <I>euntes et cetera.</I> heo oden wepende. and sowen and sculen eft cumen mid blisse and mawen. he spec&eth; of &thorn;et wes to cumene alse hit icumene were. for he wiste &thorn;et hit cume sculde. <I>Sed quo euntes; in mortem.</I> Ach hwider wenden heo; from worliche wunne ine likamliche wawe. fram hele; in unhele. from reste in to swinke. and &thorn;er hore likame pineden for to &thorn;et heo comen to his<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE> liues ende. <I>Quas lacrimas fundentes. tum compunctionis. tum compassionis. tum peregrinationis. tum contemplationis.</I> hwiche teres scheden ho; o&eth;er hwile heo scheden hate teres for hore a&yogh;en sunnen; hwenne ho hom bi&eth;ohten &thorn;et heo isuneged hefden. and &thorn;et sare bimurneden. and milce beden. <I>Tales</I> 
<PB REF="00000221.tif" N="157"> <I>lacrimas fudit Maria Magdalene quando lauit pedes domini.</I> swiche teres scedde. M. Magdalene; &thorn;a heo<NOTE PLACE="marg">&THORN;e has been dotted out before heo.</NOTE> wosch ure drihtenes fet. and heo wer&eth; hire solf waschen of hire fule sunnen. <I>Interdum uidentes aliquos affligi multotiens fuderunt lacrimas compas|sionis.</I> O&eth;er hwile &thorn;e halie .Men. scedden hare teres; for heore emcristene wawe. hwenne ho ise&yogh;en hore emcristene wandrede &thorn;olie. o&eth;er in seknesse bifalle and &thorn;et hom sare row&eth;. and bi heore mihte hore node bette. <I>Tales lacrimas fudit dominus quando lazarum suscitauit.</I> swiche teres schedde ure drihten; &thorn;a he iseh Martham and Mariam Magdalene &thorn;e sustren wepe for hore bro&eth;er de&eth; and ure drihten &thorn;ur&thorn; rou&eth;e &thorn;et he efde of hom; schedde of his halie e&yogh;ene hate teres and hore <MILESTONE N="58b" UNIT="folio">bro&eth;er arerde and weren stille of hore wope. and iturnd hore horte and heore wope to muchele blisse. <I>Plerique et tedio uite presentis affecti fuderunt lacrimas peregrinationis.</I> o&eth;erhwile &thorn;e halie .Men. sched|den hate teres for la&thorn;e of &thorn;e worlde; for hom of&thorn;uchte &thorn;et &thorn;is orliche<NOTE PLACE="marg">? eor&eth;liche.</NOTE> lif hom to longe leste. <I>Tales lacrimas fudit Iob; quando dicebat. Tedet animam meam uite mee.</I> swiche teres schedde iob; &thorn;a &thorn;e he &thorn;os word seide. Wa is mine saule; &thorn;et mi lif &thorn;us longe ilest. and dauid. &thorn;e prophete wop; for la&eth;e of &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &thorn;ere.</NOTE> world; &thorn;a he seide. <I>heu michi et cetera.</I> Wume nu &thorn;et min utbiwiste is her swa longe itu&thorn;ed. and &thorn;et ic scal wunien in unku&thorn;e londe. <I>Hoc autem dicebat. quia non habemus hic manentem ciuitatem; sed in celis debet esse conuersatio nostra.</I> &thorn;et he seide for we wunie&eth; here alse fleme. Ah ure erde is in houene; if we &thorn;er efter erne&eth;. <I>Iustus autem cum languet pro desiderio celestis patrie fundit lacrimas contemplationis.</I> &THORN;e rihtwise .Mon. &thorn;et mid &thorn;e e&yogh;ene of his horte bihalt in to houene and sic&eth; &thorn;e muchele blisse &thorn;et he is to ile&eth;ed; him wile sone longe &thorn;iderward and hwenne he ne mei &thorn;ider cume alse ra&eth;e se he walde; he send &thorn;ider his hate teres. <I>vtrasque lacrimas. scilicet peregrinati|onis &amp; contemplationis fudit fortasse apostolus quando dicebat. cupio dissolui &amp; esse cum Christo.</I> Ei&eth;er of &thorn;isse teres schedde &thorn;e apostel leste ich wene. &thorn;a &thorn;e he seide ich walde &thorn;et ich ded were; for me longe&eth; to criste. <MILESTONE N="59a" UNIT="folio"><I>hee quatuor lacrime sunt .iiii.</I><SUP>or</SUP> <I>aque quibus lauari iubemur per isayam dicentem. Lauamini</I> 
<PB REF="00000223.tif" N="159">
<I>mundi estote.</I> &thorn;os fure kunnes teres bo&eth; &thorn;e fuwer wateres; &thorn;a &thorn;e beo&eth; ihaten us on to weschen &thorn;urh ysaiam &thorn;e prophete &thorn;us que|&thorn;ende. beo&eth; iweschen; and w[u]nie&eth; clene. <I>Lacrima compunc|tionis est amara sicut aqua maris.</I> &THORN;e tere &thorn;et mon wep&eth; for his a&yogh;en sunne; is alse salt water. and &thorn;er fore hit is inemned see water. <I>Lacrima compunctionis comparatur aque niuis; que defluit contra calorem solis.</I> &THORN;e ter &thorn;et .Mon. schet for his em|cristenes sunne; is inemned snaw water for hit melt of &thorn;e neche<NOTE PLACE="marg">? nesche.</NOTE> horte swa de&eth; &thorn;e snaw to-&yogh;eines &thorn;e sunne. <I>Lacrima peregrina|tionis; comparatur aque fontis. quia sicut hec ebullit de terra; ita illa de cordis angustia.</I> &THORN;e ter &thorn;et .Mon. wep&eth; for la&eth;e of &thorn;isse liue; is inemned welle water. for he welle&eth; of &thorn;e horte swa do&eth; water of welle. <I>Lacrima contemplationis comparatur aque roris. quia sicut aqua illa nutu dei trahitur ab imo in altum; ita illa emanat per alti desiderium.</I> &THORN;e ter &thorn;et .Mon. wep&eth; for longinge to heouene; is inemned deu water for alswa se &thorn;e sunne drach up &thorn;ene deu. and make&eth; &thorn;er of kume reines; swa make&eth; &thorn;e halie gast &thorn;e .Mon. bi-halden up to houene. and hwenne he ne mai &thorn;ider cume alse ra&thorn;e se he walde; he send &thorn;ider his hate teres. and hwiche mede sculen ho fo of &thorn;isse sonde; <I>Salutem eternam. lucem perpetuam. vitam sempiternam.</I> eche hele. <MILESTONE N="59b" UNIT="folio"> les|tende liht. and endeles lif. swa wile god &thorn;et we moten &thorn;is fouwer kunnes teres sawen biuuen<NOTE PLACE="marg">? buuen.</NOTE> or&eth;e &thorn;et we moten to mede habben eche hele. and lesten[de] liht. and endeles lif. <I>Quod nobis prestare dignetur, et cetera. Amen.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="18" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XVIII. POEMA MORALE.</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ich em nu alder &thorn;ene ich wes awintre and a lare<NOTE PLACE="foot">The italics represent the rubrical letters of the MS.</NOTE>.</L>
<L>Ich welde mare &thorn;ene ich dede mi wit ahte<NOTE PLACE="marg">? ah.</NOTE> bon mare.</L>
<L>Wel longe ich habbe child ibon a worde and a<NOTE PLACE="marg">? ec a.</NOTE> dede</L>
<L N="4">&THORN;ah ich bo a wintre ald to &yogh;ung ich em on rede.
<PB REF="00000225.tif" N="161"></L>
<L>Vnnet lif ich habbe iled. and &yogh;et me &thorn;ing&thorn; ilede.</L>
<L>&THORN;enne ich me bi-&thorn;enche wel ful sare ich me adrede.</L>
<L>mest al &thorn;et ich habbe idon bi-fealt to child-hade.</L>
<L N="8">Wel late ich habbe me bi-&thorn;ocht; bute God me nu rede.</L>
<L>Fole idel word ich habbe ique&eth;en so&eth;&eth;en ich speke ku&eth;e.</L>
<L>fole &yogh;unge dede idon; &thorn;e me of-&thorn;inchet nu&eth;e.</L>
<L>Mest al &thorn;et me likede er nu; hit me mislike&eth;</L>
<L N="12">&thorn;a muchel fulie&eth; his wil; hine solf he biswike&eth;.</L>
<L>Ich mihte habbe bet idon. hefde ich &thorn;e isel&thorn;e.</L>
<L>Nu ich walde ah ich ne mei; for elde and for un-hel&thorn;e.</L>
<L>Elde me is bistolen on. er ich hit wiste.</L>
<L N="16">ne michte ich seon bi-fore me. for smike ne for miste.</L>
<L>Er&yogh;e we beo&eth; to done god. and to ufele al to &thorn;riste.</L>
<L>Mare eie stonde&eth; men of monne &thorn;anne hom do of criste.</L>
<L>&THORN;e wel ne do&eth; &thorn;e hwile &thorn;e ho mu&yogh;en. wel oft hit schal rowen;</L>
<L N="20">&thorn;enne &yogh;e mawen sculen and repen &thorn;et ho er sowen.</L>
<L>Do he to gode &thorn;et he mu&yogh;e &thorn;e hwile &thorn;et he bo aliue.</L>
<L>ne lipnie na mon to <MILESTONE N="60a" UNIT="folio">muchel to childe ne to wiue.</L>
<L>&thorn;e him solue for&yogh;et for wiue ne for childe;</L>
<L N="24">he scal cumen in uuel stude bute him God bo milde.</L>
<L>Sende&eth; sum god bi-foren eow. &thorn;e hw[i]le &thorn;et &yogh;e mu&yogh;en to houene.</L>
<L>for betere is an elmesse biforen; &thorn;enne bo&eth; efter souene.</L>
<L>Al to lome ich habbe igult a werke and o worde.</L>
<L N="28">Al to muchel ich habbe ispent. to litel ihud in horde.</L>
<L>Ne beo &thorn;e loure &thorn;ene &thorn;e solf; ne &thorn;in mei. ne &thorn;in ma&yogh;e.</L>
<L>Soht<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE> is &thorn;et is o&eth;ers monnes frond betre &thorn;en his a&yogh;en.</L>
<L>Ne lipnie wif to hire were. ne were to his wiue</L>
<L N="32">Bo for him solue ech .Mon. &thorn;e hwile &thorn;et he bo aliue.</L>
<L>Wis is &thorn;e to him solue &thorn;ench &thorn;e hwile &thorn;e mot libben.</L>
<L>For sone wule hine for&yogh;eten &thorn;e fremede and &thorn;e sibbe.</L>
<L>&thorn;e wel ne de&eth; &thorn;e hwile he mai; ne scal[he] wenne he walde.</L>
<L N="36">Monies monnes sare iswinc habbe&eth; oft unholde.</L>
<L>Ne scal na mon don afirst. ne slawen wel to done.</L>
<L>for moni mon bihate&eth; wel &thorn;e hit for&yogh;ete&eth; sone.</L>
<L>&THORN;e .Mon. &thorn;e wule siker bon to habben Godes blisse.
<PB REF="00000227.tif" N="163"></L>
<L N="40">do wel him solf hwile &thorn;et he mai; &thorn;enne haue&eth; he his mid iwisse.</L>
<L>&thorn;es riche .Men. wene&eth; bon siker &thorn;urh walle and &thorn;urh diche.</L>
<L>&thorn;e de&eth; his echte on sikere stude he hit sent to heueneriche.</L>
<L>For &thorn;er ne &thorn;erf he bon of-dred of fure ne of &thorn;oue</L>
<L N="44">&thorn;er ne <MILESTONE N="60b" UNIT="folio">&thorn;erf he him binimen &thorn;e la&eth;e ne &thorn;e loue.</L>
<L>&thorn;er ne &thorn;erf he habben kare of &yogh;efe ne of &yogh;elde.</L>
<L>&thorn;ider he sent. and solf bere&eth; to lutel and to selde.</L>
<L>&thorn;ider we sculen dra&yogh;en and don wel ofte and ilome.</L>
<L N="48">for &thorn;er ne scal me us naut binimen mid wrangwise dome.</L>
<L>&thorn;ider &yogh;e sculen &yogh;orne dra&yogh;en. walde &yogh;e god ileue.</L>
<L>for ne mei &thorn;er<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. &thorn;et.</NOTE> hit ou binimen king ne reue.</L>
<L>Al &thorn;et beste &thorn;et we hefden &thorn;ider we hit solde senden</L>
<L N="52">for &thorn;er we hit michte finden eft. and habben buten ende.</L>
<L>&THORN;o &thorn;e er do&eth; eni God for habben godes are.</L>
<L>al he hit scal finden eft &thorn;er and hundred fald mare.</L>
<L>&THORN;e &thorn;et echte wile habben wel hwile &thorn;e he mu&yogh;e es welden.</L>
<L N="56">Giue hies for godes luue; &thorn;enne de&thorn; hes wel ihalden.</L>
<L>Vre swinc and ure til&thorn;e is ofte iwoned to swinden.</L>
<L>Ach &thorn;et &thorn;e we do&eth; for godes luue; eft we sculen al finden.</L>
<L>Ne scal nan ufel bon unbocht. ne nan god unfor&yogh;olden.</L>
<L N="60">Vfel we do&eth; al to muchel. and god lesse &thorn;enne we sculden.</L>
<L>&THORN;o &thorn;e mest do&eth; nu to gode. and &thorn;e lest to la&eth;e.</L>
<L>Ei&eth;er to lutel and to muchel scal &thorn;unchen eft hom ba&thorn;e.</L>
<L>&THORN;er me scal ure werkes weien bi-foran &thorn;e heuen king.</L>
<L N="64">and &yogh;euen us ure swinkes lan efter ure erninge.</L>
<L>Ech mon mid &thorn;et he hauet mei buggen houene riche.</L>
<L>&thorn;e mare haue&thorn; and &thorn;e &thorn;e lesse; ba&thorn;e hi <MILESTONE N="61a" UNIT="folio">mu&yogh;en iliche.</L>
<L>Alse mid his penie alse o&eth;er mi&eth; his punde.</L>
<L N="68">&thorn;et is &thorn;e wunderlukeste chep; &thorn;et eni mon efre funde.</L>
<L>And &thorn;e &eth;e mare ne mai don; do hit mid his gode &thorn;onke.</L>
<L>Alse wel se &thorn;e &thorn;e haue&eth; golde fele manke.</L>
<L>And oft god kon mare &thorn;onc &thorn;en &thorn;e him &yogh;eue&eth; lesse.</L>
<L N="72">And his werkes and his we&yogh;es his milce. and rihtwisnesse.</L>
<L>lutel lac is gode lof; &thorn;et kume&eth; of gode wille.
<PB REF="00000229.tif" N="165"></L>
<L>And ec-lete<NOTE PLACE="marg">? et-lete.</NOTE> muchel &yogh;eue of &thorn;an &thorn;e herte is ille.</L>
<L>Houene and hor&thorn;e he ouer sich. his e&yogh;en bo&eth; swa brichte</L>
<L N="76">Sunne and mone and houen fur bo&eth; &thorn;estre a&yogh;ein his lihte.</L>
<L>Nis him noht forholen nihud. swa muchele bo&eth; his mihte.</L>
<L>nis hit ne swa derne [idon] ne [a] swa &thorn;ostre nihte.</L>
<L>he wat wet &thorn;enke&eth; and hwet do&eth; alle quike wihte.</L>
<L N="80">Nis na lauerd swich se is crist. ne king swuch ure drihten.</L>
<L>houene and or&eth;e and al &thorn;et is biloken is in his honde.</L>
<L>he de&eth; al &thorn;et his wil is; a wettre and alonde.</L>
<L>He makede fisses in &thorn;e se and fu&yogh;eles in &thorn;e lifte.</L>
<L N="84">he wit and walde&eth; alle &thorn;ing and scop alle scefte.</L>
<L>he is hord buten horde and ende buten ende.</L>
<L>he ane is eure an ilche stude wende &thorn;er &thorn;u wende.</L>
<L>he is buuen us and bino&thorn;en. biforen and bihinden.</L>
<L N="88">&thorn;e &thorn;e de&eth; godes wille uwer he mei him finden.</L>
<L>Helche rune he iher&eth; and wat [he] alle deden.</L>
<L>he &thorn;ur&thorn;-siche&thorn; uches monnes &thorn;onc. wi hwat scal us to rede.</L>
<L>We &thorn;et broke&eth; godes hese and gulte&eth; swa ilome.</L>
<L N="92">hwet scule we seggen o&eth;er don et &thorn;e muchele dome</L>
<L>&THORN;a &thorn;e luueden unriht and ufel lif <MILESTONE N="61b" UNIT="folio">leden.</L>
<L>Wet sculen ho seggen o&eth;er don; &thorn;en &thorn;e engles bon of-dred.</L>
<L>hwet sculen we beren biforen us mid hom scule we iquemen.</L>
<L N="96">&thorn;o &thorn;e neure god ne dude &thorn;e houenliche deme[n].</L>
<L>&thorn;er sculen bon doule swa fole &thorn;et wulle&eth; us forwreien.</L>
<L>And nabbe&eth; hi na&thorn;ing for&yogh;eten of al &thorn;et ho [ere] ise&yogh;en.</L>
<L>Al &thorn;et we misduden her; ho hit wulle&eth; ku&eth;e &thorn;ere.</L>
<L N="100">Al ho habbe&eth; in hore write &thorn;et we misduden here.</L>
<L>[Buten we habben it ibet &thorn;e wile we her were]</L>
<L>&THORN;ach we nusten ne nise&yogh;en. ho weren ure ifere.</L>
<L>Hwet sculen ordlinghes<NOTE PLACE="marg">? orlinges.</NOTE> don &thorn;a swicen and ta for|sworene</L>
<L N="104">hwi bo&eth; fole iclepede. and swa lut icorene</L>
<L>wi hwi weren ho bi&yogh;eten to hwon weren ho iborene.</L>
<L>&thorn;et sculen bon to de&thorn;e idemet. and eure ma forlorene.
<PB REF="00000231.tif" N="167"></L>
<L>Ech .Mon. scal him solue &thorn;er biclepie and bidemen.</L>
<L N="108">his a&yogh;en werch and his &thorn;onc te witnesse he scal demen<NOTE PLACE="marg">? temen.</NOTE>.</L>
<L>ne mei him na Mon alsa wel demen ne alswa rihte</L>
<L>for nan ne knau&eth; him ase &yogh;ere; buten ane drihte.</L>
<L>Ech .Mon. wat him solue best; his werkes. and his wille.</L>
<L N="112">&THORN;e &eth;e lest wat bisei&eth; ofte mest; &thorn;e hit al wat is stille.</L>
<L>nis nan witnesse alse muchel se monnes a&yogh;en horte.</L>
<L>Wa se sei&eth; &thorn;et he bo hal. him solf wat best his smirte.</L>
<L>Ech .Mon. scal hin<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. hm.</NOTE> solf demen to de&eth;e o&eth;er to liue.</L>
<L N="116">&thorn;a witnesse of his a&yogh;en werch; hine &thorn;er to scal driue.</L>
<L>Al &thorn;et ech .Mon. haue&eth; idon so&eth;&eth;en he com to monne</L>
<L>sculde he <MILESTONE N="62a" UNIT="folio">hit sechen o boke iwriten he scal i&thorn;enchen &thorn;enne.</L>
<L>Ah drihten ne deme&eth; nenne .Mon. efter his biginnigge.</L>
<L N="120">ah al his lif scal bon suilch bo&eth; his endinge.</L>
<L>&yogh;ef &thorn;et his [ende is] uuel al hit is uuel and [al] God &yogh;efe god his ende.</L>
<L>God &yogh;eue &thorn;et ure ende bo god. and wite &thorn;et he us lende.</L>
<L>&thorn;e .Mon. &thorn;et uuel<NOTE PLACE="marg">? nule.</NOTE> don na god. ne neure god lif leden.</L>
<L N="124">er de&eth; and dom come to his dure he mei him sare adreden.</L>
<L>&thorn;et he ne mu&yogh;e &thorn;enne biden are. for &thorn;et itit ilome.</L>
<L>for-&thorn;i he is wis &thorn;e biet and bit and bet bi-fore dome.</L>
<L>Wenne de&eth; is attere dure wel late he bidde&thorn; are.</L>
<L N="128">Wel late he lathe&eth; uuel werc; &thorn;e ne mei hit don ne mare.</L>
<L>&thorn;et achten we to leuen wel. for ure drihten solf hit seide.</L>
<L>A hwilke time se eure .Mon. of &thorn;inch&thorn; his mis-dede.</L>
<L>O&thorn;er ra&thorn;er o&eth;er later; milce he scal imeten.</L>
<L N="132">Ac we<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &thorn;e.</NOTE> &thorn;et &thorn;er naf[e&eth;] nocht ibet; wel muchel he haue&eth; to beten.</L>
<L>Moni mon seit hwa rech&eth; of pine &thorn;e scal habben ende.</L>
<L>Ne bidde ich na bet bo alesed a domes dei of bende.</L>
<L>Lutel he wat wet is pine. and lutel he hit scawe&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg">? icnawe&eth;.</NOTE></L>
<L N="136">hwice hete is &thorn;er &thorn;a saule wune&eth; hu biter wind &thorn;er blawe&eth;.</L>
<L>hefde he bon &thorn;er enne dei o&eth;er twa bare tide;
<PB REF="00000233.tif" N="169"></L>
<L>nolde he for al middenerd &thorn;e &thorn;erdde &thorn;er abiden.</L>
<L>&thorn;et habbe&eth; iseid &thorn;[et] comen &thorn;onen &thorn;a hit wisten mid iwissen.</L>
<L N="140">wa wur&eth; sor&yogh;e seue&yogh;er. for souenihte blisse.</L>
<L>In<NOTE PLACE="marg">? And.</NOTE> hure blisse &thorn;e <MILESTONE N="62b" UNIT="folio">&thorn;e ende haue&eth;. for endelese pine.</L>
<L>betere is wori water drunch; &thorn;en atter meind mid wine.</L>
<L>Swines brede is swi&eth;e swete. swa is of wilde dore.</L>
<L N="144">alto dore he is abuh; &thorn;e &yogh;ef&eth; &thorn;er fore his swore.</L>
<L>Ful wombe mei lihtliche speken of hunger. and of festen;</L>
<L>swa mei of pine &thorn;e ne cnau&eth; [hu] &thorn;e scal a ilesten.</L>
<L>Hef&eth; he ifonded summe stunde; he wolde al seggen o&eth;er.</L>
<L N="148">Et-lete him were wif. child. suster. feder and bro&eth;er.</L>
<L>Al he walde and o&eth;erluker don and o&eth;erluker &thorn;enchen</L>
<L>Wenne he bi-&thorn;ohte on helle fur &thorn;e nawiht ne mei quenchen.</L>
<L>Eure he walde her inne wawe and ine wene wunien;</L>
<L N="152">Wi&eth; &thorn;et &thorn;e mihte helle pine bi-flien and bi-sunien</L>
<L>Et lete him were al world wele and or&eth;liche blisse.</L>
<L>for to &thorn;et muchele blisse cumen is mur&thorn;e mid iwisse.</L>
<L>Iwule nu cumen eft to &thorn;e dome &thorn;et ich er ow of sede</L>
<L N="156">A &thorn;a dei and at ta dome us helpe crist and rede.</L>
<L>&thorn;er we mu&yogh;en bon e&thorn;e offerd and herde us adreden.</L>
<L>&thorn;er he scal al son him biforen his word and ec his deden.</L>
<L>Al scal &thorn;er bon &thorn;enne cud &thorn;er men lu&yogh;en her ent stelen.</L>
<L N="160">Al scal &thorn;er bon &thorn;anne unwron; &thorn;et men wru&yogh;en her and helen.</L>
<L>We sculen alre monne lif iknauwen [&thorn;er] alse ure ahen.</L>
<L>&thorn;er sculen eueningges bon &thorn;e riche and &thorn;e la&yogh;e.</L>
<L>Ne scal na mon smakie<NOTE PLACE="marg">for skamie.</NOTE> &thorn;er ne &thorn;erf he him adreden.</L>
<L N="164">Gif him her of-&thorn;inc&thorn; <MILESTONE N="63a" UNIT="folio">his gult and bet his misdede.</L>
<L>For him ne scame&thorn; ne ne grome&eth; &thorn;e sculen bon ibor&yogh;en.</L>
<L>Ach &thorn;o&thorn;re habbe&thorn; scome and grome and oft fele sor&yogh;e.</L>
<L>&THORN;e dom scal sone bon idon ne lest he nawiht longe.</L>
<L N="168">ne scal him na mon mene &thorn;er of streng&thorn;e ne of wronge.</L>
<L>&THORN;e sculen habbe herdne dom &thorn;a her weren herde.</L>
<L>&THORN;a &thorn;e uuele holden wreche men and uuele la&yogh;e redde.
<PB REF="00000235.tif" N="171"></L>
<L>Ec efter &thorn;et he ef&eth; idon s[c]al &thorn;er &thorn;enne [beon] idemet.</L>
<L N="172">[Bli&thorn;e mai he &thorn;anne buen &thorn;e god haued iquemed]</L>
<L>Alle &thorn;a &thorn;i sprunge bo&thorn; of adam and of eue.</L>
<L>Alle hi sculen cumen &thorn;ider for so&eth;e we hit ileue&eth;.</L>
<L>&thorn;a &thorn;e habbe&eth; wel idon efter hore mihte.</L>
<L N="176">to houene riche hi sculen faren for&eth; mid ure drihte.</L>
<L>&THORN;a &thorn;e habbe&eth; doules werc idon. and &thorn;er inne bo ifunde.</L>
<L>hi sculen faren for&eth; mid him in to helle grunde.</L>
<L>&THORN;er hi sculen wunien a buten are and ende.</L>
<L N="180">Ne breke&thorn; ne ure drihte helle gate for lesen hi of bende.</L>
<L>Nis na sullic &thorn;ech hom bo wa and hom bo uneade.</L>
<L>Ne scal neure eft crist &thorn;olie de&thorn; for lesen hom of dea&thorn;e.</L>
<L>Enes drihten helle brec his frond he ut brochte.</L>
<L N="184">him solf he &thorn;olede de&eth; for him<NOTE PLACE="marg">? heom.</NOTE>. wel dore he hom bohte.</L>
<L>Nalde hit mei do for mei. ne suster for bro&eth;er.</L>
<L>nalde hit sune do for fader. ne na mon for o&eth;er.</L>
<L>Vre alre lauerd for his &thorn;relles ipined wes a rode.</L>
<L N="188">vre bendes he unbon[d] and bohte us mid his blode.</L>
<L>We &yogh;eue&eth; <MILESTONE N="63b" UNIT="folio">une&eth;e for his luue a stuche of ure brede.</L>
<L>Ne &thorn;enke we noht &thorn;et he scal deme &thorn;a quike and &thorn;a dede.</L>
<L>Muchele luue he us cudde. walde we hit understonde</L>
<L N="192">&thorn;et ure eldre misduden; we habbe&eth; uuele on honde.</L>
<L>De&thorn; com in &thorn;is middenerde &thorn;urh &thorn;es doules honde.</L>
<L>And sake and sor&yogh;e and swinc a watere and a londe.</L>
<L>vre forme fader gult. we abu&yogh;e&eth; alle.</L>
<L N="196">[Al his ofsprunge after hym in herme is bifalle]</L>
<L>&thorn;urst and hunger. chele and hete. helde and unhel&eth;e.</L>
<L>&thorn;urh him de&eth; com in &thorn;is middenerd and o&eth;er unisel&eth;e.</L>
<L>Nere namon elles ded ne sec ne nan unsele.</L>
<L N="200">ac mihten libben eure ma a blisse and a hele.</L>
<L>lutel hit &thorn;unche&eth; moni mon. ac muchel wes &thorn;a sunne.</L>
<L>for hwam alle &thorn;olie&eth; de&eth; &thorn;e comen of hore cunne.</L>
<L>Hore sunne and ec ure a&yogh;en sare us mei of-&thorn;inche.</L>
<L N="204">&thorn;urh sunne we libbe&eth; alle in sor&yogh;e and in swinke.
<PB REF="00000237.tif" N="173"></L>
<L>Su&eth;&eth;en God nom swa muchele wrake for are misdede;</L>
<L>We &thorn;e swa muchel and swa ofte mis-do&eth;. we mu&yogh;en e&eth;e us adrede.</L>
<L>Adam and his of-sprung for are &thorn;are<NOTE PLACE="marg">? bare.</NOTE> sunne.</L>
<L N="208">Wes fele undret wintre an helle pine and an unwunne.</L>
<L>&THORN;a &thorn;e ledden hore lif mid unriht and mid wrange.</L>
<L>buten hit godes milce do ho sculen bon &thorn;er wel longe.</L>
<L>Godes wisdom is wel muchel and alswa is his mihte</L>
<L N="212">And nis his milce naut lesse. ac bi &thorn;an ilke iwichte.</L>
<L>Mare he ane mei for&yogh;euen. &thorn;en <MILESTONE N="64a" UNIT="folio">al folc gulte cunne.</L>
<L>Sulf douel mihte habben milce. &yogh;if he hit bigunne.</L>
<L>&THORN;a &thorn;e godes milce seche&eth;; he iwis mei ha ifinden.</L>
<L N="216">Ac helle king is are-les with &thorn;a &thorn;e he mei binden.</L>
<L>&thorn;e &thorn;e de&thorn; is wille mest; he haue&eth; wurst mede.</L>
<L>His ba&thorn; scal bon wallinde. his ba&eth; scal<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. scab.</NOTE> bon berninde glede.</L>
<L>Wurst he de&eth; his gode frond; &thorn;enne his fulle fond[e];</L>
<L N="220">God scilde alle godes frond. a wih swilche freonde.</L>
<L>Neure in helle hi com. ne &thorn;er ne come reche.</L>
<L>&THORN;ach ich elches worldes wele. &thorn;er me mahte feche</L>
<L>&thorn;et his wulle seggen on &thorn;at wise men us seiden.</L>
<L N="224">And aboken hit writen &thorn;er [me] mei hit reden.</L>
<L>Ich hit wille seggen &thorn;an &thorn;e hit hom solf nusten.</L>
<L>Warni hom wi&eth; hore unfrome. &yogh;if ho me wulle&eth; lusten.</L>
<L>Vnderstonde&eth; nu to me edi men and arme.</L>
<L N="228">Ich wulle tellen of helle pin; and wernin ow wi&eth; herme.</L>
<L>In helle his hunger and &thorn;urst; twa uuele iuere.</L>
<L>&thorn;as [pine] &thorn;olie&eth; &thorn;a weren maket<NOTE PLACE="marg">? mete.</NOTE> ni&thorn;inges here.</L>
<L>&THORN;er is waning and wow. efter eche streche.</L>
<L N="232">ho fare&eth; from hete to hete. and hech to frure &thorn;e wreche.</L>
<L>&thorn;enne hi bi&eth; in &thorn;ere hete; &thorn;e chele him &thorn;unchet blisse.</L>
<L>&thorn;enne hi cume&eth; eft to &thorn;e chele; of hete hi habbe&eth; misse.</L>
<L>hi hem de&eth; wa inoch nabbe&eth; hi nane blisse.</L>
<L N="236">Nute hi hwe&thorn;er hom de&thorn; wurs<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. &thorn;urs.</NOTE> mid neure nane wisse.</L>
<L>hi walke&eth; eure and seche&eth; reste <MILESTONE N="64b" UNIT="folio">ac ho ne mu&yogh;en imeten.
<PB REF="00000239.tif" N="175"></L>
<L>for-&thorn;i &thorn;e ho nolden &thorn;e hwile &thorn;et ho mihten here sunne beten.</L>
<L>ho seche&eth; reste &thorn;er nis nan. for-&thorn;i ne mu&yogh;en hi es finden.</L>
<L N="240">Ac walke&eth; weri up and dun; se water de&thorn; mid winde.</L>
<L>&thorn;o bo&eth; &thorn;a &thorn;e weren her a &thorn;anke unstedefeste.</L>
<L>And &thorn;a &thorn;e gode biheten heste and nolden hit ileste.</L>
<L>&THORN;a &thorn;e god werc bigunnen and ful enden hit nolden.</L>
<L N="244">Nu witen<NOTE PLACE="marg">? weren.</NOTE> her. and nu&eth;e &thorn;er. and nusten hwat hi wolden.</L>
<L>&thorn;er is bernunde pich hore saule to ba&thorn;ien inne.</L>
<L>&thorn;a &thorn;e ledden here lif in werre and in winne.</L>
<L>&THORN;er is fur &thorn;et is undret fald hattre. &thorn;ene bo ure.</L>
<L N="248">Ne mei quenchen salt weter ne uersc of &thorn;e burne.</L>
<L>&THORN;is is &thorn;et fur &thorn;et efre bernd ne mei nawiht hit quenchen.</L>
<L>&THORN;er inne bo&eth; &thorn;a &thorn;e was to lof wreche men to swenchen.</L>
<L>&thorn;a &thorn;e weren swikelemen and ful of uuel wrenchen.</L>
<L N="252">&thorn;a &thorn;e mihten uuel don. &thorn;e &thorn;e lef hit wes to &thorn;enchen.</L>
<L>&THORN;e luueden tening and stale. hordom and drunken</L>
<L>And a doules werche bli&thorn;eliche swunken.</L>
<L>&THORN;a &thorn;e weren swa lese<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. lele.</NOTE> &thorn;et me hom ne mihte ileuen.</L>
<L N="256">Med-ierne domes men. and wrongwise reuen.</L>
<L>&thorn;et o&eth;er monnes wif lof. his a&yogh;en et-lete.</L>
<L>&thorn;o &thorn;e sungede muchel; a drunke and an ete.</L>
<L>&thorn;e wreche mon binom his ehte. and leide his on horde.</L>
<L N="260">&thorn;et lutel let of godes borde. and godes worde.</L>
<L>And &thorn;o &thorn;e his a&yogh;en nalde &yogh;euen &thorn;er he isech. <MILESTONE N="65a" UNIT="folio">&thorn;e node</L>
<L>ne nalde iheren godes sonde. &thorn;enne he hit herde bode.</L>
<L>&THORN;e &thorn;et is o&eth;ers monnes &thorn;ing. loure &thorn;ene hit sculde.</L>
<L N="264">And weren to gredi of solure and of golde.</L>
<L>And &thorn;a &thorn;e untrownesse duden &thorn;on &thorn;e ho sculden bon holde.</L>
<L>And leten &thorn;et ho sculden don. and duden &thorn;et ho wolden.</L>
<L>&THORN;a &thorn;e weren eure abuten &thorn;isse worldes echte.</L>
<L N="268">And duden al &thorn;et &thorn;e la&thorn;e gast hechte to and tachte.</L>
<L>And alle &thorn;e &thorn;en anigewise doulen iquemde<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. iquende.</NOTE>.</L>
<L>&THORN;a bo&eth; nu mid him in helle fordon and fordemet<NOTE PLACE="marg">? fordemde.</NOTE>.</L>
<L>[Bute &thorn;o &thorn;e of&thorn;ouhte sore. her here mis-deden</L>
<L N="272">and gunnen here gultes beten. and betere lif leden
<PB REF="00000241.tif" N="177"></L>
<L>&THORN;eor be&eth; naddren and snaken. eueten and frude</L>
<L>&thorn;a tered and frete&eth; &thorn;e uuele speken. &thorn;e nihtfulle and &thorn;e prute</L>
<L>Neure sunne &thorn;er ne scin&eth;. ne mone ne steorre</L>
<L N="276">&thorn;er is muchel godes hete. and muchel godes &yogh;eorre</L>
<L>Eure &thorn;er is vuel smech. &thorn;usternesse and eie</L>
<L>nis &thorn;er neure o&thorn;er liht. &thorn;anne &thorn;e swarte leie</L>
<L>&THORN;er ligget la&eth;liche fend. in stronge raketeie</L>
<L N="280">&thorn;at bu&eth; &thorn;e &thorn;e were mid gode. on heuene wel heie</L>
<L>&THORN;er bu&eth; ateliche fend. and eisliche wihte</L>
<L>&thorn;os sculle &thorn;a wrecchen i-son. &thorn;e sunege &thorn;ur&eth; sihte</L>
<L>&THORN;er is &thorn;e lo&thorn;e sathanas. and belsebuc &thorn;e ealde</L>
<L N="284">Ie&thorn;e he muwen ben of-drad<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. of-drard.</NOTE>. &thorn;e hine sculled bi-helde</L>
<L>Ne mai non heorte it &thorn;enche. ne no tunge ne can telle</L>
<L>hu muchele pine. and hu vele. senden inne helle</L>
<L>Of &thorn;o pine &thorn;e &thorn;ere bued. nelle ic hou nout leio&yogh;en</L>
<L N="288">nis it bute gamen and gleo. al &thorn;at man mai here dreo&yogh;en</L>
<L>Ac &yogh;et ne de&eth; heom nout so wo. in &thorn;o lo&thorn;e biende</L>
<L>bute &thorn;at hi wite&eth; &thorn;at heore pine. ne scal neure habben ende</L>
<L>&THORN;er bu&eth; &thorn;o he&thorn;enemen. &thorn;e were lawe-lese</L>
<L N="292">&thorn;e heom nas nout of godes bode. ne of godes hese</L>
<L>Vuele cristenemen. hi bud here i-vere</L>
<L>&thorn;o &thorn;e heore cristen-dom. vuele heolden here</L>
<L>&YOGH;ut hi bud a wurse stede. on &thorn;ere helle grunde</L>
<L N="296">ne sculle hi neure comen vp. for marke ne for punde</L>
<L>Ne mai heom no&thorn;er helpen &thorn;er. i-bede ne almesse</L>
<L>for nis no&thorn;er inne helle. ore ne for&yogh;iuenesse</L>
<L>Sculde him elc man &thorn;e wile he mai. of &thorn;os helle pine</L>
<L N="300">And warnie &aelig;c his frend &thorn;er wid. so ic habbe mine</L>
<L>&THORN;o &thorn;e scilden heom ne cunnen. ic heom wulle teache</L>
<L>ich kan beo &yogh;if i scal. lichame and soule liache</L>
<L>Lete we &thorn;at god for-bet. alle mancunne</L>
<L N="304">and do we &thorn;at he us hat. and scilde we us wid sunne</L>
<L>Luuie we god mid vre heorte. and mid al vre mihte</L>
<L>and vre emcristene alse us suelf. swa us lerde drihte</L>
<L>Al &thorn;at me rat and sing&eth;. be-fore godes borde</L>
<L N="308">al it hanged and bi-halt. bi &thorn;isse twam worde
<PB REF="00000243.tif" N="179"></L>
<L>Alle godes lawe he ful&eth;. &thorn;e newe and &thorn;e ealde</L>
<L>he &thorn;e &thorn;os twa luue haued. and wel hi wule healde</L>
<L>Ac hi bu&eth; wunder erued-helde. swa ofte we gulted alle</L>
<L N="312">for it is strong to stonde longe. and liht it is to falle</L>
<L>Ac drihte crist he &yogh;iue us strenc&thorn;e. stonde &thorn;at we mote</L>
<L>and of alle vre gultes. unne us come bote</L>
<L>We wilnied efter worldes wele. &thorn;e longe ne mai ileste</L>
<L N="316">and legge&eth; al ure iswinch. on &thorn;inge un-stede-faste</L>
<L>Sswunche we for godes luue. half &thorn;at we do&eth; for ehte</L>
<L>ne were we nout swa bi-cherd. ne swa vuele bi-cauhte</L>
<L>&YOGH;if we serueden god. so we do&eth; erninges</L>
<L N="320">more we haueden of heuene. &thorn;anne eorles o&thorn;er kinges</L>
<L>Ne muwen hi her werien heom wid chele. wid &thorn;urst. ne wid hunger</L>
<L>ne wid elde ne wid de&eth;. &thorn;e eldre ne &thorn;e &yogh;eonger</L>
<L>Ac &thorn;er nis hunger ne &thorn;urst ne de&eth;. ne vnhel&thorn;e ne elde</L>
<L N="324">of &thorn;isse riche we &thorn;enchet oft. and of &thorn;ere to selde</L>
<L>We scolden alle us bi-&thorn;enche. oft and wel ilome</L>
<L>hwet we be&eth;. and to wan we sculle. and of wan we come</L>
<L>Hu lutel wile we be&eth; her. hu longe elles ware</L>
<L N="328">hwat we mu&yogh;en habben her. and hwet elles hware</L>
<L>&YOGH;if we were wise men. &thorn;is we scolden i&thorn;enche</L>
<L>bute we wur&thorn;e us iwar. &thorn;es worl&eth; us wule for-drenche</L>
<L>Mest alle men he &yogh;iued drinke. of one deofles scenche</L>
<L N="332">he sceal him cunne sculde wel. &yogh;if he him nele screnche</L>
<L>Mid ealm[i]hties godes luue. vte we us bi-werien</L>
<L>wid &thorn;es wrecches worldes luue. &thorn;at he ne mawe us derien</L>
<L>Mid fasten. and almesse. and ibede. werie we us wid sunne</L>
<L N="336">Mid &thorn;o wepnen &thorn;e god haued &yogh;iuen alle mancunne</L>
<L>L&aelig;te we &thorn;e brode stret. and &thorn;e wei bene</L>
<L>&thorn;e lat &thorn;e ni&yogh;e&eth;e del to helle of manne. and mo ic wene</L>
<L>Go we &thorn;ene narewe wei. and &thorn;ene wei grene</L>
<L N="340">&thorn;er for&eth;-fare&eth; lutel folc. ac it is feir and scene</L>
<L>&THORN;e brode stret is vre iwil. &eth;e is us lod for to lete</L>
<L>&thorn;e &eth;e al folewed his wil. fared bi &thorn;usse strete</L>
<L>Hi muwen lihtliche gon. mid &eth;ere nu&eth;er hulde
<PB REF="00000245.tif" N="181"></L>
<L N="344">&eth;urh ane godliese wude. in-to ane bare felde</L>
<L>&THORN;e narewei is godes hes. &thorn;er for&eth;-far&eth; wel feuwe</L>
<L>&thorn;at bu&eth; &eth;a &thorn;e heom sculde&eth; &yogh;eorne. wid elche un|&eth;eawe</L>
<L>&THORN;os god un-ie&thorn;e to-&yogh;eanes &thorn;e cliue a&yogh;ean &thorn;e he&yogh;e hulle</L>
<L N="348">&thorn;os lete&eth; al here a&yogh;en wil. for godes hese to fulle</L>
<L>Go we alle &thorn;ene wei. for he us wulle bringe</L>
<L>mid &thorn;o faire feuwe men. be-foren heuene kinge</L>
<L>&THORN;er is alre meru&thorn;e mest. mid englene songe</L>
<L N="352">&thorn;e &thorn;is a &thorn;usent wintre &thorn;er. ne &thorn;inc&eth; him noht to longe</L>
<L>&THORN;e &thorn;e lest haued. haue&eth; so muchel. &thorn;at he ne bit no more</L>
<L>&thorn;e &eth;e blisse for &eth;os for-lat. it him mai reuwe sore</L>
<L>Ne mai non vuel ne non wane. beon inne godes riche</L>
<L N="356">&eth;eh &thorn;er be&eth; wunienges fele. elc o&thorn;er vn-iliche</L>
<L>Sume &thorn;er habbet lasse murh&eth;e. and sume habbed more</L>
<L>after &thorn;an &thorn;e hi dude her. after &thorn;an &thorn;e hi swonke sore</L>
<L>Ne scal &thorn;er ben bred ne win. ne o&thorn;er cunnes este</L>
<L N="360">god one scal beo eche lif. and blisse. and eche reste</L>
<L>Ne scal &thorn;er beo fou ne grei. ne cunig ne ermine</L>
<L>ne ocquerne ne martres cheole. ne beuer ne sabeline</L>
<L>Ne scal &thorn;er beo sced ne scrud. ne woruld wele none</L>
<L N="364">al &thorn;e murh&eth;e &thorn;e me us bi-hat. al it scal beo god one</L>
<L>Ne mai non murh&eth;e beo so muchel. so is godes sihte</L>
<L>he is so&eth; sunne and briht. and dai a-buten nihte</L>
<L>He is elches godes ful. nis him no&thorn;ing &yogh;it vten</L>
<L N="368">no god nis him wane. &thorn;e wunied him abuten</L>
<L>&THORN;er is wele abute grame. and reste abuten swinche</L>
<L>&thorn;e mai and nele &thorn;ider come. sore it him scal of&thorn;inche</L>
<L>&THORN;er is blisse abuten tre&yogh;e. and lif abuten dea&thorn;e</L>
<L N="372">&thorn;e eure scullen wunien &thorn;er. bli&thorn;e muwen ben e&thorn;e</L>
<L>&THORN;er is &yogh;eo&yogh;e&eth;e bute ulde. and hele abuten vn-hel&eth;e</L>
<L>nis &thorn;er sorewe ne sor. ne neure nan vn-seal&thorn;e</L>
<L>&THORN;er me scal drihte sulf i-seon. swa he is mid iwisse</L>
<L N="376">he one mai and scal al beo. engle and manne blisse</L>
<L>And &eth;eh ne beod heore e&yogh;e naht. alle iliche brihte
<PB REF="00000247.tif" N="183"></L>
<L>&eth;i nabbed hi nouht iliche. alle of godes lihte</L>
<L>On &thorn;isse liue hi neren nout. alle of one mihte</L>
<L N="380">ne &thorn;er ne scullen hi habben god. alle bi one &yogh;ihte</L>
<L>&THORN;o scullen more of him seon. &thorn;e luuede him her more</L>
<L>and more icnawen and iwiten. his mihte and his ore</L>
<L>On him hi scullen finden al &thorn;at man mai to lesten</L>
<L N="384">hali boc hi sculle i-seon. al &thorn;at hi her nusten</L>
<L>Crist scal one beon mou. alle his durlinges</L>
<L>he one is muchele mare and betere. &thorn;anne alle o&thorn;ere &thorn;inges</L>
<L>Inoh he haued &thorn;e hine haue&eth;. &thorn;e alle &thorn;ing wealde&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. wealded.</NOTE></L>
<L N="388">of him to sene nis no sed. wel hem is &thorn;e hine bi-healde&eth;</L>
<L>God is so mere and swa muchel. in his godcunnesse</L>
<L>&thorn;at al &thorn;at is. and al &thorn;at wes is wurse. &thorn;enne he and lesse</L>
<L>Ne mai it neure no man o&thorn;er segge mid iwisse</L>
<L N="392">hu muchele murh&eth;e habbet &thorn;o. &thorn;e beod inne godes blisse</L>
<L>To &thorn;ere blisse us bringe god. &thorn;e rixlet abuten ende</L>
<L>&thorn;enne he vre soule vn-bint. of licames bende</L>
<L>Crist &yogh;yue us leden her swilc lif. and habben her swilc ende</L>
<L N="396">&thorn;at we moten &thorn;uder come. wanne we henne wende. Amen.</L>
</LG>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="19" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XIX. [ON UREISUN OF OURE LOUERDE.]</HEAD>
<P>[I] Hesu so&eth; god. godes sone. ihesu so&eth; go&eth;. so&eth; mon. Mon<MILESTONE N="65b" UNIT="folio"> Maidene bern. Ihesu min hali loue min sikere spet|nesse<NOTE PLACE="marg">?swetnesse.</NOTE>. Ihesu min heorte. Mi sel. mi saule hele. Ihesu swete. ihesu mi leof. mi lif. mi leome. Min halwi. Min huniter. &thorn;u al &thorn;et ic hopie. Ihesu mi weole mi wunne. Min bli&thorn;e breostes blisse. Ihesu teke &thorn;et tu art se softe. and se swote. &yogh;ette to swa leoflic. swo leoflic and swa lufsum. &thorn;et te engles .a. biholde&thorn; 
<PB REF="00000249.tif" N="185"> &thorn;e. Ne beo&thorn; heo neuer fulle. forto lokin on &thorn;e. Ihesu al feir a|&yogh;ein hwam. &thorn;e sunne nis boten a schadwe. ase &thorn;eo &thorn;et leose&thorn; here liht. and scome&thorn; a&yogh;ein &thorn;i brihte leor. of hire &thorn;esturnesse. &thorn;u &thorn;et &yogh;euest hire liht and al &thorn;et leome hauest aliht mi &thorn;ester heorte. &yogh;ef &thorn;i bur brihtnesse. mi saule &thorn;et is suti &yogh;et. make hire wur&thorn;e to &thorn;i swete wunninge. Ontend me wi&thorn; &thorn;e blase. of &thorn;i leitinde loue. let me beo mi<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &THORN;i.</NOTE> leofmon and her<NOTE PLACE="marg">? ler.</NOTE> to loue &thorn;e. louie &thorn;e louende louerd. wa [is me] &thorn;et ic am swa fremede. wi&thorn; &thorn;e. Ah ase &thorn;u licomliche iwend iwend me from the worlde. wend me. and<NOTE PLACE="marg">? ec.</NOTE> heorte-liche. and turn me allunge to &thorn;e. wi&thorn; so&thorn;e loue. and bileue. Ich nabbe no mong. ne felawscipe. ne priuete. wi&thorn; &thorn;e world. for wel ich &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>read</I> wat.</NOTE> mi leofmon dear ich swa clipien. &thorn;et flehsliche loue. and gostliche eor&thorn;liche lou<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. louo <I>for</I> loue?</NOTE> and heouenliche. ne ma&yogh;en onone wise beddin in a breoste. hwa se euer haue&eth; longe wone of gastliche elne. of heouenliche murh&eth;e hit is for-&thorn;i ha haue&thorn;. o&thorn;er wilne&thorn; after cunfort on eor&thorn;e. &thorn;et is fikel. and fals. and al imengd wi&thorn; balewsi&eth;. and wi&thorn; bitternesse. nis nan blisse so&thorn;es inan &thorn;ing &thorn;et is utewi&eth;. &thorn;et ne beo to bitter aboht. &thorn;et et huni &thorn;er in beo&thorn; liked of &thorn;ornes. me nis he fol <MILESTONE N="66a" UNIT="folio">chapmon &thorn;e bu&thorn; deore a wac &thorn;ing. and for forsake&thorn; a deorwur&thorn;e &thorn;ing. &thorn;et me beode&thorn; him for naut and bi-hat him &thorn;er take mede. forto nimen hit. Min ihesu liues louerd &thorn;u beodest us &thorn;in elming<NOTE PLACE="marg">? elnung.</NOTE>. al wi&thorn; uthen<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE> bune. and &thorn;er after bihastest<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE> us wi&thorn; &thorn;on &thorn;et we neomen hit heouenliche blissen. and we wende&thorn; us &thorn;er from. and bugge&thorn; worldles froure. wi&thorn; moni sori teone. and elne of monnes speche. a ihesu louerd &thorn;i gri&thorn;. hwi abbe ich eni<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. ein.</NOTE> licung in o&thorn;er &thorn;ing &thorn;ene in &thorn;e. hwi loue ich eni<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. ein.</NOTE> &thorn;ing boten &thorn;e one. hwi ne bi-hold ich hu &thorn;u strahstest &thorn;e for me on &thorn;e rode. hwine warpe ich me bitweone &thorn;e ilke earmes. swa swi&thorn;e wide to-spradde. he opene&thorn; swa &thorn;e moder hire earmes hire leoue child for to cluppen; &yogh;e so&thorn;es and tu deorwur&thorn;e louerd. gostliche to us and to [&thorn;ine] deorlinges wi&thorn; &thorn;e ilke spredunge gest. as &thorn;e moder to hire child. hua leof; hwa lif; hwa de&thorn; him &thorn;e bitweonen. hwa wule beo bi-cluppet; a ihesu &thorn;in eadmodnesse. and &thorn;in muchele milce. hwi nam ich in &thorn;in earmes. In &thorn;in earmes swa istrahte. and isprad on rode. and wene&eth; ei to beon bi-clupped bi-twene &thorn;ine blisfulle earmes. In 
<PB REF="00000251.tif" N="187"> heouene bute he warpe. er her bitweone &thorn;ine rewfulle earmes on &thorn;e rode. Nai so&thorn;es. nai. Ne wene hit neuer no mon. &thorn;urh his lahe clupping. me mot come heh to &thorn;e &thorn;er<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &THORN;et, or &THORN;us.</NOTE> &thorn;e wule bi-cluppe. &thorn;e &thorn;ear swilc. ase &thorn;u art &thorn;ear louerd of leome. he mot cluppe &thorn;e ear her swilc. ase &thorn;u makedest te her wreche. for us wreches. &thorn;et is to suggen hwa se euer wule habbe lot wi&thorn; &thorn;e of &thorn;i blisse; he mot deale wi&thorn; &thorn;e of &thorn;ine pine on eor&thorn;e. Nis na trewe ifere &thorn;e nule naut scottin in &thorn;e lure. ase in &thorn;e bi&yogh;ete; he mot scottin efne after his euene. [&thorn;]e wule beo &thorn;in fela&yogh;e luuiende louerd. he mot fole&yogh;i &thorn;ine steapes &thorn;urh sar. and &thorn;urh sorewe to to <MILESTONE N="66b" UNIT="folio">wunninge. of weole and of eche wunne. Ne wene na mon to stihen wi&eth; este to &thorn;e steorren. A swete ihesu hwi w[i&eth;] earmes of luue ne cluppe ich &thorn;e swa faste. &thorn;et na &thorn;ing ne &thorn;eonne ne ma&yogh;e breide min heorte. hwine cusse ich &thorn;e sweteliche ine gaste wi&eth; swote munegunge. of &thorn;ine god-deden. hwinis me bitter al &thorn;et mi flehs like&eth;. hwi nis me unwurh&thorn; elc wur&thorn;liche &thorn;ing. a&yogh;ein &thorn;e muchel delit of &thorn;i swetnesse. hwi ne fele ich &thorn;e in mi breostes swo swote ase &thorn;u art. hwi art tu me swo fremede. hwine con ich &thorn;e wo&yogh;e wi&thorn; swete luue. uor alle &thorn;inge swetest. alre &thorn;inge leoflucest. and luue wur&eth;est. wei. wei. &thorn;e bitternesse of mine sunnen attri is &thorn;e lettunge. mine sunnen beo&thorn; wal bi-tweone me and &thorn;e. Mine sunnen werne&thorn; me al &thorn;is swotnesse. Mine sunnen habbe&thorn; grimliche iwre&thorn;ed me. and iueed me towart te luueliche louerd. and &thorn;et is lute wunder. for swa ich am wi&thorn; hare hori fenliche ifuled. &thorn;et ich ne mai ne ne dear cume lufsum god in &thorn;in ehsih&thorn;e. A ihesu &thorn;in aore hwet de&thorn; &thorn;enne &thorn;i blod isched on &thorn;e rode. hwet de&thorn; &thorn;enne &thorn;e large broc of &thorn;i softe side. &thorn;e strunden &thorn;e striken adun of &thorn;ine deorwur&thorn;e fet. and of &thorn;ine edi honden. Nes hit for to waschen sunfulle saulen. Nes hit for to sauuin seke inne sunne. hwa is &thorn;enne unwaschen &thorn;e haue&thorn; &thorn;is halwende wet inwi&eth; his heorte. hwa derf beon un-sauuet &thorn;e haue&thorn; se mihti salue. ase ofte as he &thorn;er to haue&thorn; trewe bileue. min heoueneliche leche. &thorn;et makedest us of &thorn;i seolf se mihti medi|cine. iblesced beo &thorn;u euer as mi trust is &thorn;er to. hit beo mi lechunge hit beo mi bote. &yogh;ef min uuel is muchel. &thorn;e mihte &thorn;er of is more. as wis ase dieope<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>for</I> drope.</NOTE> of &thorn;i deorwur&thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. deor|&thorn;ur&thorn;e.</NOTE> blod. mahte 
<PB REF="00000253.tif" N="189"> waschen a-wai alle folkes ful&thorn;e. ase wis lifes louerd &thorn;e <MILESTONE N="67a" UNIT="folio">ilke fif wallen &thorn;et of &thorn;i blisfulle bodi sprungen. and strike dun strondes of blode wasche mine fif wittes of alle bodi sunnen. of al &thorn;et ich abbe mis-seien mid e&yogh;en. mid min eren iherd. mid mu&thorn; ispekin. o&thorn;er ismaht. and wi&eth; neose ismelled. wi&thorn; eini lim mis ifeled. and wi&eth; flehs isuneged. &thorn;ine wunden healen &thorn;e wunden of mi saule. &thorn;i dea&thorn; adeadi in me flehces licunge. and licomliche lustes. and do me liuien to &thorn;e. &thorn;er ich ma&yogh;e. seggen; wi&thorn; seinte pawel &thorn;e sei&thorn;. Ic liuie naut ic ac crist liue&eth; in me. &thorn;et is to seggen. Ic liuie ic ilif &thorn;et ic leuede. ah crist liue&thorn; in me &thorn;urh his wunende grace. &thorn;et acwike&eth; me wel wes ha iboren &thorn;o mai ihesu &thorn;is balde|liche segge to &thorn;e. &thorn;u &thorn;et ert eafter him alle helpleses help. and sunfulles hele &thorn;et to &thorn;e habbe&thorn; hope. helpe me englene quene. heoueneliche leafdi seinte marie moder and maiden deorwur&thorn; wimmon forto salui sunne ihesu crist bicom &thorn;i sone. for ure sake &thorn;u were maked maiden godes moder. Nere &thorn;u naut &thorn;et tu art edi ouer alle &yogh;ef sunfulle neren for &thorn;i a&yogh;en sunfulle to cleopien to &thorn;e baldeliche. for hwam &thorn;u hauest &thorn;in edinesse. and ti muchele heh-schipe. maiden moder. maiden and hwas moder. his hwas dohter &thorn;u art. his &thorn;at wrahte. and walt [al] &thorn;at ischapen is. his &thorn;et naue&thorn; nou&thorn;er ne biginnunge &thorn;et is euer ilic wi&thorn;-ute truch|unge. &thorn;et halt euer anon wi&thorn;-ute sturunge. O. muchele menske to beon moder of swuche sone. mid holscipe of maiden and habben him swa abandun. &thorn;et he wule &thorn;et al &thorn;ine wil ihwer beo ifor&thorn;ed. forto schawen us &thorn;is he strahte for&thorn; his riht earm ase [he] stod o rode. and bere&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="marg">? beie&thorn;.</NOTE> dun towart te his deorwur&thorn;e heaued ase &thorn;ah he saide. Moder &thorn;et &thorn;u wult<NOTE PLACE="foot">For remainder of text, see p. 203, ll. 10-21.</NOTE> . . . . .
</P>

