<DIV2 N="20" TYPE="homily"><PB REF="00000255.tif" N="191">
<HEAD>XX. ON GOD UREISUN OF URE LEFDI.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Cotton. MS. Nero A xiv.</NOTE></HEAD>
<MILESTONE UNIT="Cotton MS. Nero A xiv folio" N="120b">
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Cristes milde moder seynte marie.</L>
<L>Mines liues leome mi leoue lefdi.</L>
<L>To &thorn;e ich buwe and mine kneon ich beie.</L>
<L N="4">And al min heorte blod to &eth;e ich offrie.</L>
<L>&THORN;u ert mire soule liht. and mine heorte blisse.</L>
<L>Mi lif and mi tohope min heale mid iwisse.</L>
<L>Ich ouh wur&eth;ie &eth;e mid alle mine mihte.</L>
<L N="8">And singge &thorn;e lofsong bi daie and bi nihte.</L>
<L>Vor &thorn;u me hauest iholpen aueole kunne wise.</L>
<L>And ibrouht of helle in-to paradise.</L>
<L>Ich hit &thorn;onkie &eth;e mi leoue lefdi.</L>
<L N="12">And &thorn;onkie wulle &thorn;e hwule &eth;et ich liuie.</L>
<L>Alle cristene men owen don &eth;e wurschipe.</L>
<L>And singen &eth;e lofsong mid swu&eth;e muchele gledschipe.</L>
<L>Vor &eth;u ham hauest alesed of deoflene honde.</L>
<L N="16">And i-send mid blisse to englene londe.</L>
<L>Wel owe we &thorn;e luuien mi swete lefdi.<MILESTONE UNIT="Cotton MS. Nero A xiv folio" N="121a"></L>
<L>Wel owen we uor &thorn;ine luue ure heorte beien.</L>
<L>&THORN;u ert briht and blisful ouer alle wummen.</L>
<L N="20">And god &eth;u ert and gode leof ouer alle wepmen.</L>
<L>Alle meidene were wur&eth;e&eth; &thorn;e one.</L>
<L>Vor &thorn;u ert hore blostme biuoren godes trone.</L>
<L>Nis no wummon iboren &thorn;et &eth;e beo iliche.</L>
<L N="24">Ne non &thorn;er nis &thorn;in efning wi&eth;-inne heoueriche.</L>
<L>Heih is &thorn;i kinestol onuppe cherubine.</L>
<L>Biuoren &eth;ine leoue sune wi&eth;-innen seraphine.</L>
<L>Murie dreame&eth; engles biuoren &thorn;in onsene.
<PB REF="00000257.tif" N="193"></L>
<L N="28">Pleie&eth;. and sweie&eth;. and singe&eth;. bitweonen.</L>
<L>Swu&eth;e wel ham like&eth; biuoren &thorn;e to beonne.</L>
<L>Vor heo neuer ne beo&eth; sead &thorn;i ueir to iseonne.</L>
<L>&THORN;ine blisse ne mei nowiht understonden.</L>
<L N="32">Vor al is godes riche an under &thorn;ine honden.</L>
<L>Alle &thorn;ine ureondes &thorn;u makest riche kinges.</L>
<L>&THORN;u ham &yogh;iuest kinescrud beies and gold ringes.</L>
<L>&THORN;u &yogh;iuest eche reste ful of swete blisse.</L>
<L N="36">&THORN;er &eth;e neure dea&eth; ne com; ne herm ne sorinesse.</L>
<L>&THORN;er blowe&eth; inne blisse blostmen. hwite and reade.</L>
<L>&THORN;er ham neuer ne mei. snou. ne uorst iureden.</L>
<L>&THORN;er ne mei non ualuwen. uor &thorn;er is eche sumer.</L>
<L N="40">Ne non liuiinde &thorn;ing woc &thorn;er nis ne &yogh;eomer.</L>
<L>&THORN;er heo schulen resten &thorn;e her &eth;e do&eth; wurschipe.</L>
<L>&YOGH;if heo &yogh;eme&eth; hore lif cleane urom alle queadschipe.</L>
<L>&THORN;er ne schulen heo neuer karien ne swinken.</L>
<L N="44">Ne weopen ne murnen ne helle stenches stinken.</L>
<L>&THORN;er me schal ham steoren mid guldene chelle.</L>
<L>And schenchen ham eche lif mid englene wille.<MILESTONE UNIT="Cotton MS. Nero A xiv folio" N="121b"></L>
<L>Ne mei non heorte &thorn;enchen ne nowiht arechen.</L>
<L N="48">Ne no mu&eth; imelen ne no tunge tegen<NOTE PLACE="marg">? techen.</NOTE>.</L>
<L>Hu muchel god &eth;u &yogh;eirkest wi&eth;-inne paradise.</L>
<L>Ham &thorn;et swinke&eth; dei and niht i&eth;ine seruise.</L>
<L>Al &thorn;in hird is i-schrud mid hwite ciclatune.</L>
<L N="52">And alle heo beo&eth; ikruned mid guldene krune.</L>
<L>Heo beo&eth; so read so rose so hwit so &thorn;e lilie.</L>
<L>And euer more heo beo&eth; gled and singe&eth; &thorn;uruhut murie.</L>
<L>Mid brihte &yogh;imstones hore krune is al biset.</L>
<L N="56">And al heo do&eth; &thorn;et ham like&eth;. so &thorn;et no &thorn;ing ham ne let.</L>
<L>&THORN;i leoue sune is hore king and &thorn;u ert hore kwene.</L>
<L>Ne beo&eth; heo neuer i-dreaued mid winde ne mid reine.</L>
<L>Mid ham is euer more dei wi&eth;-ute nihte.</L>
<L N="60">Song wi&eth;-ute seoruwe and sib wi&eth;-ute uihte.</L>
<L>Mid ham is muruh&eth;e moniuold wi&eth;-ute teone and treie.</L>
<L>Gleobeames and gome inouh liues wil and eche pleie.</L>
<L>&THORN;ereuore leoue lefdi long hit &thorn;unche&eth; us wrecchen.
<PB REF="00000259.tif" N="195"></L>
<L N="64">Vort &thorn;u of &thorn;isse erme liue to &eth;e suluen us fecche.</L>
<L>We ne muwen neuer habben fulle gledschipe.</L>
<L>Er we to &thorn;e suluen kumen to &thorn;ine heie wurschipe.</L>
<L>Swete Godes moder softe meiden and wel icoren.</L>
<L N="68">&THORN;in iliche neuer nes ne neuermore ne wur&eth; iboren.</L>
<L>Moder &thorn;u ert and meiden cleane of alle laste.</L>
<L>&THORN;uruhtut hei and holi in englene reste.</L>
<L>Al englene were and alle holie &thorn;ing.</L>
<L N="72">Sigge&eth; and singe&eth; &thorn;et tu ert liues welsprung.</L>
<L>And heo sigge&eth; alle &thorn;et &eth;e ne wonte&eth; neuer ore.</L>
<L>Ne no mon &thorn;et &eth;e wur&eth;e&eth; ne mei neuer beon uorloren.</L>
<L>&THORN;u ert mire soule wi&eth;-ute leasunge.<MILESTONE UNIT="Cotton MS. Nero A xiv folio" N="122a"></L>
<L N="76">Efter &thorn;ine leoue sune; leouest alre &thorn;inge.</L>
<L>Al is &thorn;e heouene ful of &thorn;ine blisse.</L>
<L>And so is al &thorn;es middeleard of &thorn;ine mildheortnesse</L>
<L>So muchel is &thorn;i milce and &thorn;in edmodnesse.</L>
<L N="80">&THORN;et no mon &thorn;et &eth;e &yogh;eorne bit of helpe ne mei missen.</L>
<L>Ilch mon &thorn;et to &thorn;e bisih&eth; &thorn;u &yogh;iuest milce and ore.</L>
<L>&THORN;auh he &eth;e habbe swu&eth;e agult and i-dreaued sore.</L>
<L>&THORN;ereuore ich &eth;e bidde holi heouene kwene.</L>
<L N="84">&THORN;et tu &yogh;if &thorn;i wille is iher mine bene.</L>
<L>Ich &eth;e bidde lefdi uor &thorn;ere gretunge.</L>
<L>&THORN;et Gabriel &eth;e brouhte urom ure heouen kinge.</L>
<L>And ek ich &eth;e biseche uor ihesu cristes blode.</L>
<L N="88">&THORN;et for ure note was i-sched o&eth;ere rode.</L>
<L>Vor &eth;e muchele seoruwe &eth;et was o&eth;ine mode.</L>
<L>&THORN;o &thorn;u et &eth;e dea&eth;e him bi-uore stode.</L>
<L>&THORN;et tu me makie cleane wi&eth;-uten and eke wi&eth;-innen.</L>
<L N="92">So &thorn;et me ne schende none kunnes sunne.</L>
<L>&THORN;ene lo&eth;e deouel and alle kunnes dweoluh&eth;e.</L>
<L>Aulem urom me ueor awei mid hore fule ful&eth;e.</L>
<L>Mi leoue lif urom &thorn;ine luue ne schal me no &thorn;ing to-dealen.</L>
<L N="96">Vor o&eth;e is al ilong mi lif and eke min heale.</L>
<L>Vor &thorn;ine luue i swinke and sike wel ilome.</L>
<L>Vor &thorn;ine luue ich ham ibrouht in to &thorn;eoudome.</L>
<L>Vor &thorn;ine luue ich uorsoc al &thorn;et me leof was.
<PB REF="00000261.tif" N="197"></L>
<L N="100">And &yogh;ef &eth;e al mi suluen. looue lif i&thorn;ench &thorn;u &thorn;es.</L>
<L>&THORN;et ich &eth;e wre&eth;ede sume si&eth;e hit me reowe&eth; sore.</L>
<L>Vor cristes fif wunden &eth;u &yogh;if me milce and ore.</L>
<L>&YOGH;if &thorn;u milce nauest of me &thorn;et ich wot wel &yogh;eorne</L>
<L N="104">&THORN;et ine helle pine swelten ich schal and beornen.<MILESTONE UNIT="Cotton MS. Nero A xiv folio" N="122b"></L>
<L>Ful wel &thorn;u me iseie &thorn;auh &thorn;u stille were.</L>
<L>Hwar ich was and hwat i dude &thorn;auh &thorn;u me uorbere.</L>
<L>&YOGH;if &thorn;u heuedest wreche inumen of mine lu&eth;ernesse.</L>
<L N="108">Iwis ich heuede al uorloren paradises blisse.</L>
<L>&THORN;u hauest &yogh;et forboren me uor &thorn;ine godnesse.</L>
<L>And nu ich hopie habben fulle uor&yogh;iuenesse.</L>
<L>Ne wene ich neure uallen in-to helle pine.</L>
<L N="112">Hwon ich am to &eth;e ikumen and am &eth;in owune hine.</L>
<L>&THORN;in ich am and wule beon nu and euer more.</L>
<L>Vor o&eth;e is al mi lif ilong and o godes ore.</L>
<L>Mi leoue swete lefdi to &thorn;e me longe&eth; swu&eth;e.</L>
<L N="116">Bute ich habbe &thorn;ine help ne beo ich neuer bli&eth;e.</L>
<L>Ich &thorn;e bidde &thorn;et tu kume to mine uor&eth;-si&eth;e.</L>
<L>And nomeliche &thorn;eonne &thorn;ine luue ku&eth;e.</L>
<L>Auouh mine soule hwon ich of &thorn;isse liue uare.</L>
<L N="120">And i-schild me urom seoruwe and from eche dea&eth;es kare.</L>
<L>&YOGH;if &thorn;u wult &eth;et ich i&eth;eo gode &yogh;eme nim to me.</L>
<L>Vor wel ne wur&eth; me neuer bute hit beo &thorn;uruh &eth;e.</L>
<L>Mid swu&thorn;e lu&eth;ere lasten mi soule is &thorn;uruh bunden.</L>
<L N="124">Ne mei no &thorn;ing so wel so &thorn;u healen mine wunden.</L>
<L>To &thorn;e one is al mi trust efter &thorn;ine leoue sune.</L>
<L>Vor is holie nome of mine liue &yogh;if me lune.</L>
<L>Ne &thorn;ole &thorn;u &thorn;ene unwine &thorn;et he me arine.</L>
<L N="128">Ne &thorn;et he me drawe in-to helle pine.</L>
<L>Nim nu &yogh;eme to me so me best a beo &eth;e beo.</L>
<L>Vor &thorn;in is &thorn;e wurchipe &yogh;if ich wreeche wel i&thorn;eo.</L>
<L>&THORN;u ne uorsakest nenne mon uor his lu&eth;ernesse.</L>
<L N="132">&YOGH;if he is to bote &yogh;eruh and bit &thorn;e uor&yogh;iuenesse.</L>
<L>&THORN;u miht lihtliche &yogh;if &thorn;u wult al mi sor aleggen.<MILESTONE UNIT="Cotton MS. Nero A xiv folio" N="123a"></L>
<L>And muchele bet biseon to me &thorn;en ich kunne siggen.</L>
<L>&THORN;u miht for&yogh;elden lihtliche mine gretunge.
<PB REF="00000263.tif" N="199"></L>
<L N="136">Al mi swinc and mi sor and mine kneouwunge.</L>
<L>Ine me nis no&thorn;ing feier on to biseonne.</L>
<L>Ne no &thorn;ing &thorn;et beo wur&eth;e biuoren &thorn;e to beonne.</L>
<L>&THORN;ereuore ich &thorn;e bidde &thorn;et &thorn;u me wassche and schrude</L>
<L N="140">&THORN;uruh &thorn;ine muchele milce &thorn;et spert<NOTE PLACE="marg">? spret.</NOTE> so swu&eth;e wide.</L>
<L>Nis hit &eth;e no wur&eth;scipe &thorn;et &thorn;e deouel me to-drawe.</L>
<L>&yogh;if &thorn;u wult hit i&eth;auien iwis he wule &eth;urchut fawe.</L>
<L>Vor he nolde neuere &thorn;et &thorn;u hefedest wur&eth;schipe.</L>
<L N="144">Ne no mon &thorn;et &thorn;e wur&eth;e&eth; &thorn;et he hedde gledschipe.</L>
<L>&THORN;u hit wost ful &yogh;eorne &thorn;et &thorn;e deouel hate&eth; me.</L>
<L>And nomeliche &thorn;ereuore &thorn;et ich wur&eth;ie &thorn;e.</L>
<L>&THORN;ereuore ich &thorn;e bidde &thorn;et &thorn;u me wite and werie.</L>
<L N="148">&THORN;et &thorn;e deouel me ne drecche ne dweol&eth;e me ne derie.</L>
<L>So &thorn;u dest and so &thorn;u schalt uor &eth;ire mild-heortnesse.</L>
<L>&THORN;u schalt me a ueir dol of heoueriche blisse.</L>
<L>&YOGH;if ich habbe muchel ibroken muchel ich wulle beten.</L>
<L N="152">And do mine schrifte and &thorn;e ueire greten.</L>
<L>&THORN;e hwule &thorn;et ich habbe mi lif and mine heale.</L>
<L>Vrom &eth;ire seruise ne schal me no &thorn;ing deale.</L>
<L>Biuoren &thorn;ine uote ich wulle liggen and greden.</L>
<L N="156">Vort ich habbe uor&yogh;iuenesse of mine misdeden.</L>
<L>Mi lif is &thorn;in mi luue is &thorn;in mine heorte blod is &thorn;in.</L>
<L>And &yogh;if ich der seggen mi leoue leafdi &thorn;u ert min.</L>
<L>Alle wur&eth;schipe haue &thorn;u on heouene and ec on eor&eth;e.</L>
<L N="160">And alle gledschipe haue &thorn;u al so &thorn;u ert wur&eth;e.</L>
<L>Nu ich &thorn;e bi-seche ine cristes cherite.<MILESTONE UNIT="Cotton MS. Nero A xiv folio" N="123b"></L>
<L>&THORN;et &thorn;u &thorn;ine blescinge and &thorn;ine luue &yogh;iue me.</L>
<L>&YOGH;eme mine licame ine clenenesse.</L>
<L N="164">God almihti unne me vor his mild-heortnesse.</L>
<L>&THORN;et ich mote &thorn;e iseo in &eth;ire heie blisse.</L>
<L>And alle mine ureondmen &thorn;e bet beo nu to dai.</L>
<L>&THORN;et ich habbe i-sungen &thorn;e &eth;esne englissce lai.</L>
<L N="168">And nu ich &thorn;e bi-seche vor &eth;ire holinesse.</L>
<L>&THORN;et &thorn;u bringe &thorn;ene Munuch to &thorn;ire glednesse.</L>
<L>&THORN;et funde &eth;esne song bi &eth;e mi looue leafdi.</L>
<L>Cristes milde moder seinte marie. amen.
<PB REF="00000265.tif" N="201"></L>
</LG>
<P>beot him for nowt. and bihat him &thorn;er teken mede. for to nimen hit; Mi iesu liues louerd. &thorn;u beodest &thorn;in elning. al wi&eth;-ute bone. and &thorn;er efter bihotest us wi&eth; &thorn;en &eth;et we nimen hit. heouenliche blissen; and we wende&eth; us &thorn;er from. and bugge&eth; worldes froure. wi&eth; moni sor. and teone. and elne of monnes speche; a; iesu louerd. &thorn;i gri&eth;. hwi habbe ich eni <MILESTONE UNIT="Cotton MS. Nero A xiv folio" N="124b"> licunge. in o&eth;er &thorn;inge; &thorn;en i &thorn;e. hwi luuie ich ei &thorn;ing bute &thorn;e one; hwi ne bi-hold ich hu &thorn;u streihtest &thorn;e for me on &thorn;e rode; hwi ne worpe ich me bi-tweonen &thorn;eo ilke ermes so swi&eth;e wi&eth;e to-spredde. and i-opene&eth; so &thorn;e moder de&eth; hire ermes. hire leoue child for to bi|cluppen; &yogh;e so&eth;es. and &thorn;u deorewur&eth;e louerd gostliche to us and to &eth;ine deorelinges. wi&eth; &thorn;e ilke spredunge &yogh;eiest. ase &thorn;e moder to hire childe. hwo leof; hwo lif; hwo de&eth; him her bitweonen; hwoa wule beon bi-clupped; a iesu &thorn;in edmodnesse. and &thorn;i muchele milce. hwi nam ich i&thorn;in ermes so istreihte. and ispred on rode; and wene&eth; ei to beon bi-clupped bitweonen &thorn;ine blisfulle ermes in heouene. bute he worpe er him her; bi-tweon|en &thorn;ine rew&eth;ful ermes o&eth;e rode; Nai so&eth;es nai; ne wene hit neuer nomon. &thorn;uurh &thorn;is lowe cluppinge. me mot come to &thorn;e heie; &thorn;et wule bi-cluppen &thorn;e &thorn;er swuch; ase &thorn;u ert &thorn;er louerd of leoue. he mot cluppen &thorn;e er her; swuch ase &thorn;u makedest &thorn;e her. wrecche; for us wrecches. &eth;et is to seggen. hwoa so euer wule habben lot wi&eth; &thorn;e of &thorn;ine blisse; he mot delen wi&eth; &thorn;e; of &thorn;ine pine on eor&eth;e. nis he nout treowe ifere &thorn;et nule nout scotten i&thorn;e lure; ase i&thorn;e bi-&yogh;ete. he mot scotten efne efter his euene. &thorn;et wule beon &thorn;i felawe; liuiinde louerd. <MILESTONE UNIT="Cotton MS. Nero A xiv folio" N="125a">he mot folewen &thorn;ine steopes. &thorn;uruh sor. and &thorn;uruh seoruwe. to &eth;e wununge of weole; and of eche wunne. Ne wene nomon to stihen wi&eth; este to &thorn;e steorren. A swete iesu. hwi mid ermes of luue ne cluppe ich &thorn;e so feste. &thorn;et no &thorn;ing &thorn;eonne ne muwe breiden mine heorte; hwi ne cusse ich &thorn;e sweteliche ine goste. wi&eth; swete munegunge of &thorn;ine goddeden; hwi nis me bitter. al &thorn;et mi flesch like&eth;. hwi nis me unwur&eth; euerich wordlich &thorn;ing a-&yogh;ein &thorn;e muchele delit of &thorn;ine swetnesse; hwi ne iuele ich &thorn;e imine breoste so swete ase &thorn;u ert; hwi ertu me so freomede; hwi ne con ich wowen &thorn;e. wi&eth; swete luue wordes alre &thorn;inge swetest. and alre &thorn;inge leoflu|to 
<PB REF="00000267.tif" N="203"> &thorn;e baldeliche; for hwam &thorn;u hauest &thorn;in eadinesse. and &thorn;ine muchele heihschipe. Meiden. and moder. Meiden [and] hwas moder [his hwas] dohter &thorn;u ert his &thorn;et wrohte and welt. al &thorn;et ischeapen is. his &thorn;et naue&eth; nou&eth;er ende; ne biginnunge. &thorn;et is euer i-liche. wi&eth;-ute sturiunge o&thorn;e muchele menske to boen<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> moder of swich sune wi&eth; iholschipe of meiden. and habben him so abaundune. &eth;et he wule &eth;et &thorn;in wille oueral beo i-uor&eth;ed. for to scheawen us &thorn;is; he strecche&eth; &thorn;ene ritht<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> erm uor&eth;. ase he stont orode. and beie&eth; adun toward &thorn;e. his deorewur&eth;e heaued. ase &thorn;auh he seide. Moder al &thorn;et &thorn;u wult; al ich wulle. aswete leafdi. hwi leafdi hwi; nabe ich euer bi-foren mine heorte eihen. &thorn;eo ilke &thorn;reo stondunges. &thorn;i sune was ituht on rode. &thorn;urh driuen fet and honden. wi&eth; dulte neiles. blodi his side. and &thorn;i stondunge leafdi. and sein iohanes ewangelistes weopinde otwo half wi&eth; sorhfule sikes; hwi ne bi-hold ich &thorn;is euer in mine heorte. and &thorn;enche &eth;et hit was for me. and for o&eth;re sunfule <MILESTONE UNIT="Cotton MS. Nero A xiv folio" N="126b">to aredden of helle. and forto &yogh;iuen us heoueriche blisse; &thorn;is &thorn;oht wolde siker|liche ontenden so so&eth; luue on me. Nere &thorn;e heorte so cold. &thorn;et ne schulde neuer sunne habben for&eth;er in-&yogh;ong. &thorn;er &thorn;is brune were. a iesu hwuder schal ich fleon hwon &thorn;e deouel hunte&eth; efter me bute to &thorn;ine rode;
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="22" TYPE="homily"><PB REF="00000269.tif" N="205">
<HEAD>XXII. [ON LOFSONG OF URE LEFDI.]</HEAD>
<P>Swete leafdi seinte marie meiden ouer alle meidnes. &thorn;et bere &eth;et blisfule bern. &thorn;et aredde<NOTE PLACE="marg">? arerdde.</NOTE> al moncun up. &thorn;et was adun a-fallen. &eth;et<NOTE PLACE="marg">Originally &eth;er.</NOTE> &thorn;uru&eth; adames sunne. and &eth;et<NOTE PLACE="marg">Originally &eth;er.</NOTE> &thorn;uruh his holi pas|siun werp &thorn;ene deouel adun. and heriede helle. ich on sori sunfule &thorn;ing; bidde &thorn;in ore. &eth;et tu beo mi motild a&yogh;eines mine soule fon. &thorn;et heo hire ne muwen bitellen. auh were me. and help me milzfule meiden; in alle mine neoden. Mine widerwines habbe&eth; biset me on euche half abuten; and seche&eth; mine soule dea&eth;. lu&eth;re men and deoflen. heo habbe&eth; monie wunden on me ifestned; &thorn;et acwelle&eth; mine soule. bute &thorn;u beo mi leche. ich habbe ofte ibuwen to alle mine &thorn;reo i-fon. to &thorn;e feond. and to &thorn;e world. and to mine flesches sunne. ich icnowe me gulti. and creie &thorn;e leafdi merci. for ich habbe imaked &yogh;etes of alle mine fif wittes. to sun|fule un&thorn;eawes. mis i-loked. Mis ihercned. Mis ifeled. mis ispeken. iloued swote smelles. prude and wilnunge of pris; me habbe&eth; sore iwunded. <MILESTONE UNIT="Cotton MS. Nero A xiv folio" N="127a">ase wre&eth;&eth;e. and onde. lesunge. missware. vuele i-holden treou&eth;e. cursunge. bac bitunge. and fikelunge; summe tide. ich habbe iheued of o&eth;er monnes mid woh. and mid unriht i&yogh;euen mis. and inumen mis. and mis etholden ofte. tovel; spac. and slow; to Godd. &yogh;emeleas; and unlusti. sumehwile to pleiful; to drupi o&eth;er hwiles. ich habbe i-suneged ine mete. and ine drunche bo&eth;e. and mid flesches ful&eth;e ifuled me. &thorn;us ich am lod|liche i-hurt ine licame. and ine soule; wi&eth; alle cunnes sunnen. for &thorn;auh &thorn;et werc nere i &thorn;e bodie; &thorn;e wil was in &thorn;e heorte. al &thorn;is ich i-cnoulechie &thorn;e swete leafdi seinte marie. heiest alre hale|wen. Nim mot for me and were me. for ich am pine wur&eth;e. bi|sech for me &thorn;ine seli sune; Milce. and merci. and ore. for nout ne mai he werne &thorn;e; maiden &thorn;e hine bere of alle &thorn;ine bisocnen. Ich bide &thorn;e and biseche &thorn;e and halsi &yogh;if me howe&eth; hit; bi his flech founge of &thorn;ine eadie bodie. bi his iborenesse. bi his eadi 
<PB REF="00000271.tif" N="207"> festunge i&thorn;e wildernesse. bi &thorn;e herde hurtes and &thorn;e unwur&eth;e wowes &eth;et he for us sunfule willeliche &thorn;olede. bi his dea&eth;fule grure. and bi his blodie swote. bi his eadi beoden in hulles him one. bi his nimunge. and bindunge. bi his ledunge for&eth;. bi al &thorn;et me him demde. bi his clo&eth;es wrixlunge. Nu red. nu hwit. him on hokerunge. bi his scornunge. and bi his spotlunge. and bufet|tunge. <MILESTONE UNIT="Cotton MS. Nero A xiv folio" N="127b">and his heliunge. bi &thorn;e &thorn;ornene crununge. bi &eth;e kine&yogh;erde of rode.<NOTE PLACE="marg">=rede.</NOTE> him of scornunge. bi his owune rode. on his softe schul|dres. so herde druggunge. bi &thorn;e dulte neiles. bi &thorn;e sore wunden; bi &thorn;e holie rode. bi his side openunge. bi his blodi Rune &thorn;et ron inne monie studen. In umbe keoruunge. in his blod swetunge<NOTE PLACE="marg">A word erased.</NOTE>. in his pine &thorn;ornene crununge. erest in his one hond and seo&eth;&eth;en in his o&eth;er. olast in his side &thorn;urlunge wi&eth;-ute sore wunde. &YOGH;et ase halewen wene&eth;. &thorn;et to&eth;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">? so&eth;e.</NOTE> blod rune. was in his ereste. nimunge in &thorn;e feste bindunge. &thorn;et tet blod wrong ut et his eadie neiles. ich halsi &thorn;e &thorn;et &eth;u bi-seche him bi his schome. bi his sor. bi his dea&eth; on rode. bi al &thorn;et he seide wrohte and &thorn;olede in eor&eth;e. bi &thorn;e holi sacrement of his flech and of his blod &thorn;et &eth;e preost sacre&eth;. &thorn;urh &thorn;e grace of fuluht. &thorn;urh alle &thorn;e o&eth;re sacre|menz. &thorn;et holi chirche foluwe&eth; and use&eth;. &thorn;urh alle ich bi-seche &thorn;e godes deore-wur&eth;e moder &thorn;et heore mihte helpe me. and hore strenc&eth;e go for&eth;. &thorn;er min offringe wonte&eth;. for min bileue is &thorn;et ich schal &thorn;uruh ham beon iboreuwen. iesu &thorn;i sune and Godes sune. &yogh;if us al him suluen and al is ure &thorn;et he spec and wrohte and &thorn;olede in or&eth;e. his pine on rode and his dea&eth; acwellen Mine sunnen. and his ariste arere me in lif holinesse. and his <MILESTONE UNIT="Cotton MS. Nero A xiv folio" N="128a">up ariste do me stepen uwward in heie and holi &thorn;eawes. from heih and to herre euer &eth;et ich iseo in syon &thorn;e heie tur of heouene; &thorn;ene louerd of leome. &thorn;et te engles euer biholde&eth;. and euer so lengrre so heo &yogh;irne&eth; hit more. for i&thorn;et seli song is al &thorn;et me seche&eth;. leafdi &thorn;urh &thorn;in erndinge tu&eth;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">? cu&eth;e.</NOTE> me mine bone to &thorn;ine eadi sune amen.
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="23" TYPE="homily"><PB REF="00000273.tif" N="209">
<HEAD>XXIII. [ON LOFSONG OF URE LOUERDE.]</HEAD>
<DIV3 TYPE="hymn">
<P>Iesu crist godes sune so&eth; godd and so&eth; mon of &thorn;e eadie meiden iboren maria. &thorn;et is meiden and bute make moder. ich of alle sunfulle am on mest ifuled of sunne ase ich drede. ich bidde and bi-seche &thorn;e wi&eth; inwarde heorte &thorn;urh &thorn;in akennednesse ine meidenes licame of &thorn;e holi Goste. and &thorn;uruh &thorn;in iborenesse wi&eth; uten bruche of hire bodie &thorn;uruh al &thorn;et &eth;u tawhtest. and &thorn;oledest for sunfule in eor&eth;e. &thorn;urh &thorn;ine vif wunden. and &thorn;e eadie flod &thorn;et of ham fledde. &thorn;urh &eth;e irene neiles and &thorn;e &thorn;ornene crune. and &thorn;urh &thorn;e pinen and &thorn;e schomen and &thorn;i deorewur&eth;e dea&eth; o&eth;e rode and &thorn;uruh &eth;e ilke rode i-halewed of &thorn;ine deorewur&eth;e limen. &eth;et &thorn;u on hire mildeliche streihtest. and &thorn;ine moderes ream and sein i[o]hanes soruwe &thorn;o &thorn;u somnedest ham ase sune and moder. uor rew&eth;e of &thorn;ine pinen and &thorn;urch &thorn;ine blisfule ariste &thorn;e &thorn;ridde dai of dea&eth;e. and &thorn;urh &thorn;ine wur&eth;ful astiunge into heouene. &thorn;urh &eth;e grace and &thorn;e &yogh;eoue of &thorn;e holi goste. &thorn;et &thorn;u on hwite sune dai sendest &thorn;ine deorewur&eth;e <MILESTONE UNIT="Cotton MS. Nero A xiv folio" N="128b">deciples. and &yogh;ettedest to &thorn;eo &thorn;et rith luuie&eth; &thorn;e and leued. and &thorn;urh &thorn;ine eisfule cume a domesdai to demen bo&eth;e cwike and deade. and &thorn;urh &thorn;ine eadi flesche and &thorn;ine iblescede blode i-sacred o&eth;e weouede. &thorn;urh &thorn;e mihte of fuluht. &thorn;urh alle &thorn;e o&eth;re sacremens. &thorn;et holi chirche ileue&eth;. &thorn;urh &thorn;ine muchele milce and merci &thorn;et is more &thorn;en al &thorn;et is inempned wi&eth;-ute &thorn;e grace of &thorn;e oli goste. &thorn;et is efne wi&eth; &thorn;e and wi&eth; &thorn;in eadi feder. Godd of alle godd ful. haue merci of me and iher mine bonen. &thorn;uruh &thorn;e selie bonen of &thorn;ine milde moder and seint iohannes ewangeliste. and alle &thorn;ine halewen. for-&yogh;if me mine sunnen &thorn;et ateliche beo&eth; and grisliche i &thorn;ine eih sih&eth;e. louerd ich i-seo ham wi&eth; muchel ugge of &thorn;in eie. ne bi-hold &thorn;u ham nout leste &thorn;u wreoke ham on 
<PB REF="00000275.tif" N="211"> me iwodschipe of &thorn;ine wre&eth;&eth;e. louerd &thorn;in apostel sei&eth; &thorn;us. &YOGH;if we ne fordemden us seoluen ne schulde we nout beon elles hwar for-demed. milde merciable godd ich deme to &thorn;e; efter &thorn;ine milce &thorn;et is [mo]re &thorn;en al min [uu]el is; ase wis [as]e a drope of &thorn;ine deorewur&eth;e blode &thorn;et tu o rode scheddest were i-nouh to weaschen alle folkes ful&eth;e. &thorn;eo sterke stremes and &thorn;et flod &thorn;et fleaw of &thorn;ine wunden. moncun uor to helen; clense and waschs mine sunfule soule &thorn;urh &thorn;ine fif wunden iopened o rode. wi&eth; neiles uor-driuene and seoruhfulliche fordutte. hel me uorwunded <MILESTONE UNIT="Cotton MS. Nero A xiv folio" N="129a">&thorn;urh mine fif wittes wi&eth; deadliche sunnen. and opene ham heouenliche king touward heouenliche &thorn;inges. and turn to &thorn;e worlde &thorn;i wur&eth;fule rode &thorn;et &thorn;u spreddest &thorn;e on. beo mi scheld and mi warant on euche half; a&yogh;ein &thorn;es feondes flon &thorn;et he scheot to me on euche halue &thorn;e swike. &thorn;i passiun acwenche &thorn;e passiun of sunnen &thorn;et wunie&eth; wi&eth; inne me. &thorn;ine pinen buruwen me from &thorn;e pinen of helle. and &thorn;i dereowur&eth;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE> dea&eth; from &thorn;ene dea&eth; &eth;et neuer ne deie&eth;. &thorn;et &eth;i dea&eth; a-deadie &thorn;e dea&eth;liche lustes of mine licame. and te lawen of mine limen beo &eth;e world [dead] to me. and me to &thorn;e worlde. &thorn;urh &thorn;ine ariste louerd to liue; bute dea&eth;e. of soule dea&eth;e arer me. and &yogh;if me lif in &eth;e. &thorn;et ich i&thorn;isse worlde ne luuie nout bute &thorn;e liuinde louerd. and hwat so god is uor &thorn;e. &thorn;et ich to &thorn;e world beo dead. and euer liuie<NOTE PLACE="marg">A stroke too many in MS.</NOTE> to &thorn;e. &thorn;et ich muwe siggen wi&eth; seinte powel &thorn;et sei&eth;. ich liuie nout ich; auh crist liue&eth; in me. louerd &thorn;i merci ase ich ham heie iclumben wi&eth; &thorn;is ilke bone. &thorn;et ligge so lowe. and uor eor&eth;liche luren so muche mislicunge habbe in mine heorte. Milde godd &thorn;i milce. for her&thorn;urh ich deie &thorn;et spec er of swuche &thorn;inge. and dea&eth;liche sunegi. heie helinde godd help me. and hel herof mine heorte. leoue louerd iesu crist loke toward me ase ich ligge lowe. and mone to &eth;e of &thorn;inge &eth;et me derue&eth; mest nu&eth;e efter mine sunnen. heie helinde <MILESTONE UNIT="Cotton MS. Nero A xiv folio" N="129b">beih &thorn;e to me. and buh to mine bonen. Nabbich now&eth;er in me wisdom ne wurschipe and am redleas nab ich [h]waremide le[de]n mi lif i &thorn;is[se] worlde and am helples. ich habbe on monie wise mislicunge of &thorn;onke and heorte sec of sorwe. and nabbe hwoa me froure. Deorewur&eth;e drihten ase 
<PB REF="00000277.tif" N="213"> &thorn;u ert redlease red. red me &thorn;et am helples and redles. hu ich schule leden me and liuien on eor&eth;e wi&eth; meidhod and ine clennesse of soule. and of bodie bo&eth;e. ase &thorn;u ert neodfulles help bi-hold heie louerd hu monnes help truke&eth; me. &thorn;in help beo me &thorn;e &yogh;arewere forto &thorn;e one ich chulle trusten and hopien euer buten ende. hefdich &yogh;are so idon me stode betere &thorn;en me de&eth; ich hit wot to so&eth;e. uor &thorn;eo hwile &eth;et ich truste uppo mon &thorn;u seidest. hold &thorn;e to ham and lettest me al iwurden wi&eth; &thorn;eo &thorn;et ich truste uppon. and heo beo&eth; me itrukede heouenlich louerd. ich i-leue for mine selh&eth;e ich herie &thorn;e and &thorn;onke. &thorn;u ham hauest bi-nume me. uor &thorn;u iseihe. &thorn;et te hope of ham bi|swoc me and wult &thorn;et ich hopie and truste to &thorn;e one. for to schewen hu &thorn;is hope to &thorn;in ones help schal gon me betere ut. &thorn;en dude er &thorn;e o&eth;res. &thorn;u hauest binume me fulst of monne; uor &thorn;u wult &thorn;in &yogh;eouen me. Iblesced beo &thorn;et &thorn;us went lure to bi&yogh;eate. sikerliche al mi woa on eor&eth;e schal turnen me to ioie. &yogh;if ich Godd luuie mid treowe bileaue. louerd <MILESTONE UNIT="Cotton MS. Nero A xiv folio" N="130a">ich ileue hit and luuie and wulle luuien &thorn;e more louerd &thorn;urh &thorn;is wondred &thorn;en er in al mine weole. uor ich wot to so&eth;e hit wolde habben al bi-swike me. &YOGH;if &thorn;e help nere louerd of &thorn;ine grace. louerd ich bi-seche &eth;e wi&eth; inwarde heorte ne &yogh;if &thorn;u me nou&eth;er to muchel ne to lutel. uor &thorn;urh ei&eth;er moni mon sunegge&eth; i-lome. auh leue me &eth;et ich mote so&eth;liche seggen wi&eth; &eth;e meiden &thorn;et of &thorn;e sei&eth; &thorn;eors<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE> wordes. Mi leofmonnes luft erm halt up min heaued heo sei&eth;. and his riht erm schal biclupen me abuten. let me beo &thorn;i leouemon and siggen ase heo sei&eth;. leof wi&eth; &thorn;i luft erm. &thorn;et is. wi&eth; &thorn;ine worldliche &yogh;eouen hold up min heawed &eth;et ich &thorn;urh to muche wone ne falle i ful&eth;e of sunne. and leof wi&eth; &thorn;in riht erm. &thorn;et is in heuene wi&eth; endelease blissen bi-clupe me abuten. al schal beon &thorn;et ich wulle &thorn;eonne for&eth; swete milde louerd bidde o&eth;er wilni ich bidde &eth;e &eth;et ich mote under-uon in obedience bo&eth;e wone and weole &thorn;e ine cwemnesse. &thorn;auh ich nabbe nout one al &eth;et me biheouede ne me ne cume nowt ase sone ase ich wolde. ich ne mishopie &thorn;e nout auh am al siker of &eth;et &thorn;u wult binime me &eth;et me wolde herm don. and &yogh;ife me &thorn;et me is biheue swete milzfule louerd. auh &thorn;u &thorn;et alle &thorn;ing 
<PB REF="00000279.tif" N="215"> isihst &eth;et abidest his time. Nu ich habbe uorloren al moncunne froure ich wot <MILESTONE UNIT="Cotton MS. Nero A xiv folio" N="130b">&thorn;et &thorn;u wult senden me &thorn;ene holi gost to elnen me. and reden me and helpen me and froure me betere &thorn;en alle &thorn;eo ilke muhten &thorn;et ich on truste. uor &thorn;us sei&eth; &thorn;e salmwruhte daui&eth; i&thorn;e sawter. &thorn;e world haue&eth; for-let me. and godd hawe&eth; underfo me. eft elles hwar he sei&eth;. haue &thorn;i licung ine godd and he wule &yogh;iuen &thorn;e bonen of &thorn;ine heorte. vnwrih him &thorn;ene wei &thorn;et is &thorn;i wilnunge. and he wule hit for&eth;en. &thorn;u wost hwat ich wilni al weldinde Godd. auh of &thorn;et ase of helles hwat; iwur&eth;e &thorn;i wille euer. uor &thorn;u wult inouhre&eth;e don betere bi me &thorn;en is &thorn;et ich wilni. and ich buhsumliche bi-seche &thorn;e louerd &thorn;uruh non of|seruunge to &eth;e. auh &thorn;urh &thorn;is hope. and i &thorn;is trust to &thorn;ine muchele milce. &eth;et &thorn;u beo mi red nu. Min help and min elne. auh &thorn;e ich chulle luuien nu. uor ham &thorn;et ich luuede er and truste to and hopede. uor nu ich understonde hu so&eth; hit is &eth;et seint austin sei&eth; in his boc. uniseli is &eth;et is wi&eth; luue to eni eor&eth;lich &thorn;ing iteied. uor euer bi&eth; &eth;et swete; abouht mid twofold of bittre. auh me ne hit under&yogh;it nout er &thorn;en me hit leose. and to lure hit bi-kume&eth; of hwuche half so hit falle&eth;; er me lest wene.</P>
<P>Swete softe iesu iseli beo&eth; &eth;et &thorn;e luuie&eth; and &thorn;ine siker swet|nesse. &thorn;et no mon ne mai leosen bute he &thorn;e treulac of &thorn;ine luue lete auh wi&eth;-uten &thorn;ine &yogh;eoue ne mai &thorn;e non <MILESTONE UNIT="Cotton MS. Nero A xiv folio" N="131a">luuien. wi&eth; &thorn;e lai louerd of &thorn;e holigost. &thorn;et is &thorn;i feder luue and &thorn;in. tend mine heorte and uorbern al &thorn;at is baluful. &thorn;er inne and fed hit so for&eth;ward. &thorn;et hit ontende me euere i&thorn;ine bileaue and in &thorn;ine luue. so lengre so more. Mi luue and mi red al min help and mi froure fulst me euer to gode and cher me from sunne. and &yogh;if me wil and mihte and wit to leten euch uuel and wel uorto wurchen. deorwur&eth;e drithen &thorn;u nowest none mon nowitht &thorn;urh his of-seruunge auh dest us al &thorn;et &thorn;u dest &thorn;urh &thorn;ine swete grace al unofserued cui&eth; in me hwat is milce and &thorn;et grace is grace nout hure werkes auh do so bi me. &thorn;et mine fon grennen and gode gladien and blescien &thorn;ine nome. and herien buten hende. hwat mote ich milzfule louerd to &thorn;e 
<PB REF="00000281.tif" N="217"> &thorn;et alle &thorn;ing meiht. and const. and wult wel don. and wult al &thorn;et god is. al &thorn;et god is. al &thorn;et me euer is neod. ich biseche &thorn;e godd of alle godd ful wi&eth; &thorn;eos &thorn;reo wordes. ase &thorn;u meiht. and const. and wult. Milzfule louerd haue merci of me and of alle cristene men. amen.</P>
