<DIV2 N="24" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XXIV. [DE INITIO CREATURE.<MILESTONE UNIT="Cott. Vesp. A. 22. folio" N="54"><NOTE PLACE="foot">Cott. Vesp. A. 22.</NOTE>]</HEAD>
<P>Vre hlaford almihti&yogh; god wile and &uacute;s h&oacute;t. &thorn;at we h&iacute;ne lufie. and &oacute;f him sm&aacute;&yogh;e and spece. naht him t&oacute; m&eacute;de ac h&uacute;s to freme and to fult&uacute;me. f&oacute;r. him se&iacute;&yogh;c alle hisc&eacute;fte. <I>Bonorum meorum non [in]-diges.</I> hlaford to mine g&oacute;de ne ben&iacute;ede&eth; &thorn;e. Ac alswo sanctus augustinus cwe&eth;. Gif non m&aacute;n ne &thorn;oht &oacute;f G&oacute;de. non ne spece of him. Gif non &oacute;f him ne spece non h&iacute;ne ne lufede. Gif non h&iacute;ne ne lufede. non to him ne c&oacute;me. ne delende n&eacute;re &oacute;f his e&aacute;din&eacute;sse. n&oacute;f h&iacute;s merh&eth;e. Hit is wel swete of him t&oacute; sp&eacute;cene. &thorn;enche &yogh;&iacute;e &aelig;lc word of him swete. al sw&aacute; &aacute;n huni t&iacute;ar felle upe &yogh;&iacute;ure h&iacute;erte. H&eacute;o is hefone liht. and eor&eth;e briht|nesse. loftes leom. and all hiscefte &yogh;&iacute;mston. anglene blisse. and manc&eacute;nne hiht and hope. richtwisen strenhc&thorn;e. and n&iacute;edfulle fr&oacute;uer. Heo his &aelig;lra &thorn;&iacute;nga angin. and hordfruma and &aelig;nde. he his &oacute;rd f&oacute;r he wes efre. he is &aelig;nde buton &aelig;lcere &yogh;iendun&yogh;e. 
<PB REF="00000283.tif" N="219"> heo is alra kingene king. and alra hlaforden hlaford. he h&aacute;lt mid his mihte hefene and eor&eth;e. and alle &yogh;escefte buton &yogh;e|swince. Ne m&eacute;&yogh; nan iscefte fulfremedlice sme&aacute;&yogh;an ne under|stonden &eacute;mbe god. heo &yogh;escop &yogh;esceafte &thorn;a&eth;a he w&oacute;lde. &thorn;urh h&iacute;s wisdom (se sune) heo &yogh;eworhte alle &thorn;ing. and &thorn;urh his wille (ali gast.) he hi alle &yogh;eliffeste. &thorn;eos &thorn;r&iacute;mnis &iacute;s an g&oacute;d. &thorn;at is s&eacute; fader. and his wisdom. of him selfe efre acenned. and hare be&iacute;re wille &thorn;at is s&eacute; hali gast. he g&eacute;&eth; of &thorn;e fader and of &thorn;e sune &yogh;elice. He &yogh;esc&oacute;p tyen engle werod. (o&eth;er h&aacute;d.) o&eth;er hapes. &thorn;at beo&eth;. angeli (b&oacute;den.) archangeli. (hahboden.) Troni. (&thorn;rimsetles.) Domina|tiones. hlafordscipe. Principatus alderscipen. Potestates. an|wealda gastes. Uirtutes. mihti gastes. Cherubim. &yogh;efildnesse of yw&iacute;tte. Seraphim birninde o&eth;er anhelend. for wan hi beo&eth; &thorn;uss icw&eacute;&eth;e me scel sigge, an o&eth;re stowe. Her beo&eth; n&iacute;&yogh;en anglen hapes. [o&eth;er had.] o&eth;er werod. Hi nabbe&eth; nenne lichama. ac hi b&aelig;&eth; alle gastes. swi&eth;e strange and mihti an mucele feirnesse isceapen to lofe and to wurhminte hare sceoppinde. &thorn;at teon&eth;e werod abrea&eth;. and awende &oacute;n yfele o&eth;er al swa fele &thorn;e me mihte &thorn;at tio&eth;e hape fulfellen. G&oacute;d &yogh;esceop alle gode. and l&eacute;t hi hi habben &aacute;&yogh;en ch&iacute;re. to ch&iacute;esen &yogh;&iacute;ef [h]y wolden hare sceappinde lufie. o&eth;er hine ferleten. &THORN;a wes &thorn;es tyendes hapes alder swi&thorn;e feir isceapen. swa &thorn;at heo was &yogh;ehoten leoht berinde. &THORN;a be-gan h&eacute; to modienne fer &thorn;ere feirnesse. &thorn;e h&eacute;o hafde. and cwe&eth; an his h&eacute;rto. &thorn;at he wolde and ea&eth;e mihte bien his sceoppende &yogh;elic. and sitte &aacute;n nor&eth;dele hefene riches. and habbe anwealda and riche an&yogh;en godelmichti &thorn;a yfesten[d]e [he] &thorn;isne red. wi&eth; &thorn;an hape &thorn;e [he] bewiste. and hi alle to rede gebu&yogh;on. &THORN;a &thorn;e li<NOTE PLACE="marg">? hi.</NOTE> alle hafeden &thorn;isne r&eacute;d betwuxe ham &yogh;efestnod. &thorn;a be-com godes grama ofer ham alle. and hi alle wur&eth;on <MILESTONE UNIT="Cott. Vesp. A. 22. folio" N="54b">awende of &thorn;an f&eacute;&yogh;re h&iacute;we &thorn;e hi an&yogh;escapen were to lo&eth;lice de&oacute;flen. and swi&eth;e richtlice ham sw&aacute; b&eacute;lamp. &THORN;&aacute;&eth;e hi wolde mid modinesse be&oacute;n betere &thorn;onne he &yogh;esceapen w&eacute;re. and cwe&eth; h&aacute;re alder &thorn;at he mihte be&oacute;n &thorn;am &aelig;lmihti g&oacute;d &yogh;elic. &thorn;a war&eth; he and halle his if&eacute;ren forcu&eth;ran and wursan &thorn;anne &aelig;n&iacute;g o&eth;er &yogh;esceafte. And &thorn;a wile &thorn;e he sm&eacute;ade hu he mihte delen r&iacute;ce wi&eth; g&oacute;d. &thorn;a wile &yogh;earcode se almihti sceappende him and his iferen helle wite. and hi alle adrefde of heofan r&iacute;ces 
