<P>[H]it &yogh;elamp &thorn;at an rice king wes. strang and mihti. his land g&eacute;lest wide and side. his folc was swi&eth;e &aelig;rfe&eth;-telle. his under-&thorn;&eacute;oden &yogh;&eacute;w&eacute;r on his cyne r&iacute;ce wuneden. &THORN;a be-fel hit swa &thorn;at him a &thorn;ance bef&eacute;ll to under&yogh;e&iacute;te w&aacute; an alle his cyne rice him were frend o&eth;er fend. hold o&eth;er f&aacute;. and he nam him t&oacute; rede &thorn;at heom wolde &yogh;earceon an&aelig; grate la&eth;ienge. and &thorn;ider &yogh;eclep&iacute;en all his under&thorn;e&oacute;d. &thorn;at hi bi &eacute;ne f&eacute;ce to his curt [berie] come sceolde and sette &aelig;nne d&eacute;&yogh;ie. &thorn;at hi alle be &thorn;e l&aacute;tst to &thorn;a de&yogh;ie. &thorn;er were. Ac &thorn;is &yogh;esceod he hadde is&eacute;tt bi-tweone frend and fend. &thorn;at &thorn;an hi come mistlice to ber&iacute;e. &yogh;ef he frend w&eacute;re. me hine sceolde <ABBR>derewrlice</ABBR> for&eth; clepien. and do hine wasse. and &yogh;&iacute;efe him h&iacute;s formemete. &thorn;at him to lang ne &thorn;uhte to abiden of fe<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>read</I> o&eth; se.</NOTE> laford to &thorn;e none inn come. Gief he fend w&eacute;re. me sceolden &aacute;non eter<NOTE PLACE="marg">= et &thorn;er.</NOTE> gat &yogh;emete mid gode repples and stiarne sw&eacute;pen. and stiarne h&iacute;ne bes&iacute;&eacute;. and binde him hand and f&eacute;tt. and do hine into &thorn;iester|nesse. and &thorn;er abide of<NOTE PLACE="marg">? of=o&eth;.</NOTE> all his &yogh;eferen were &yogh;egadered. &thorn;at hi alle clone. s&iacute;mle bel&oacute;cen were. &THORN;a sende se king his &aelig;rndraches of fif ce&eth;en to alle his under&thorn;eoden. to &yogh;ela&eth;ie &thorn;is folc. hwet bute &iacute;come s&uacute;m c&oacute;fer sum l&aacute;ter sum frend sum fend. and was idon b&iacute; ham al sw&aacute; &aelig;r cwe&eth;e &thorn;at isett was. &THORN;a hit &thorn;er to com. &thorn;at se hlaford into &thorn;ar halle come. mid his d&iacute;erewurd &yogh;eferede. mid &aelig;rlen and aldren. mid cnihten mid &thorn;e&iacute;nen. &thorn;a cwe&eth; se hlafor[d] to his. &AElig;&eacute;r &thorn;anne we mid ure frienden to&eth;e mete g&oacute;. scepie<NOTE PLACE="marg">? scewie.</NOTE> we &thorn;es unco&eth;e m&aelig;n ur &yogh;ef&oacute;. &thorn;a hi to-for him c&oacute;me. &thorn;a w&eacute;nte he hin to 
<PB REF="00000297.tif" N="233"> ham and &thorn;us cwe&eth;. Unwraste man wat lacede &yogh;&eacute;u an alle m&iacute;re rice &thorn;at &yogh;&iacute;e hatrede and widerwardnesse a&yogh;&eacute;nes me &yogh;e win sceolde. and to mine f&aacute; &yogh;ebugon. Sw&aacute; ibr&uacute;ce ic mine rice ne scule &yogh;&iacute;e mine mete ibite. ac scule &thorn;a &thorn;e hit mid mire lufe &yogh;earnede. &THORN;a &thorn;is was is&eacute;gd. &thorn;a were cofe abruden into &thorn;esternesse. &thorn;e hi sturfe hungre. and se hlaford nam hit him to is frenden and et and dranc and macede hine wel bli&eth;e mid his and &thorn;er hi hadden brad and win. and vii. sandon. &para; [N]u gode menn understande&eth; &thorn;is bispel. &THORN;es king is ure hlaford almihti god &thorn;e is king ofer alle kingen. and hlaford ofer alle hlaforden. S[t]rang he his and michti. for he &yogh;esceop alle &thorn;ing of nahte. and na &thorn;ing ne m&aacute;&yogh;i &aacute;&yogh;enes his wille. ne him wi&eth;stande. for &thorn;an him seigd se w&iacute;t&iacute;&yogh;e. <I>Qui celorum contines tronos et cetera.</I> &thorn;at is. hlaford of mihte &thorn;e alste hefenen &thorn;rimsettles. and t&oacute; neowelnesse &thorn;e under eor&eth;e is be-loc&eacute;st. in. pon<NOTE PLACE="marg">? uppon.</NOTE>. &thorn;e dunan &thorn;u awi&eth;hst eor&eth;e belucst<NOTE PLACE="marg">in. pon &thorn;e dunan eor&eth;e belucst <I>seems to be an inter|polation of the scribe.</I></NOTE> mid &thorn;ina hand; he is &iacute;wiss mihti for &thorn;an &thorn;e non mihte nis buton fram him. His land is all &thorn;es middenard. for he alle &yogh;esceop. and all dihte wi&eth;-ute swince. He us is. king. and sceppend. and fader. and hlaford. King for he mid rihtwisnesse diht man and engel god and euel. sceppende. for he us machede lichame and sawle ableow. feder for he us fett and scred. and for&eth;teh al se is cyldren. hlaford for &thorn;an &thorn;e is &yogh;&eacute;ie and drednesse is ofer hus. and [vel as] &aacute;h to bienne. He is hure fader. he len&eth; us his eor&eth;e t&oacute; tolie. he corn to sawe. his eor&eth;e us werp&eth; corn and westm. n&iacute;att. and dierchin. his loht le&oacute;em and lif. his w&aacute;ter. drench and fiscynn. his f&eacute;r manifeald &thorn;en&iacute;nge. his s&oacute;nne. mone. sterren. rien. d&aacute;w. wind. wude. unitald fultume al &thorn;at we habbe&eth; of &thorn;&eacute;se feder we habbe&eth;. of<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. os.</NOTE> wam we alle and us siel&thorn;e habbe&eth;. M&uacute;&yogh;e we ahct clepeien hine moder wene we. &yogh;&iacute;e mu&yogh;e we. hwat de&eth; si moder hire bearn. formes hi hit chete&eth; and blissi&eth; be &thorn;e lichte. and se&thorn;e hi die&eth; under hire &aacute;rme <MILESTONE UNIT="Cott. Vesp. A. 22. folio" N="57a">o&eth;er his hafed hele&eth; to don him slepe. and reste. &THORN;is de&eth; all &yogh;&iacute;ure drihte. he blisse&eth; hus mid d&yogh;&eacute;ies<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE> licht. h[e] sweue&eth; hus mid &thorn;iestre nicht. G&iacute;et for an o&eth;re &thorn;ing god &yogh;escop &thorn;a niht. He wat wel &thorn;at man&iacute;&yogh;e men bie&eth; sa ful of &yogh;&eacute;scung. mihti efre &iacute;s&iacute;. N&aacute; &yogh;ew&oacute;ld ham selfe. to bigeten wrldlic &eacute;chte. &thorn;er for. god hafd &yogh;escepe ham reste. 
<PB REF="00000299.tif" N="235"> s&uacute;me wile hares un&thorn;ances. &yogh;e&iacute;et he cwe&eth; a wunder worder to &thorn;ar sawle bi &thorn;a wit&iacute;e ysaiam. <I>Numquid potest mulier obliuisci in|fantem suum ut non misereatur filii uteri sui.</I> &thorn;at is la l&iacute;ef ma&yogh;&iacute;e wiman for&yogh;eten his oge cild. &thorn;at hi ne milsi. hire b&aacute;rn of hire ogen inno&eth;. and &yogh;ief hi for&yogh;iet &thorn;ah hw&eacute;&eth;er nell &iacute;c for&yogh;ete &thorn;e cwe&eth; drihten. be &thorn;am &middot; &thorn;e he fader is and laf&oacute;rd he him sel&thorn; cwed be &thorn;e wit&iacute;e. <I>Si ego pater ubi est honor meus. si dominus ubi est timor meus.</I> &thorn;at is. gif ic fader ham. wer his mi manscipe. &yogh;if ic. hlaford wer h&iacute;s<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. hss.</NOTE> mine a&yogh;&eacute;&iacute;e? &thorn;er fore. G. m. ure king. we o&yogh;e&eth; <ABBR>wrhmint</ABBR>. hur sceappend al &thorn;at we bie&eth;. ure fader so&eth;e lufe. ur hlaford drednesse. And &thorn;is is s&eacute;o king &thorn;e wile w&iacute;te an alle his under|&thorn;eode w&aacute; hine lufe&eth; and hwa hine hate&eth;. hw&aacute; him is frend o&eth;er fend. And &thorn;er for he ha&eth; &yogh;ela&eth;ed alle fol[c]. to ane d&yogh;e&iacute;e. &thorn;at is domes d&yogh;e&iacute;e. &thorn;at hi alle &thorn;er beon be &thorn;e latst. hw&eacute; seden &aelig;rst &thorn;at &thorn;es &aelig;rndraces wer isent of fif che&eth;en. swa ibeo&eth;. &thorn;as fif che&eth;en beo&eth; fif l&aacute;gan. for &thorn;an &thorn;e god is &thorn;urh &thorn;esen &yogh;ecn&oacute;w&eacute;. Si forme lage &thorn;at is si &yogh;&eacute;c&eacute;nde l&aacute;ge. &thorn;e god sett formest an &thorn;es mannes heorte. &thorn;at is &thorn;at non man ne don o&eth;ere. buton &thorn;at &thorn;e he wolde &thorn;at me ded him. Wi&eth;-ute &thorn;eser l&aacute;ge nis man &thorn;e &yogh;escod habbe. &AElig;rndraces of &thorn;isser lage wer<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. &thorn;er.</NOTE> abel. Seth. enoc.