<PB REF="00000301.tif" N="237"> acolede &thorn;urh manifead f&eacute;nne<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>read</I> s&eacute;nne.</NOTE>. and hur and hur &thorn;urh false g&oacute;des &thorn;e &aelig;lc &thorn;iode ham selfe m&aacute;cede. sume of golde. s&uacute;m of silure. of treowe. of stane. and awente godes lof and wrhminte fram &thorn;e sceappende to &thorn;are &yogh;esceafte. swa &thorn;at &thorn;a ure halende wes accenned of &thorn;am unwemmede mede sante Marie. al se middennard was mid senne begripe. and al folc &yogh;ede in to &thorn;es diefles mu&eth;e. buton wel fe&aacute;we of wam his lefe moder wes istriened. he &thorn;a arerd alle godnisse. and sette his hal&iacute;e l&aacute;ge. and &thorn;at &thorn;e m&oacute;re his. &yogh;iaf miht and strenc&thorn;e &thorn;url<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &thorn;urh.</NOTE> &thorn;e gief of his gaste his hesne to fulfor&eth;ie. &thorn;at non o&eth;re la&yogh;e ne mihte. and understande&eth; hwu. &THORN;ri ampres were an mancyn &aelig;r his to-cyme. Ure acenneng wes ful. un<NOTE PLACE="marg">? ur.</NOTE> lif unwreast. ur dea&eth; grislic. he com and brochte &thorn;ri &thorn;in[g] &thorn;er a&yogh;&eacute;n. he wes ac&eacute;nde of &thorn;e clene mede. &thorn;e efer &thorn;urh lefede mede. his lif was hal&iacute;&yogh;e. his dea&eth; ful of milce. his clene acennende cl&eacute;ns&eacute;de ure fule acennende. his hali lif rihtlecede ure unwreaste lif. his admoded dea&eth; ofer com. and fordede ure sor&iacute;&yogh;e and &yogh;elice dea&eth;. &thorn;&iacute;s &iacute;s <MILESTONE UNIT="Cott. Vesp. A. 22. folio" N="57b">si fier&eth;e l&aacute;ge. An &thorn;isser were &aelig;rndraces and &yogh;ela&eth;ieres &thorn;a apostles and &thorn;e leorninchihtes. &thorn;er efter ures helendes upst&iacute;&yogh;e to heuene. &thorn;a apostles and hare &iacute;unglenges &thorn;e[r] efter come hal&iacute;e men and &thorn;e hafedmen &thorn;e nu beo&eth; in hal&iacute;e cyrce. and wr&eth;e&eth; of<NOTE PLACE="marg">? o&eth;.</NOTE> domes d&eacute;&yogh;e. &thorn;urh &thorn;es hali gastes &yogh;&iacute;fe. and al swa ure helende ham le&oacute;rde. man&iacute;&yogh;e &thorn;ing ehten &thorn;a folce to freme. and &thorn;is is si fifte lage. An &thorn;isser beo&eth; bedeles and la&eth;ieres to berie archebiscopes. and biscopes. prestes. and hare &yogh;egeng. Ac &thorn;ah we fif n&aelig;mm&iacute;e. alle hit on godes wille. and &eacute;lc of ham &yogh;estren&eth; and fulfell&thorn; o&eth;re. Of &thorn;eses fif ce&thorn;en and of hare bedeles we habbe&eth; &yogh;&eacute;u &yogh;&eacute;s&eacute;d. Of &thorn;e folce we sigge&eth; &thorn;at hit cum&thorn; fastlice. fram middenardes anginn alse fele alse deade beo&eth; alse fele beo&eth; to berie &iacute;c&oacute;me. wat frend. wat f&aacute;. and elce de&yogh;&iacute;e &thorn;&iacute;cce &thorn;ringe&eth;. Ac &yogh;ief &yogh;&eacute; habbe&eth; under|stande &thorn;at we &yogh;&iacute;u er s&eacute;de. eter gate me his sc&yacute;ft. and &thorn;er me hi to &yogh;esceode&eth;. Si gate &thorn;at is elces mannes endede&iacute;e. &thorn;at he step&eth; ut of &thorn;ese life into &thorn;an o&eth;re<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. dd&eth;re.</NOTE>. Ac we sede &yogh;ehw. &thorn;at &yogh;ief he frend were me sceolde &yogh;ief him his m&oacute;r&yogh;e mete &thorn;at he &thorn;e bet mihte abide &thorn;ane more mete. Swa hit is here. &thorn;at se gode man &thorn;e godes lufe ha&eth; &yogh;efolged to is ende cum&thorn;. witetlice wi&eth;-ut m&iacute;antruce &thorn;er cume&eth; &thorn;e hali engles him t&oacute;. and &yogh;&eacute;f ha&eth; ahte uniwasse o&eth;er hit 
<PB REF="00000303.tif" N="239"> wr&eth; &yogh;ewasse i&thorn;er pine of &thorn;e dea&eth;e &thorn;e he her &thorn;&aacute;le&eth;. o&eth;er efter mid e&eth;elice lette. and &thorn;an lat me &thorn;a sawle to <ABBR>merchestowe</ABBR>. &thorn;at his se mor&yogh;emete si blisse &thorn;e he ha&eth; an &thorn;ar sawle. &thorn;at wite &yogh;e wel. nan halege na&eth; his fulle blisse er he underf&oacute; adomes de&iacute;e his licame. &thorn;at wr&eth; se fulle mete. &thorn;an se mann mid sawle and mid licame underfang&eth; sicernesse of &eacute;cer blisse. And wat belimp&eth; hit &yogh;ief he fend his &thorn;e to &thorn;are gate cum&thorn;? God &thorn;urh his mucele milce ne letes us nefer fandie. Ac na&thorn;eles &yogh;ief he fend his an unwreast mann &thorn;er beo&eth; an&uacute; &yogh;er&eacute;die. &thorn;e weregede gastes &thorn;e hine uniredlice underfange&eth; min stiarne swupen. Alse fele un&thorn;eawes alse hade upe him and sennenn. al swa fendes he &thorn;er &yogh;emet. h&imacr;ne to underf&oacute;. and to don h&imacr;ne into &thorn;iesternesse. oft a domes d&yogh;&eacute;i alle godes fend simle fram his &yogh;esec&eth;e abroden bienn. and hi to hare lean ham &thorn;e lange scel &yogh;eleste. &THORN;us hit ha&eth; &iacute;b&iacute; and &iacute;s. and wr&eth; oft domesdei. Ac &thorn;anne hit &thorn;er to cum&thorn; &thorn;at se hlaford &aacute; &thorn;e mucele de&iacute;e. cum&thorn; fort&eacute; &iacute;s&iacute; and frend and fend. &thorn;ann cum&thorn; all his under&thorn;iede him to-fore. &thorn;er he sit mid his derewr&thorn;e &yogh;efered mid ni&yogh;en anglene had. mid &thorn;er unw&emacr;mmed meide his moder. mid his apostlen. mid &thorn;a h&aacute;gefaderen. and &thorn;o hal&iacute;&yogh;e w&iacute;tien. mid martiren. mi[d] hali confessoren mid halie meiden. mid al &thorn;an &thorn;e &thorn;er midenarde for his lufe werpe&eth; ab&eacute;c. and lagelice her him &thorn;eni&eth;. wic &yogh;e&iacute;e. wic drednesse wur&eth; &thorn;er. &thorn;an &thorn;at fer to for him abern&eth; &thorn;at middernad<NOTE PLACE="marg">sic.</NOTE>. &thorn;an si eor&eth;e alle cw&aacute;ced &thorn;an &thorn;e sterren falle&eth;. si sunne and se mone a&thorn;estre&eth; for godes brictnesse. &thorn;e wlcne to ga&eth;. and si hali rode tacne mid &thorn;e spere and mid &thorn;e neiles &thorn;urh angles beo&eth; for&eth; ibrocht. &thorn;anne &thorn;e angles cwacia&eth;. and t&oacute; richtw&iacute;se ham adrede&eth;. wat sceol se senfulle don. &thorn;e isecg&eth; &thorn;er his richtwise deme. &thorn;e non ne ma&iacute;e bechece. non beswice. he his him sel&thorn; witnisse and deme. Wat sceol se wrecce don. &thorn;e bufon is&eacute;&yogh;&eth; his hlaford &thorn;e he &yogh;egremed &aacute;fe&eth;. under him helle mu&eth; open. abuuten him all folc. him selfe bi sandlice senne beswapen. &thorn;er ne m&aacute;i non frend o&eth;re helpe. &aelig;lc had inn&oacute;h to donne an him selfe. &THORN;an seied ham god &thorn;e gelty mannen &yogh;e sene&yogh;eden. an &yogh;eur &eacute;cenesse. and &yogh;e scule <MILESTONE UNIT="Cott. Vesp. A. 22. folio" N="58a">birne an mire &eacute;cenisse. &YOGH;e sene&yogh;den alse lange alse &yogh;&eacute; lefede and &yogh;e scule birne alse longe as &iacute;c lefie. Wite&eth; into &eacute;ce fer. &thorn;e is &yogh;&aelig;arced mine f&oacute; and his 
<PB REF="00000305.tif" N="241"> &yogh;egen[g] Son hi wr&eth;e&eth; abroden of his &yogh;esec&thorn;e. And &thorn;an sone<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. fone.</NOTE> ge&eth; se hlaford mid his frenden to his mete. &thorn;at his to is esten. &thorn;e sei&eth; an &thorn;an hali write <I>Delicie m&eacute;&eacute; sunt esse cum filiis homi|num.</I> &thorn;at is. Mine esten beo&eth; wunian mid mannen bearnen. Ac we[habbe&eth; &yogh;e-] sed &yogh;&iacute;u litl her &thorn;at hi sceolden abben god brad and uin. and vii. sonden. hi sculen habe &thorn;at brad &thorn;e sei&eth; i&thorn;e godspel. <I>Ego sum panis uiuus qui de celo descendit.</I> &THORN;et is. Ic &aacute;m cwuce bread &thorn;e astah fram hefene. se&yogh;&eth; ure helende. Se &thorn;e of &thorn;ese brad ett. ne sterfe&eth; he nefer. &THORN;is bread was &iacute;maced of ane hwete corne. al swa se he cwe&eth; &yogh;e&eth;e godspelle. <I>Nisi granum frumenti. et cetera.</I> &thorn;is corn was &yogh;esawen &thorn;urh &thorn;es &aelig;ngles mu&eth; into &eth;es meidenes &aelig;re Marie. in &thorn;are burh of nazareth. &thorn;is corn c&oacute;m<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. c&oacute;n.</NOTE> ferst inne bethleem. &thorn;at cwe&eth; us of breade. hit wex and ble&oacute;wu. in iudea. hit r&iacute;pede in ierusalem. Iudas and &thorn;at leo&eth;re folc hit r&eacute;p&eacute;n. and deden hit an &thorn;ar rode alswa alse betwenen melstanent. Sede hit was idon into &thorn;er berien. alswa into h&oacute;fne. &thorn;anen hit was ibroht up into heofene to &thorn;es hahes hlafordes borde. &thorn;er hit fet. and engles. and mancinn in &eacute;cenisse. and &thorn;is is hare bread. hwer scule we win finden? Al swa se he cwe&eth;. <I>Ego sum uitis uera. et cetera.</I></P>
