<DIV2 N="27" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XXVII. [DOMINICA IIII. POST PENTECOSTEN.]</HEAD>
<P><I>[E]rant appropinquantes. et cetera.</I> &thorn;et h&aacute;li godspell &uacute;s sei&eth;.<MILESTONE UNIT="Cott. Vesp. A. 22. folio" N="59b"> &thorn;at hi-r&eacute;fen and syn&thorn;ulle<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> m&eacute;n &yogh;eneahlehton &thorn;an helende. and woldan his l&aacute;re &yogh;ehiran. &THORN;a c&eacute;arodon &thorn;a sunder h&aacute;l&yogh;&aacute;n and 
<PB REF="00000309.tif" N="245"> &thorn;a boceras &thorn;er he&eth;en &thorn;eode. for &eth;an &thorn;e se helende under-feng &thorn;a sinfullan. and ham mid im&oacute;ne hafede. &THORN;a sede se helende &thorn;a sunder hal&yogh;e and &thorn;a b&oacute;cere &thorn;is bispell. Hwilc eower hef&eth; an hu[n]dred sceap. Gif he fo[r]list &amacr;n &thorn;ara sceape. la h&uacute;ne forlet h&eacute; ne&yogh;on and hun neo&yogh;ontie a westene and ge&eth; secende &thorn;at an &thorn;e him losede? Gif he hit &thorn;an &yogh;emet. he hit ber&eth; an his eaxlun to &thorn;ara eowde. oder falde blissiende. &THORN;an he ham cym&eth; he &yogh;ela&eth;e&eth; his frend and nichi-bures him to and cwe&eth;. Blissia&eth; mid me fo[r]&thorn;an &thorn;e ic im&eacute;te mi sceap &thorn;e me losede. Ic sege eow &thorn;at mare blisse bi&eth; an hefene be anun synfulle man. &yogh;if he his synnen mid dedbote bere&uacute;se&eth;. &thorn;an him s&iacute; be nigon and hund negont&iacute;e rihtwisen &thorn;e ne beofia&eth; nanre ded bote.</P>
