<PB REF="00000311.tif" N="247"> lauerd. ant hwer. se he is &yogh;emeles; nis hare nan &thorn;e ne feare&eth; ofte untoheliche. ant gulte&eth; ilome. o&eth;er ifol semblant; oder in vuel dede. In wi&eth; beo&eth; his hinen. in se moni mislich &thorn;onc to cwemen wel &thorn;e husewif; a&yogh;ein godes wille. ant swerie&eth; somet rea&eth;liche. &thorn;at efter hire hit schal <MILESTONE UNIT="Bodleian MS. 34 folio" N="76b">gan. &thorn;ah we hit ne here nawt; we<NOTE PLACE="marg">omitted.</NOTE> mahen ifelen<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. i&thorn;&thorn;len.</NOTE> hare nurh&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg">nur&eth;.</NOTE>. ant hare untohe bere. a &thorn;et hit<NOTE PLACE="marg">wit.</NOTE> cume for&eth;. ant ba wi&eth; eie. ant wi&eth; luue tuhte ham &thorn;e betere. Ne bi&eth; neauer his hus for &thorn;eos hinen wel iwist. for hwon &thorn;at he slepe. o&eth;er ohwider<NOTE PLACE="marg">ohwider fare.</NOTE> from hame. &thorn;at is hwen mon for&yogh;et his wit. ant let ham iwur&eth;en. ah ne bihoue&eth; hit nawt. &thorn;at tis hus beo irobbet. for &thorn;er is inne &thorn;e tre[sur] &thorn;at godd &yogh;ef him seolf fore. &thorn;at is monnes sawle. forte breoke &thorn;is hus efter &thorn;is tresor. &thorn;at godd bohte mid his dea&eth;. ant lette lif o rode; is moni &thorn;eof a buten ba bi dei ant bi niht. vnseheliche gasttes wi&eth; alle unwreaste &thorn;eawes. ant a&yogh;ein euch god &thorn;eaw. &thorn;e biwite&eth; i&thorn;is hus godes deore castel<NOTE PLACE="marg">chatel.</NOTE>. vnder wittes wissunge &thorn;at is huse lauerd. is eauer hire un&thorn;eaw forte sechen in &yogh;ong abute &thorn;e wahes to a mur&eth;rin hire &thorn;rinne. &thorn;at heaued &thorn;rof is &thorn;e feont. &thorn;e meistre&eth; ham alle a&yogh;eines him ant his keis. &thorn;e husebonde &thorn;at is wit. warne&eth; his hus &thorn;us. vre lauerd haue&eth; ileanett him froure<NOTE PLACE="marg">fowre.</NOTE> of his dehtren. &thorn;at beo&eth; to vnderstonden &thorn;e fowr heaued &thorn;eawes. &thorn;e earste is warschipe icleopet. ant te o&thorn;er is ihaten gastelich streng&eth;e. ant te &thorn;ridde is mea&eth;. rihtwisnesse &thorn;e feor&eth;e. Wit &thorn;e husbonde godes cunestable cleope&eth; war <MILESTONE UNIT="Bodleian MS. 34 folio" N="77a">schipe for&eth;. ant maki&eth; hire durewart. &thorn;e war|liche loki hwam ha leote in ant ut. ant of feor bihalde alle &thorn;e cuminde. hwuch beo wur&eth;e in&yogh;ong to habben; o&eth;er beon bistek|en &thorn;rute. Streng&eth;e stont nest hire. &thorn;at &yogh;ef ei wule in; war|schipes<NOTE PLACE="marg">omitted.</NOTE> vn &thorn;onkes. warni streng&eth;e fore. &thorn;at is hire suster; ant heo hit ut warpe. &thorn;e &thorn;ridde suster &thorn;at is mea&eth;. hire he make&eth; meistre ouer his willesfule hir&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg">hinen.</NOTE> &thorn;at we ear of speken. &thorn;at ha leare ham mete<NOTE PLACE="marg">me &eth;e.</NOTE>. &thorn;at me<NOTE PLACE="marg">omitted.</NOTE> meosure hat. &thorn;e middel of twa uueles<NOTE PLACE="marg">&thorn;ing.</NOTE>. for &thorn;at is &thorn;eaw in euch stude ant tuht forte halden. ant hate&eth; ham alle &thorn;at nan of ham a&yogh;ein hire; nohwer wid vnmeo&eth;; ne ga ouer mete. &thorn;e feor&eth;e suster rihtwisnesse. sit on hest as deme<NOTE PLACE="marg">demere.</NOTE>. ant beate&eth; &thorn;eo &thorn;e a&yogh;ulte&eth;. ant crune&eth; &thorn;eo &thorn;e wel do&eth;. ant deme&eth; euchan his dom efter his rihte. for dret<NOTE PLACE="marg">dred.</NOTE> of hire nime&eth; his<NOTE PLACE="marg">&thorn;is.</NOTE> 
