uche murh&eth;e as of his ahne<NOTE PLACE="marg">as him seoluen.</NOTE>. bi &thorn;is &yogh;e mahen seon ant witen. &thorn;at euchan haue&eth; sunderlepes ase feole glead|schipes; as ha beod monie alle. ant euch of &thorn;e ilke gleadschipes is<NOTE PLACE="marg">beo&eth;.</NOTE> to eauer euch an ase muche gleadunge; as his ahne sunderliche. &yogh;et ouer al &thorn;is. hwen euchan luue&eth; godd mare &thorn;en him seoluen. ant &thorn;en alle &thorn;e odre; mare he gleade&eth; of godd wi&eth; uten ei et|lunge<NOTE PLACE="marg">ei eilung.</NOTE> &thorn;en of his ahne gleadunge. ant of alle &thorn;e o&eth;res. Neome&eth; nu &thorn;enne &yogh;eme &yogh;ef neauer anes heorte ne mei in hire [und]<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. torn.</NOTE> eruon hire ahne gleadunge sunderliche [iseide. so unim] ete muchel is &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">&thorn;en.</NOTE> anlepi blisse. &thorn;at ha nime&eth; i[n] hi[re] &thorn;us monie. ant &thorn;us muchele. for &thorn;i seide ure lauerd to &thorn;eo &thorn;e him hefden ic|wemet. <I>Intra in gaudium. et cetera.</I> Ga quo&eth; he in to &thorn;i lauerdes blisse<NOTE PLACE="marg">hus.</NOTE>. &thorn;u most al gan &thorn;rin. ant al beon bigotten &thorn;rin for in &thorn;e ne mei hit nanesweis<NOTE PLACE="marg">o nane wise.</NOTE> neomen in. her of ha herie&eth; godd ant singe&eth; 
<PB REF="00000329.tif" N="265"> &aacute; un werget eauer iliche lusti in &thorn;is loft songes. as hit iwriten is. <I>Beati qui habitant. et cetera.</I> Eadi beo&eth; &thorn;eo lauerd. &thorn;e i&thorn;in<NOTE PLACE="marg">in &thorn;is.</NOTE> hus wunie&eth; ha schulen herien &thorn;e from [worlde into worlde]. Ha beo&eth; alle ase li[hte ant as swifte as &thorn;e sunne] gleam &thorn;e sc[heot from est into west. ase &thorn;in] <MILESTONE UNIT="Bodleian MS. 34 folio" N="84b">ehe-lid tune&eth; ant opene&eth; for hwer se eauer &thorn;e gast wule &thorn;e bodi is anan riht wi&eth; ute lettunge. for ne mei ham na &thorn;ing a&yogh;eines etstonden. for euch an is al<NOTE PLACE="marg">as.</NOTE> mihti to don al &thorn;at he wule. &yogh;e makie to cwakien heouene ba ant eor&eth;e wi&eth; his an finger. Sikere ha beo&eth; of al &thorn;is of &thorn;ulli lif. of &thorn;ulli wit. of &thorn;ulli luue ant<NOTE PLACE="marg">a.</NOTE> gleadunge &thorn;rof. ant of &thorn;ulli blisse. &thorn;at hit ne me neauer mare lutlin ne wursin. ne neome nan ende. &thorn;is lutle ich habbe iseid of &thorn;at ich iseh in heouene ah nower neh ne neh ich al. ne &thorn;at &yogh;et &thorn;at ich [iseh. ne] ne con ich half<NOTE PLACE="marg">al.</NOTE> tellen. Witer|[liche quo&eth;] warschipe. wel we understonde&eth; &thorn;at tu hauest ibeo &thorn;ear ant so&eth; hauest iseid trof. efter &thorn;i sih&eth;e. ant wel is him &thorn;at is war. ant bisi&eth; him hu he mahe beast halden his hus &thorn;at godes tresor is in a&yogh;eines godes unwine &thorn;e weorre&eth; &thorn;er towart a wi&eth; un&thorn;eawes. for &thorn;et. schal bringen him &thorn;ider as he schal. al &thorn;is &thorn;at tu hauest ispeken of an<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>ant.</I></NOTE> hundret si&eth;e mare of blisse buten euch bale<NOTE PLACE="marg">wi&eth; uten balesi&eth;.</NOTE> folhin ant ifinden. Quo&eth; streng&eth;e hwen hit swa is; hwet mei tweamen us from godd ant hald[en us &thorn;eonne. ih] am siker ine godd. [&thorn;at ne schal lif ne de&eth;; ne wa] ne wunne now&eth;er [to dealen us ant his luue. ah al &thorn;is] us haue&eth; igarc<NOTE PLACE="marg">Bodl. MS.</NOTE> [ket &yogh;&egrave;f we as treowe tresures wite&eth; wel his tresor &thorn;at is bitaht us to halden. as we schulen ful wel under his wengen. Warpe&eth; ut quo&eth; warschipe; farlac ure fa. nis nawt riht &thorn;at an hus halde &thorn;eos tweien. for &thorn;er as mur&eth;es sonde is; ant so&eth; luue of eche lif. farlac is fleme. nu ut quo&eth; stren&eth;e farlac ne schaltu na lengere leuen in ure ende. nu quo&eth; ich seide for god al &thorn;at ich seide. ant &thorn;ah hit muri nere nes na lessere mi tale &thorn;en wes murh&eth;es sondes ne unbihefre to ow. &thorn;ah hit ne beo so licwur&eth;e ne icweme. Ei&eth;er of ow haue&eth; his stunde to speokene. ne nis incker no&eth;res tale to schunien in his time. &thorn;u warnest of wa. he telle&eth; of wunne. muche neod is &thorn;at me ow ba &yogh;eornliche hercni. Flute nu farlac &thorn;ah. hwil liues luue is herinne. ant &thorn;ole wi&eth; efne heorte &thorn;e dom of rihtwisnesse. for &thorn;u schal[t]. ful bli&eth;eliche beon 
<PB REF="00000331.tif" N="267"> under-fon in as ofte as liues luue stinte&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. stutte&eth;.</NOTE> forto spekene. Nv is wil &thorn;at husewif al stille. &thorn;at er wes so willesful. Al ituht efter wittes wissunge &thorn;at is husebonde. ant Al &thorn;at hird halt him stille. &thorn;at wes i-wunet to beon fulitohen ant don efter wil hare lefdi. Ant nawt efter wit; lustne&eth; nu his lare. ant fonde&eth; euer euchan efter &thorn;at him limpe&eth; to. &thorn;urh &thorn;eos twa sonden. &thorn;at ha i-herd habbe&eth;. ant &thorn;at fowr sustren lerden &thorn;ruppe for euch un&thorn;eawes in&yogh;ong his warde te witene. ant te warden treowliche. &THORN;vs ah mon te &thorn;enchen ofte Ant ilome. Ant wi&eth; &thorn;ulliche &thorn;ohtes awec|chen his heorte. &thorn;e islep of &yogh;emeles for-&yogh;et hire sawle heale. efter &thorn;eos twa sonden. From helle sih&eth;e biseon; to &thorn;e blisse of heouene. To habben farlac of &thorn;at an; luue toward &thorn;at o&eth;er. ant leaden him ant hinen. &thorn;at beo&eth; his limen alle. nawt efter wil &thorn;e untohe lefdi ant his lust leare&eth;. ah efter &thorn;at wit wule &thorn;at is husebonde tuhten ant teachen &thorn;at wit ga euer biuore ant teache wil efter him. to al &thorn;at he dihte&eth; ant deme&eth; to donne. ant wi&eth; &thorn;e fowr sustren; &thorn;er fore &thorn;e fowr heued &thorn;eawes. War|schipe. Strenc&eth;e in godd. Ant Me&eth;. Ant Rihtwisnesse. witen godes treosor &thorn;at is his ahne sawle. i&thorn;e hus of &thorn;e bodi; from &thorn;e &thorn;eof of helle. &thorn;ulli &thorn;oht make&eth; mon te fleon alle un&thorn;eawes ant ontent his heorte toward &thorn;e blisse of heouene. &thorn;at ure lauerd &yogh;eue us &thorn;urh his hali milce &thorn;at wi&eth; &thorn;e feder. ant e sune ant e hali gast rixle&eth; in &thorn;reo had &aacute; buten ende. AMEN.</P>
<P>Par seinte charite bidde&eth; a pater noster for iohan &thorn;at &thorn;eos boc wrat.</P>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwa se &thorn;is writ haue&eth; ired.</L>
<L>Ant crist him haue&eth; swa isped.</L>
<L>Ich bidde par seinte charite.</L>
<L>&THORN;et &yogh;e bidden ofte for me.</L>
<L>Aa pater noster. ant aue marie.</L>
<L>&THORN;et ich mote &thorn;at lif her drehen.</L>
<L>Ant ure lauerd wel icwemen.</L>
<L>I Mi &yogh;uhe&eth;e ant in min elde.</L>
<L>&THORN;et ich mote ihesu crist mi sawle &yogh;elden.]</L>
<TRAILER>AMEN.
</TRAILER>

</LG>
