<DIV2 N="29" TYPE="homily"><PB REF="00000333.tif" N="269">
<HEAD>XXIX. HER BIGINNES &THORN;E WOHUNGE OF URE LAUERD.<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. Cotton Titus D. 18.</NOTE></HEAD>
<P>Ihesu swete ihesu. mi dru&eth;. mi derling. mi drihtin. mi healend. mi huniter. mi haliwei. Swetter is munegunge of &thorn;e &thorn;en mildeu o mu&eth;e. Hwa ne mei luue &thorn;i luueli leor? Hwat herte is swa hard &thorn;at ne mei to-melte i &thorn;e munegunge of &thorn;e? Ah hwa ne mei luue &thorn;e luueliche ihesu? for inwi&eth; &thorn;e ane arn alle &thorn;e &thorn;inges igedered &thorn;at eauer muhen maken ani mon luuewur&eth;i to o&eth;er. feirnesse and lufsum neb. flesch hwit under schrud makes moni mon beo luued te ra&eth;er. and te mare. Summe gold and Gersum and ahte of &thorn;is worlde makes luued and heried. Sume; fredom and largesce &thorn;at leuer is menskli to &yogh;iuen &thorn;en cwedli to wi&eth; halde. Summe; wit and wisdom and &yogh;apschipe of werlde. Summe; maht and streng&eth;e to beo kid and kene ifiht his riht for to halde. Summe; noblesce. and hehnesse of bur&eth;e. Summe; &thorn;eaw. and hendeleic and lastelese<MILESTONE UNIT="MS. Cotton Titus D. 18. folio" N="127b"> lates. Summe; menske and mildeschipe and debonairte of herte and dede. And &yogh;ette ouer al &thorn;is; kinde makes sibbe frend euchan to luuen o&eth;er. Nu mi derewur&eth;e dru&eth;. mi luue. mi lif. mi leof. mi luueleuest, mi heorte haliwei. mi sawle swetnesse. &THORN;u art lufsum on leor. &thorn;u art al schene. al engles lif is ti neb to bihalden. for &thorn;i leor is swa unimete lufsum and lusti on to loken; &thorn;at &yogh;if &thorn;e forwariede &thorn;at wallen in helle mihten hit echeliche seon; al &thorn;at pinende pik. ne walde ham &thorn;unche bote a softe bekinde ba&eth;. for &yogh;if hit swa mihte beon; leuere ham were eauer mare in wa for to welle and o &thorn;at welefule wlite eauer mar to loken; &thorn;en in alle blisse beon and forgan &thorn;i sih&eth;e. &THORN;u art swa schene and swa hwit; &thorn;at te sunne were dosk &yogh;if hit to &thorn;i blisfule bleo mihte beo euenet. &THORN;a &yogh;if &thorn;at iwile animon for feirnesse luue; luue iwile &thorn;e mi leue lif, moder sune feirest. A ihesu mi swete 
<PB REF="00000335.tif" N="271"> ihesu leue &thorn;at te luue of &thorn;e beo al mi likinge. Bote nu iwile for ahte lefmon chese for aihwer wi&eth; chatel mon mai luue cheape. Ah is ani ricchere &thorn;en &thorn;u mi leof &thorn;at rixles in heuene. &thorn;u art kid keiser &thorn;at al &thorn;is werld wrahtes. for as te hali prophete dauid cwiddes. drihtines is te eor&eth;e. and al &thorn;at hit fulles werld and al &thorn;at trin wune&eth;. Heuene wi&eth; &thorn;e murh&eth;es and ta unimete blisses. Al is tin mi sweting. and al &thorn;u wilt &yogh;iue me &yogh;if i &thorn;e riht luuie. Ne mai i na man &yogh;iue mi luue to swettere bi&yogh;ete. Halde iwile &thorn;a to &thorn;e mi leof for &thorn;e self luue &thorn;e seluen. and for &thorn;i luue leten alle o&eth;re &thorn;inges &thorn;at min herte fram &thorn;i luue mihte drahe and turnen. A Ihesu swete ihesu leoue &thorn;at te luue of &thorn;e beo al mi likinge. Bote <MILESTONE UNIT="MS. Cotton Titus D. 18. folio" N="128a">hwat is ahte and weorldes wele wur&eth; wi&eth;|uten fredom? And hwa is frerre &thorn;en &thorn;u? For first &thorn;u mades al &thorn;is werld and dides hit under mine fet. and makedes me lauedi ouer alle &thorn;ine schaftes &thorn;at tu schop on eor&eth;e. Bote Ich hit rewli fordide &thorn;urh-hut mine sunnes. Ah lest ine al forlesede &thorn;u &yogh;ef &thorn;e seluen for me to lese me fra pine &THORN;enne &yogh;if i ani wile for largesce luue; luue iwile &thorn;e ihesu crist largest ouer o&eth;re. For o&eth;re largemen &yogh;iuen &thorn;ise uttre &thorn;inges. bute &thorn;u swete ihesu for me &yogh;ef &thorn;e seluen. &thorn;at tin ahne heorte blod ne cu&eth;es tu wi&eth;-halde. Derre druri ne &yogh;ef neauer na lefmon to o&eth;er. And tu &thorn;at erst me &yogh;ef al &thorn;e seluen; &thorn;u hafdes me heht mi lefmon to &thorn;e &yogh;iue al me seluen. to rixlen o &thorn;i rihthond crunet wi&eth; &thorn;e seluen. Hwa is ta largere &thorn;en &thorn;u. Hwa for largesce is betere wur&eth; to beo luued &thorn;en &thorn;u mi luue lif. A ihesu swete ihesu leue &thorn;at te luue of &thorn;e beo al mi likinge. Bote largesce is lutel wur&eth; &thorn;er wisdom wontes. And &yogh;if &thorn;at iwile animon luue for wisdom; nis nan wisere &thorn;en &thorn;u &thorn;at art wisedom cald of &thorn;i fader in heuene. For he &thorn;urh &thorn;e &thorn;at wisdom art al &thorn;is world wrahte and dihte&eth; hit and deale&eth; as hit best seme&eth;. Inwi&eth; &thorn;e mi leue lif is hord of alle wisedom hid as te bok witnesses. A ihesu swete ihesu leue &thorn;at te luue of &thorn;e beo al mi likinge. Bote moni man &thorn;urh his streng&eth;e and hardischipe ek makes him luued and &yogh;erned. And is ani swa hardi swa artu? Nai. for &thorn;u &thorn;e ane dreddes nawt wi&eth; &thorn;in anre deore bodi to fihte a&yogh;aines alle &thorn;e ahefulle deueles of helle. &thorn;at hwuch of ham swa is lest la&eth;eliche. and grureful. 
<PB REF="00000337.tif" N="273">  mihte he swuch as he is to monkin him scheawe; al &thorn;e world were offeard him ane to bihalde for ne mihte na mon him seo and in his wit wunie. bute &yogh;if &thorn;e grace <MILESTONE UNIT="MS. Cotton Titus D. 18. folio" N="128b">and te streng&eth;e of crist baldede his heorte. &thorn;u art &yogh;ette her wi&eth; swa unimete mihti &thorn;at wi&eth; &thorn;i deorewur&eth;e hond nailet on rode; &thorn;u band ta helle dogges. and reftes ham hare praie &thorn;at tai hefden grediliche gripen and helden hit faste for adames sunne. &thorn;u kene kidde kempe robbedes helle hus. lesedes tine prisuns and riddes ham ut of cwalm hus and leddes ham wi&eth; &thorn;e self to &thorn;i &yogh;immede bur. bold of eche blisse. for&thorn;i of &thorn;e mi lefmon was so&eth;liche quiddet. Drihti[n] is mahti strong and kene ifihte. And for &thorn;i &yogh;if me likes stalewur&eth;e lefmon; luue iwile &thorn;e ihesu strongest ouer alle. &thorn;at &thorn;i maht felle mine starke sawle fan. and te streng&eth;e of &thorn;e helpe mi muchele wacnesse. and hardischipe of &thorn;e balde min herte. A ihesu swete ihesu leue &thorn;at te luue of &thorn;e beo al mi likinge. Ah noble men and gentile and of heh bur&eth;e ofte winnen luue lihtliche cheape. for ofte moni wummon letes hire mensket &thorn;urh &thorn;e luue of wepmon &thorn;at is of heh bur&eth;e. &thorn;enne swete ihesu up o hwat herre mon mai i mi luue sette. hwer mai i gentiller mon chese &thorn;en &thorn;e &thorn;at art te kinges sune &thorn;at tis world wealdes. and king and euene wi&eth; &thorn;i fader. king ouer kinges lauerd ouer lauerdes And &yogh;ette onont ti monhad born &thorn;u wes of marie meiden mildest o mod. kine bearn of bur&eth;e. of daui&eth;es kin &thorn;e king. of Abrahames streone. Hehere bur&eth;e &thorn;en &thorn;is nis nan under sunne. Luue iwile &thorn;e &thorn;a swete ihesu as te gentileste lif &thorn;at eauer liuede on eor&eth;e. alswa for in al &thorn;i lif neauer na leaste nes ifunden. mi deore lefmon lasteles. and tat com &thorn;e of bur&eth;e. and of foster alswa. &thorn;u &thorn;at eauer wunedest i &thorn;e hurd of heouene. <MILESTONE UNIT="MS. Cotton Titus D. 18. folio" N="129">A mi deorewur&eth;e dru&eth; swa gentile and swa hende. ne &thorn;ole me neauer mi luue nohwer to sette o karlische &thorn;inges. ne eor&eth;li &thorn;ing ne fleschli a&yogh;aines te &yogh;erne ne luue a&yogh;ain &thorn;i wille. A ihesu swete ihesu leue &thorn;at te luue of &thorn;e beo al mi likinge. Meknesse and mildschipe makes mon eihwer luued. and tu mi leue ihesu for &thorn;i mikle meknesse to lamb was euenet. For a&yogh;aines al &thorn;e woh and te schome &thorn;at tu &thorn;oledest. and a&yogh;aines al &thorn;e wa and te pinfule wundes; neauer ne opnedes ti mu&eth; 
