<PB REF="00000349.tif" N="285"> sune. was wi&eth;inne martird i&thorn;i moderliche herte. &thorn;at seh to cleue his heorte wi&eth; &thorn;e speres ord. Bote lafdi for &thorn;e Ioie &thorn;at tu hefdes of his ariste &thorn;e &thorn;ridde dai &thorn;er after; leue me vnderstonde &thorn;i dol and herteli to felen sum hwat of &thorn;e sorhe &thorn;at tu &thorn;a hefdes and helpe &thorn;e to wepe. &thorn;at i wi&eth; him and wi&eth; &thorn;e muhe i min ariste o domes dai gladien and wi&eth; &yogh;u beon i blisse &thorn;at he me swa bitterliche wi&eth; his blod bohte. Ihesu swete ihesu &thorn;us tu faht for me a&yogh;aines mine sawle fan. &thorn;u me derennedes wi&eth; like. and makedes of me wrecche &thorn;i leofmon and spuse. Broht tu haues me fra &thorn;e world to bur of &thorn;i bur&eth;e. steked me i chaumbre. I mai &thorn;er &thorn;e swa sweteli kissen and cluppen. and of &thorn;i luue haue gastli likinge. A swete ihesu mi liues luue wi&eth; &thorn;i blod &thorn;u haues me boht. and fram &thorn;e world &thorn;u haues me broht. Bote nu mai i seggen wi&eth; &thorn;e salmewrihte. <I>Quid retribuam domino pro omnibus que retribuit michi.</I> Lauerd hwat mai i &yogh;elde &thorn;e for al &thorn;at tu haues &yogh;iuen me. Hwat mai &thorn;ole for &thorn;e for al &thorn;at tu &thorn;oledes for me? Ah me <MILESTONE UNIT="MS. Cotton Titus D. 18. folio" N="132b">bihoue&eth; &thorn;at tu beo ea&eth; to paie. a wrecche bodi and a wac bere ich ouer eor&eth;e. and tat swuch as hit is haue &yogh;iuen and &yogh;iue wile to &thorn;i seruise. Mi bodi henge wi&eth; &thorn;i bodi neiled o rode. sperred querfaste wi&eth; inne fowr wahes and henge i wile wi&eth; &thorn;e and neauer mare of mi rode cume til &thorn;at i deie. For &thorn;enne schal i lepen fra rode in to reste. fra wa to wele and to eche blisse A. ihesu swa swet hit is wi&eth; &thorn;e to henge. for hwen &thorn;at i seo o &thorn;e &thorn;at henges me biside; &thorn;e muchele swetnesse of &thorn;e; reaues me fele of pine. Bote swete ihesu hwat mai mi bodi a&yogh;aines tin for &yogh;if ich mihte a &thorn;usand fald &yogh;iue &thorn;e me seluen nere hit nowt onont te &thorn;at &yogh;ef &thorn;e seluen for me. And &yogh;et ich haue an heorte unwrest and unwur&eth;i and westi and poure of alle gode &thorn;eawes and tat swuch as hit is; tac hit to &thorn;e nu leue lif wi&eth; treowe luuenesse. and ne &thorn;ole me neauer nan o&eth;er &thorn;ing a&yogh;ain &thorn;i wille luuie for ne mai ich nowhwer mi luue bettre sette &thorn;en o &thorn;e ihesu crist &thorn;at bohtes hit swa dere. nis nan swa wur&eth;i to beo luued as tu swete ihesu &thorn;at in &thorn;e haues alle &thorn;ing hwer fore mon ah beo luuewur&eth;i to o&eth;er. &thorn;u art best wur&eth; mi luue &thorn;at for mi luue deidest. &yogh;ette &yogh;if &thorn;at i mi luue bede for to selle. and sette 
<PB REF="00000351.tif" N="287"> feor &thorn;er upon swa hehe swa ich eauer wile; &yogh;ette &thorn;u wult hit habbe and teken al &thorn;at tu haues &yogh;iuen; wil tu eke mare. and &yogh;if i &thorn;e riht luuie. wilt me crune in heuene wi&eth; &thorn;e self to rixlen werld in to werlde A ihesu swete ihesu mi luue. mi lef. mi lif. mi luue leuest &thorn;at swa muchel luuedes me &thorn;at tu deides for luue of me and fra &thorn;e world haues broht <MILESTONE UNIT="MS. Cotton Titus D. 18. folio" N="133">me. and ti spuse haues maked me. and al &thorn;i blisse haues heht me; leue &thorn;at te luue of &thorn;e beo al mi likinge.</P>
<P>Prei for me mi leue suster. &thorn;is haue i writen &thorn;e for &thorn;i &thorn;at wordes ofte quemen &thorn;e heorte to &thorn;enken on ure lauerd And for &thorn;i hwen &thorn;u art on eise carpe toward ihesu and seie &thorn;ise wordes. and &thorn;enc as tah he heng biside &thorn;e blodi up o rode. And he &thorn;urh his grace opn[e] &thorn;in heorte to his luue and to reow&eth;e of his pine.</P>
