<HEAD>APPENDIX III.</HEAD>
<HEAD>ROYAL MS. 17 A 27, FOL. 70.</HEAD>
<HEAD><I>Her cumse&eth; &thorn;e oreisun of seinte Marie.</I></HEAD>
<P><MILESTONE UNIT="ROYAL MS. 17 A 27 folio" N="70a">SWETE lefdi seinte marie meiden ouer meidnes &thorn;u bere &thorn;at blisfule bern. &thorn;e arerde mon cun &thorn;at wes adun ifallet &thorn;urh adames sunnen. ant &thorn;urh his hali passiun weorp &thorn;en deouel adun ant herehede helle. Ich a sari sunful &thorn;ing bidde &thorn;in are. &thorn;at tu beo mi motild a&yogh;eines mine sawle fan. &thorn;at ha hire ne bitellen. ah were me ant help me milzfule meiden. in alle mine neoden. ha habbe&eth; monie wunden o me nunan ifestnet. &thorn;e acwelle&eth; mi sawle bute &thorn;u beo mi leche. ich habbe ofte ibuhen to alle mine &thorn;reo fan. to &thorn;e feont.<MILESTONE UNIT="ROYAL MS. 17 A 27 folio" N="70b"> ant te &thorn;eo world. ant to mi flesches sunne. ich cnawe me schuldi. ant crie lefdi merci. for ich habbe imaket &yogh;eten of alle mine fif wittes to sunfule un&thorn;eawe. Misloket. Mishercnet. Misispeken. Misifelet. Misiliket swote smelles. prude ant wilnunge of pris me habbe&eth; sare iwundet. alswa wre&eth;&eth;e. ant onde. leasunsunge.<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> Missware. uuele halden treow&eth;e. cursunge. bacbitunge. ant fikelunge summe tide. ich habbe ihaued of o&eth;er monnes mid woh. ant wi&eth; unrihte. i&yogh;eue mis. iunne mis. ant ethalden ofte. spac to uuel. ant slaw to god. &yogh;emeles ant unlusti. sum time to pleiful to drupi oderhwiles. ich habbe isuneget in mete ant idrunch ba&eth;e. wi&eth; flesches ful&eth;e ifulet &thorn;at ich am ladliche ihurt ilicome ant isawle wi&eth; allescunes pinen of sunnen for<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. sor.</NOTE> &thorn;ah &thorn;e werc nere in &thorn;e bodi &thorn;e wil wes in &thorn;e heorte. al &thorn;is ich cnawlechi to &thorn;e swete lefdi seinte marie. hehest alre halehen. Nim mot for me ant were me. for ich am pine wur&eth;e. bisech for me &thorn;i milde sune Milce. Merci. are. for nawt ne mei he wernen &thorn;e; moder &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg">Or? &thorn;e.</NOTE> him bere. of alle &thorn;ine bisocnen. ich bidde ant biseche &thorn;e. ant halsi &yogh;ef me hahe&eth; hit. bi his flesch founge of &thorn;in edi bodi. bi his ibornesse. bi his edi uestunge i&thorn;e wildernesse. bi &thorn;e harde hurtes. ant te unwur&eth;e wohes &thorn;at he for us sunfule willeliche . . . . . <NOTE PLACE="end">[The rest is lacking.]</NOTE></P>
